{"type":"message","id":"a28b53c1","parentId":"883af8c0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou ler estes docs e sintetizar o que eles estão realmente a dizer sobre a arquitectura, especialmente a fronteira entre bloco legado funcional e partes onde OpenClaw faz sentido.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fd71f108190b77d8f5e1ad80132\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AGJuYxE4cnLQOuYiTs5yZlcn|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb1c81908609a4622a75ee1e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco1_agents_and_prompts.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco1_agents_and_prompts.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lZv20KVjjX81soy6iiWuGHn3|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb2c8190901229411067a8e1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco1_script_to_audio.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco1_script_to_audio.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_u7WwDFcc9wgkzJQZFDN9WdU0|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb34819099967c438c479fa3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco2_output_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco2_output_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0Qltp7CpgmsR3i4dq8y9QQoa|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb3881909ebe10caf65233ed","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco2_visual_production.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco2_visual_production.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_v9sMfFizhRRDsSGeTs25TtCC|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb408190997b8840c6bdd94e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco3_planners_and_config.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco3_planners_and_config.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SspXQbzeEcB02GLsuQojTFtg|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb448190b57e954ea88c69e7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\cfv3_blocs\\bloco3_video_assembly.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\cfv3_blocs\\\\bloco3_video_assembly.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qIVhXcCi1NbqXjYQvoy5064g|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb488190a07f0bf7084b0c3a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\v2_context.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\v2_context.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":493,"output":369,"cacheRead":36736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37598,"cost":{"input":0.0012325,"output":0.005535,"cacheRead":0.009184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0159515}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775140821546,"responseId":"resp_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fd661a081909c4be7791331f6db"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9136cb8a","parentId":"a28b53c1","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.889Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_AGJuYxE4cnLQOuYiTs5yZlcn|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb1c81908609a4622a75ee1e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 1 -- LLM Agents and Prompts Reference\n\n> **Scope**: This document covers all LLM/AI calls that occur during Bloco 1 (Script & Screenplay + TTS Generation) of the Content Factory V3 pipeline. It is written for migration planning -- every agent, prompt file, model, and integration point is catalogued so the target system can decide what to preserve, replace, or remove.\n>\n> **Date**: 2026-04-02\n> **Source**: Live production code in `content_factory_v3/`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Pipeline Overview -- Bloco 1 Steps\n\nBloco 1 runs inside each account's orchestrator (e.g., `orchestrator_002.py`). The steps are:\n\n| Step | Name | LLM Calls | Model |\n|------|------|-----------|-------|\n| 0 | Machine Config | None | -- |\n| 1 | Fetch Script | None (Google Sheets API) | -- |\n| 2 | Screenplay Analysis | **Screenplay Agent** (1 call per ~400-word batch) | GPT-4.1-mini via KMS or direct OpenAI |\n| 3 | TTS Generation | **TTS Polish Agent** (1 call per 6-chunk batch) | GPT-4.1-mini (direct OpenAI) |\n| 3 | TTS Generation | **TTS Polish Evaluator** (optional, 1 eval per batch) | GPT-4.1-mini (direct OpenAI) |\n| 3 | TTS Generation | **Narrator Gender Detector** (1 call per video) | GPT-4.1-mini |\n| 3 | TTS Generation | **TTS Safe Rewriter** (0-4 calls per blocked scene) | GPT-4.1-mini (direct OpenAI) |\n\nThe Gemini TTS audio generation call (Step 3 Phase 2) is NOT an LLM text call -- it uses `gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts` for speech synthesis. It is documented here only for completeness of the pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## 2. LLM Agents -- Detailed Inventory\n\n### 2.1 Screenplay Agent\n\n**What it does**: Divides the raw script (~1500-3000 words) into visual scenes of 19-57 words each, choosing scene boundaries at sentence endings based on faction changes, location changes, time jumps, and emotional tone shifts.\n\n**Agent location**: Not a standalone class. The LLM call is made directly in `orchestrator_002.py` method `_process_screenplay_batch()` (local mode) or via `ParallelScreenplayProcessor` (KMS mode).\n\n**Code files**:\n- `accounts/{NNN}/workflow/orchestrator_{NNN}.py` -- sequential batch processing\n- `shared/processors/parallel_screenplay.py` -- KMS parallel batch processing (async, `Semaphore(8)`)\n\n**Model**: `gpt-4.1-mini` (acquired via KMS `model_group` or direct OpenAI key)\n\n**Temperature**: 0.7\n\n**Response format**: `{\"type\": \"json_object\"}`\n\n**Timeout**: 600s (10 min) for local mode\n\n**Prompt files** (account-specific, per-language):\n```\naccounts/{NNN}/prompts/bloco1/{lang}/screenplay_agent_{NNN}_system.txt\n```\n\n**Accounts with bloco1 prompts**: 001, 002, 003 (and likely all active accounts)\n\n**Languages**: en, es, fr, de, it, pt, pl, ru, tr, ja, ko (varies per account)\n\n**Prompt structure** (using 002-en as canonical example):\n1. Role definition -- \"Master Screenwriter for War Documentation\"\n2. Visual Interpretation Spectrum -- literal / evocative / metaphorical / foreshadowing\n3. Scene division rules -- word count limits, sentence boundary requirement, merge/split criteria\n4. Account-specific context -- topic scope, style, narration perspective\n5. Output JSON format -- scene_number, text, word_count, scene_type, interpretation_mode, faction_shown, emotional_tone, reasoning\n6. Critical rules -- exact text preservation (zero tolerance), no duplication, no dropping\n7. Examples by interpretation mode\n\n**User prompt** (built dynamically in orchestrator):\n```\nVIDEO CONTEXT:\nTitle: {title}\nDescription: {description}\nLanguage: {language}\n\nTEXT TO DIVIDE INTO SCENES:\n{batch_text}\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Minimum words per scene: {min_words}\n- Maximum words per scene: {max_words}\n```\n\n**Retry strategy**: `tenacity` -- 3 attempts with exponential backoff (min=4s, max=10s)\n\n**Post-processing**: Python `SceneReconstructor` validates word count, sentence boundaries, and coverage (concatenated scene texts must match original input character-by-character).\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 TTS Polish Agent\n\n**What it does**: Optimizes text chunks for natural TTS narration -- expands abbreviations, handles ordinals/Roman numerals, corrects spelling, expands units of measurement. Critical rule: cardinal numbers MUST stay as digits (the TTS engine reads them correctly).\n\n**Agent class**: `shared/processors/tts_polish_agent.py` -- `TTSPolishAgent`\n\n**Model**: `gpt-4.1-mini` (direct OpenAI key from `.env`)\n\n**Temperature**: 0.4\n\n**Response format**: `{\"type\": \"json_object\"}`\n\n**Timeout**: 120s\n\n**Batch size**: 6 chunks per API call\n\n**Prompt files** (shared, per-language):\n```\nshared/prompts/tts_polish/tts_polish_{lang}_system.txt\n```\n\n**Languages with dedicated prompts** (13 total):\nen, pt, es, fr, de, it, tr, pl, ru, nl, ja, ko, ar\n\n**Prompt structure** (using EN as canonical):\n1. Role -- \"Expert in preparing ENGLISH text for TTS systems\"\n2. Mandatory rules -- no meaning changes, exact chunk count preservation\n3. Absolute prohibitions -- never add words not in original, never remove text\n4. Corrections to apply (priority order):\n   - Spelling correction (top priority)\n   - Abbreviation expansion (Dr. -> Doctor, Gen. -> General, etc.)\n   - **Numbers stay as digits ALWAYS** (critical rule, boxed emphasis)\n   - Ordinals and Roman numerals (16th -> sixteenth, Henry VIII -> Henry the Eighth)\n   - Time/date preservation (keep numeric format)\n   - Unit expansion (km -> kilometers, but number stays as digits)\n   - Alphanumeric equipment codes (M16 -> M sixteen, AK-47 -> A K forty-seven)\n   - Firearms/ammunition terminology\n   - International organization acronyms\n5. Checklist before returning\n6. Output JSON format: `{\"chunks\": [{\"index\": 0, \"text\": \"...\"}]}`\n\n**Additional prompt injection** (from account config):\n- `domain_context` -- appended as \"=== DOMAIN CONTEXT ===\" section\n- `protected_terms` -- appended as \"=== PROTECTED TERMS (DO NOT EXPAND) ===\" section\n\n**Retry strategy**: `tenacity` -- 3 attempts with exponential backoff\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 TTS Polish Evaluator (Optional)\n\n**What it does**: Evaluates the TTS Polish Agent output for quality -- detects hallucinations (added words), content deletions, numbers incorrectly converted to words, broken ordinals, equipment code errors, chunk count mismatches.\n\n**Agent class**: `shared/agents/evaluator_agent.py` -- `EvaluatorAgent`\n\n**Activation**: Controlled by `enable_evaluator` flag on TTSPolishAgent (default: disabled)\n\n**Model**: `gpt-4.1-mini` (direct OpenAI key)\n\n**Temperature**: 0.3\n\n**Response format**: `{\"type\": \"json_object\"}`\n\n**Score threshold**: 85/100 to pass\n\n**Max refinements**: 2 (configurable)\n\n**Prompt files**:\n```\nshared/prompts/evaluators/tts_polish/tts_polish_evaluator_{lang}_system.txt\n```\n\n**Languages with evaluator prompts** (12 total):\nen, pt, es, fr, de, it, tr, pl, ru, ar, ko, ja\n\n**Prompt structure** (using EN as canonical):\n1. Role -- \"Quality evaluator for ENGLISH TTS text optimization\"\n2. Consistency rule -- don't flag same text as both correct and incorrect\n3. Critical validations (auto-fail):\n   - Hallucination detection (word-by-word comparison)\n   - Content deletion detection (sentence count match)\n   - Number incorrectly converted to words (CRITICAL)\n   - Ordinal conversion validation\n   - Equipment model code validation\n   - Chunk count validation\n   - Time/date format preservation\n4. Standard validations (MAJOR): unexpanded abbreviations, unconverted ordinals\n5. Output JSON: score, passed, issues[], summary, refinement_needed, statistics\n6. Scoring: start at 100, -15 per critical, -5 per major, -2 per minor\n7. Evaluation examples with expected output\n\n**Refinement loop**: `shared/agents/refinement_loop.py` -- `RefinementLoop`\n- Generate -> Evaluate -> Refine cycle\n- Keeps best-scoring version across iterations\n- Only refines if score < 85 AND critical issues exist\n- Saves evaluation logs per batch\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 Narrator Gender Detector\n\n**What it does**: Single LLM call to classify the narrator as male or female based on textual cues (pronouns, relationship terms, gendered adjectives). Used to select appropriate TTS voice.\n\n**Agent class**: `shared/processors/narrator_gender_detector.py` -- `NarratorGenderDetector`\n\n**Model**: `gpt-4.1-mini`\n\n**Temperature**: 0.0 (deterministic)\n\n**Input**: First ~500 words of script text\n\n**System prompt** (hardcoded, not file-based):\n```\nYou are analyzing a first-person narrative script. Determine the gender of\nthe narrator based on textual cues: pronouns, relationship terms\n(\"my wife\"/\"my husband\", \"my mother told me\"), gendered adjectives\n(in Romance languages: \"cansado\"/\"cansada\", \"solo\"/\"sola\"), name mentions, etc.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object: {\"gender\": \"male\"} or {\"gender\": \"female\"}\n\nIf the text is ambiguous or provides no clear gender signal, default to \"male\".\n```\n\n**Output**: `{\"gender\": \"male\"}` or `{\"gender\": \"female\"}`\n\n**KMS support**: Yes -- uses `call_kms_text_json()` when key_manager is provided\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 TTS Safe Rewriter\n\n**What it does**: Rewrites text that was blocked by Gemini TTS content filters (PROHIBITED_CONTENT). Uses 4 progressive strategies with escalating conservatism.\n\n**Agent class**: `shared/processors/tts_safe_rewriter.py` -- `TTSSafeRewriter`\n\n**Model**: `gpt-4.1-mini` (direct OpenAI key)\n\n**Temperature**: (uses default from OpenAI client)\n\n**Prompt files**:\n```\nshared/prompts/tts_safe_rewriter/tts_safe_rewriter_{lang}_system.txt\n```\n\n**Languages** (13 total):\nen, es, de, fr, nl, it, ar, pl, ja, pt, ko, ru, tr\n\n**Fallback**: English prompt if language-specific file not found\n\n**4 Progressive strategies**:\n\n| Attempt | Strategy | Description |\n|---------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `soften_explicit` | Replace triggering terms with euphemisms (minimal changes) |\n| 2 | `indirect_narration` | Change perspective from direct to indirect (show reactions) |\n| 3 | `metaphorical` | Use metaphor and allusion instead of literal description |\n| 4 | `contextual_summary` | Dry historical facts only -- nuclear option, always passes |\n\n**Input JSON**:\n```json\n{\n  \"original_text\": \"The text that was blocked\",\n  \"attempt\": 1,\n  \"strategy\": \"soften_explicit\",\n  \"previous_attempts\": [],\n  \"scene_number\": 37,\n  \"language\": \"en\"\n}\n```\n\n**Output JSON**:\n```json\n{\n  \"safe_text\": \"The rewritten text\",\n  \"strategy_used\": \"soften_explicit\",\n  \"changes_made\": \"Brief description of changes\"\n}\n```\n\n**Key rules**:\n- Preserve length within +/- 15% of original (TTS must sync with video timing)\n- Preserve all proper nouns, dates, numbers\n- Numbers stay as digits\n- Never repeat a previous failed attempt\n- Each strategy is more conservative than the last\n\n**Commonly blocked terms** (from prompt): torture, execution, murder, blood, corpse, rape, child+violence, suicide, burning alive, drowning, starvation, plague, slavery, genocide\n\n**Retry strategy**: `tenacity` -- 3 attempts with exponential backoff (min=2s, max=8s)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Model Selection Summary\n\n| Agent | Model | Provider | Temperature | Via KMS? |\n|-------|-------|----------|-------------|----------|\n| Screenplay Agent | `gpt-4.1-mini` | OpenAI | 0.7 | Yes (parallel) or direct |\n| TTS Polish Agent | `gpt-4.1-mini` | OpenAI | 0.4 | No (direct key from .env) |\n| TTS Polish Evaluator | `gpt-4.1-mini` | OpenAI | 0.3 | No (direct key from .env) |\n| Narrator Gender Detector | `gpt-4.1-mini` | OpenAI | 0.0 | Yes (when key_manager provided) |\n| TTS Safe Rewriter | `gpt-4.1-mini` | OpenAI | default | No (direct key from .env) |\n| Gemini TTS (audio) | `gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts` | Google | -- | Yes |\n\nAll Bloco 1 LLM text calls use **GPT-4.1-mini** exclusively. There are no Gemini text calls in Bloco 1.\n\n---\n\n## 4. KMS Integration\n\n### 4.1 Key Manager Factory\n\n**File**: `shared/clients/key_manager_factory.py`\n\nDecision logic:\n1. If `key_management.enabled = true` in account YAML config:\n   - Create `KmsSyncClient` pointing at KMS Railway server\n   - Health check: `get_available_key_count(\"gemini-2.5-flash\")`\n   - If KMS unreachable and `fallback_to_local = true`: fall back to local `ApiKeyManager`\n2. If `key_management.enabled = false`:\n   - Use local `ApiKeyManager` (YAML-based key registry)\n\n### 4.2 KMS Sync Client\n\n**File**: `shared/clients/kms_client_sync.py` -- `KmsSyncClient`\n\n**Endpoints used**:\n- `POST /api/v1/acquire` -- get next API key (supports `model`, `model_group`, `exclude_tiers`)\n- `POST /api/v1/report` -- report success with token usage\n- `POST /api/v1/report-error` -- report error, get alternative key\n- `GET /api/v1/keys/available-count` -- health check\n\n**Acquire flow**:\n1. Send `{service, machine_id, model/model_group}` to KMS\n2. If response is `\"throttled\"`: sleep `wait_ms`, re-acquire\n3. If no keys: raise `NoKeysAvailableError` with `status` and `retry_after_ms`\n4. Return `api_key` string; cache `key_id`, `tier`, `model_id`, `provider` for reporting\n\n**Error reporting** enrichment fields: `agent_name`, `step_name`, `account_code`, `language`, `system_name`, `video_title`\n\n**call_with_resilience() helper**: acquire -> call -> report success/error -> retry with alternative key (max 2 retries). Content blocks (`ContentBlockedError`) are NOT retried.\n\n**HTTP retry**: 3 retries with exponential backoff (0.5s base) for connection/timeout errors against KMS server itself.\n\n**Model-to-service mapping**:\n```\ngemini-2.5-flash -> llm\ngemini-3-flash -> llm\ngpt-4.1-mini -> llm\ngemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts -> tts\ngemini-3.1-flash-image-preview -> image\n```\n\n### 4.3 Screenplay Agent KMS Path\n\nThe `ParallelScreenplayProcessor` uses `CentralizedKeyClient` (async version) with `Semaphore(8)` for up to 8 concurrent batches. Each batch:\n1. Async acquire key from KMS\n2. Create `AsyncOpenAI(api_key=key)` \n3. Call chat completion with screenplay system prompt\n4. Report success/error to KMS\n\n---\n\n## 5. Client Configuration\n\n### 5.1 OpenAI Client\n\n**File**: `shared/clients/openai_client.py` -- `OpenAIClient`\n\n- Default model: `gpt-4.1-mini`\n- API key: from `config.openai_api_key` (reads `OPENAI_API_KEY` from `.env`)\n- Supports account-specific prompt loading from `resources/prompts/agent_prompt_{account_id}_{lang}.txt`\n- Has a hardcoded Renaissance painting fallback prompt (used for legacy image prompt generation, NOT for Bloco 1)\n- `generate_segment_prompts()` -- used by Bloco 2 v1 (not Bloco 1)\n- `chat_completion()` / `create_completion()` -- generic methods used by various agents\n\n### 5.2 Gemini Client\n\n**File**: `shared/clients/gemini_client.py` -- `GeminiClient`\n\n- Default model: `gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview` (image generation only)\n- NOT used in Bloco 1 for text calls\n- Used in Bloco 2 for image generation\n- Supports reference images for character consistency\n- Client created via `genai_factory.py` which handles AI Studio vs Vertex AI routing\n\n### 5.3 GenAI Factory\n\n**File**: `shared/clients/genai_factory.py`\n\n- Creates `genai.Client` for either API key mode or Vertex AI (service account)\n- Model-to-location routing for Vertex AI endpoints\n- Thread-safe credential caching for service accounts\n- Handles backward compatibility with plain string keys, SimpleNamespace objects, and full KMS key_info dicts\n\n### 5.4 Config Singleton\n\n**File**: `shared/config.py` -- `Config`\n\n- Priority: `machine_config.yaml` > `.env` > hardcoded defaults\n- Machine-specific: service URLs (XTTS, WhisperX, ComfyUI), paths, hardware config\n- Shared: API keys from `.env` (`OPENAI_API_KEY`)\n- Supports dot-notation nested access: `config.get(\"services.alltalk.url\")`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cost Profile (Per Video)\n\nApproximate token usage for a typical video (~2000 words script, ~50 scenes):\n\n| Agent | Calls | Input tokens/call | Output tokens/call | Total tokens | Est. cost |\n|-------|-------|-------------------|-------------------|--------------|-----------|\n| Screenplay Agent | ~5 batches | ~2,000 | ~1,500 | ~17,500 | ~$0.007 |\n| TTS Polish Agent | ~9 batches (6 chunks each) | ~1,500 | ~500 | ~18,000 | ~$0.007 |\n| TTS Polish Evaluator | 0-9 (if enabled) | ~2,000 | ~800 | ~0-25,200 | $0-$0.010 |\n| Narrator Gender Detector | 1 | ~600 | ~10 | ~610 | ~$0.0002 |\n| TTS Safe Rewriter | 0-8 (content-dependent) | ~1,000 | ~300 | ~0-10,400 | $0-$0.004 |\n\n**Typical Bloco 1 total**: ~36,000-71,000 tokens per video, ~$0.014-$0.028\n\n**GPT-4.1-mini pricing** (as of Mar 2026): $0.40/1M input, $1.60/1M output\n\nNotes:\n- Evaluator is typically disabled in production (low ROI vs cost)\n- TTS Safe Rewriter calls are rare (only triggered by Gemini content blocks)\n- Screenplay batches can run in parallel via KMS (wall-clock time: ~10-15s vs ~60s sequential)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Fallback Chains\n\n### 7.1 Screenplay Agent\n\n```\nKMS parallel (8 concurrent batches, any available OpenAI key)\n  -> KMS alternative key on 429/error\n    -> Exhaust all KMS keys: NoKeysAvailableError -> pipeline stops\n    \nLocal sequential (single OpenAI key from .env)\n  -> tenacity 3 retries with exponential backoff\n    -> Exhaust retries: Exception -> pipeline stops\n```\n\n### 7.2 TTS Polish Agent\n\n```\nDirect OpenAI key (from .env)\n  -> tenacity 3 retries with exponential backoff\n    -> If evaluator enabled and score < 85 with critical issues:\n      -> Refine with feedback (up to 2 refinements)\n        -> Keep best-scoring version\n    -> Exhaust retries: Exception -> pipeline stops\n```\n\n### 7.3 Narrator Gender Detector\n\n```\nKMS mode: call_kms_text_json() with resilience\n  -> On failure: returns \"male\" (safe default)\n\nDirect mode: single OpenAI call\n  -> On failure: returns \"male\" (safe default)\n```\n\n### 7.4 TTS Safe Rewriter\n\n```\nStrategy 1: soften_explicit\n  -> Gemini TTS retry -> still blocked?\nStrategy 2: indirect_narration\n  -> Gemini TTS retry -> still blocked?\nStrategy 3: metaphorical\n  -> Gemini TTS retry -> still blocked?\nStrategy 4: contextual_summary (always passes)\n  -> Gemini TTS retry -> still blocked?\n    -> PermanentBlockError -> pipeline stops for this scene\n```\n\n### 7.5 Key Manager Factory\n\n```\nKMS enabled + reachable -> KmsSyncClient\nKMS enabled + unreachable + fallback_to_local=true -> local ApiKeyManager\nKMS enabled + unreachable + fallback_to_local=false -> RuntimeError\nKMS disabled -> local ApiKeyManager\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Prompt File Inventory\n\n### Account-Specific (Bloco 1)\n\nPattern: `accounts/{NNN}/prompts/bloco1/{lang}/screenplay_agent_{NNN}_system.txt`\n\n| Account | Languages |\n|---------|-----------|\n| 001_dark_forensics | de, fr, pt |\n| 002_wars_and_conquer | en, es, fr, de, it, pt, pl, ru, tr, ja, ko |\n| 003_wwii_photography | en, es, fr, de, it, pt, pl, ru, tr, ja, ko (likely) |\n| Others | Similar pattern |\n\n### Shared (Language-Specific)\n\n| Prompt Set | Path Pattern | Count |\n|------------|-------------|-------|\n| TTS Polish | `shared/prompts/tts_polish/tts_polish_{lang}_system.txt` | 13 |\n| TTS Polish Evaluator | `shared/prompts/evaluators/tts_polish/tts_polish_evaluator_{lang}_system.txt` | 12 |\n| TTS Safe Rewriter | `shared/prompts/tts_safe_rewriter/tts_safe_rewriter_{lang}_system.txt` | 13 |\n\n### Hardcoded (No File)\n\n| Agent | Location |\n|-------|----------|\n| Narrator Gender Detector | `shared/processors/narrator_gender_detector.py` (SYSTEM_PROMPT constant) |\n| Evaluator fallback | `shared/agents/evaluator_agent.py` (`_get_fallback_prompt()`) |\n| TTS Polish fallback | `shared/processors/tts_polish_agent.py` (`_get_fallback_prompt()`) |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Migration Notes\n\n### What to Preserve\n\n1. **Screenplay Agent prompts** -- These are heavily tuned per-account, per-language. The prompt for 002-en alone is 388 lines. The scene division logic (faction changes, word count limits, interpretation modes) is critical to video quality. These prompts should be migrated as-is.\n\n2. **TTS Polish prompts** -- The number-handling rules (keep as digits, except ordinals/Roman numerals) are specific to Gemini TTS behavior. If the target TTS engine differs, these rules need re-evaluation.\n\n3. **TTS Safe Rewriter prompts** -- The 4-strategy progressive escalation and blocked-term tables are tuned to Gemini TTS content filters. If moving to a different TTS engine, these may become unnecessary.\n\n### What Could Change\n\n1. **Model choice** -- All Bloco 1 text calls use GPT-4.1-mini. This could potentially be replaced with a cheaper/faster model for TTS Polish (low-complexity text transformation) while keeping GPT-4.1-mini for Screenplay (higher creative reasoning required).\n\n2. **KMS vs direct keys** -- The TTS Polish Agent and TTS Safe Rewriter use direct OpenAI keys from `.env` while the Screenplay Agent uses KMS. This inconsistency could be unified.\n\n3. **Evaluator** -- The TTS Polish Evaluator is typically disabled in production. If the TTS Polish quality is consistently high, it can be removed entirely to save tokens.\n\n### Dependencies on Other Systems\n\n- **Google Sheets API** -- Script fetching (Step 1)\n- **Gemini TTS** -- Audio generation (Step 3, Phase 2) -- triggers TTS Safe Rewriter when content is blocked\n- **AllTalk/XTTS** -- Legacy TTS engine (still supported via `tts_engine` config)\n- **WhisperX** -- Audio validation (Step 3, Phase 3)\n- **KMS Railway server** -- Key management for parallel processing\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829877}}
{"type":"message","id":"67c771b0","parentId":"9136cb8a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.905Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_lZv20KVjjX81soy6iiWuGHn3|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb2c8190901229411067a8e1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 1: Script to Audio Pipeline\n\n> Content Factory V3 -- Production Documentation\n> Last updated: 2026-04-02\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nBloco 1 transforms a raw script into per-scene audio clips with validated transcriptions. It is the foundational block of the Content Factory V3 pipeline -- Bloco 2 (images) and Bloco 3 (video composition) both depend on its outputs.\n\n**End-to-end flow:**\n\n```\nRaw Script (Google Sheets)\n  -> Clean + Language-Specific Formatting (Python, deterministic)\n  -> Scene Division (GPT-4.1-mini, batched)\n  -> Scene Reconstruction (Python, deterministic auto-fix)\n  -> TTS Polish (GPT-4.1-mini, batched)\n  -> Text-to-Speech (Gemini TTS API or ElevenLabs)\n  -> Silence Trimming (pydub/FFmpeg, deterministic)\n  -> Loudness Normalization (pydub, deterministic)\n  -> NISQA Audio Quality Gate (GPU, deterministic)\n  -> WhisperX Transcription Validation (GPU, deterministic)\n  -> Per-scene MP3 clips + word timestamps + metadata JSON\n```\n\n**Supported languages (12):** en, pt, es, fr, de, it, tr, pl, ru, nl, ja, ko\n\n**Two execution modes:**\n- **KMS Parallel** (production): All batches/scenes processed concurrently via KMS key pool\n- **Local Sequential** (fallback): One batch/scene at a time, local API keys\n\n---\n\n## 2. Entry Point\n\nBloco 1 is invoked from per-account orchestrators. Each account (001-013) has its own orchestrator file that inherits the same pattern.\n\n**Representative entry point:**\n```\ncontent_factory_v3/accounts/003_wwii_photography/workflow/orchestrator_003.py\n```\n\n**CLI invocation:**\n```bash\npython -m accounts.003_wwii_photography.workflow.orchestrator_003 --language en --steps 0-3\n```\n\n**Queue system (production):**\n```bash\npython -m queue_cli add 003 en --steps 0-3\npython -m queue_cli run\n```\n\n**Class:** `Orchestrator003` (each account has its own `Orchestrator_NNN`)\n\n**Bloco 1 spans steps 0-3:**\n| Step | Method | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| 0 | `step_00_load_config()` | Load machine config, validate services |\n| 1 | `step_01_fetch_script()` | Fetch script from Google Sheets (or use provided text) |\n| 2 | `step_02_screenplay_analysis()` | Divide script into scenes via GPT + Python auto-fix |\n| 3 | `step_03_generate_audio()` | Per-scene TTS + validation pipeline |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pipeline Steps (Detailed)\n\n### Step 0: Load Config (`step_00_load_config`)\n\n**File:** Per-account orchestrator (e.g., `orchestrator_003.py` line 460)\n\n**Action:** Loads machine configuration from the V3 config singleton. Validates that required services (AllTalk, WhisperX, ComfyUI) are reachable via health check endpoints.\n\n**Data flow:**\n- Input: `machine_config.yaml` (auto-detected per machine)\n- Output: `Dict` with `machine_id`, `services` status, `paths`\n\n**No LLM calls. Deterministic.**\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Fetch Script (`step_01_fetch_script`)\n\n**File:** Per-account orchestrator (line 520)\n\n**Action:** Fetches the next available script from Google Sheets, sets its status to \"processing\" (atomic lock), and saves it locally. Alternatively, accepts script content directly via constructor argument.\n\n**Data flow:**\n- Input: Google Sheet ID from YAML config (`sheet_scripts_id`, `sheet_scripts_name`)\n- Output: `script.txt` saved to video directory + checkpoint `01_script_fetched`\n\n**Output dict:**\n```python\n{\n    \"title\": str,          # Video title from sheet\n    \"description\": str,    # Video description (emojis stripped)\n    \"script\": str,         # Raw script text\n    \"chars\": int,          # Character count\n    \"words\": int,          # Word count\n    \"row_number\": int,     # Row in Google Sheet (for tracking)\n    \"source\": \"google_sheets\" | \"provided\"\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies:** `shared.clients.google_sheets.GoogleSheetsClient`\n\n**No LLM calls. Deterministic (I/O only).**\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Screenplay Analysis (`step_02_screenplay_analysis`)\n\n**File:** Per-account orchestrator (line 638) + `shared/processors/parallel_screenplay.py` + `shared/processors/scene_reconstructor.py`\n\n**Action:** Divides the full script into scenes of controlled word count. Two sub-steps:\n\n#### 2a. Batch Extraction (Deterministic)\n\nThe script is split into batches of ~400 words at sentence boundaries. Function: `_extract_text_batches(text, max_words=400)`. CJK languages use character count and split on full-width punctuation.\n\n#### 2b. Screenplay Agent (LLM)\n\nEach batch is sent to GPT-4.1-mini to split into scenes. Two paths:\n\n**KMS Parallel path** (production):\n- Class: `ParallelScreenplayProcessor` (`shared/processors/parallel_screenplay.py`)\n- All batches sent concurrently with `Semaphore(8)`\n- Key acquisition via `CentralizedKeyClient` (async KMS)\n- Model: `gpt-4.1-mini`, temperature 0.4, JSON response format\n- Timeout: 120s per call\n\n**Local Sequential path** (fallback):\n- Uses `OpenAIClient` directly\n- One batch at a time\n\n**Agent input format:**\n```json\n{\n    \"input_type\": \"TEXT_BATCH\",\n    \"batch_number\": 1,\n    \"total_batches\": 3,\n    \"video_context\": {\"title\": \"...\", \"description\": \"...\", \"language\": \"en\"},\n    \"data\": {\"text\": \"batch text...\", \"word_count\": 380},\n    \"constraints\": {\n        \"min_words_per_scene\": 14,\n        \"max_words_per_scene\": 52,\n        \"counting_unit\": \"words\",\n        \"start_scene_number\": 1\n    },\n    \"feedback\": null\n}\n```\n\n**Agent output format:**\n```json\n{\n    \"scenes\": [\n        {\n            \"scene_number\": 1,\n            \"text\": \"Scene text...\",\n            \"word_count\": 35,\n            \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\n            \"faction_shown\": \"allied\",\n            \"interpretation_mode\": \"literal\",\n            \"emotional_tone\": \"somber\",\n            \"reasoning\": \"...\"\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n**System prompt:** Per-account, per-language file at `accounts/NNN/prompts/bloco1/{lang}/screenplay_agent_NNN_system.txt`\n\n#### 2c. Scene Reconstruction (Deterministic)\n\n**File:** `shared/processors/scene_reconstructor.py`\n\n**Function:** `reconstruct_scenes(scenes, original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language)`\n\nAfter the LLM returns scenes, this pure-Python processor validates and auto-fixes them. Zero LLM retries.\n\n**Three paths:**\n1. **passthrough** -- Text matches original AND all word counts in range. Just renumber sequentially.\n2. **match_fix** -- Text matches original BUT some word counts violate limits. Redistributes whole sentences between adjacent scenes (up to 10 passes). Falls back to path 3 if redistribution fails.\n3. **reconstruct** -- Text corrupted/mismatched. Rebuilds ALL scenes from scratch using greedy sentence distribution targeting `(min + max) / 2` words per scene, then applies word count fixes.\n\n**CJK support:** Uses character count instead of word count for `ja`/`ko`. Splits on full-width punctuation (`\\u3002\\uff01\\uff1f`).\n\n**Output:** `(fixed_scenes: List[Dict], report: Dict)` where report contains `path`, `changes_made`, `original_scene_count`, `final_scene_count`.\n\n#### 2d. Coverage Validation (Deterministic)\n\n**File:** `shared/processors/scene_text_validator.py`\n\n**Function:** `validate_scene_text(scenes, original_text)`\n\nChecks: empty scenes, duplicate text, missing text (>10% threshold), sequential scene numbers. Returns `(True, None)` or `(False, feedback_dict)`.\n\n**File:** `shared/processors/scene_word_count_checker.py`\n\n**Function:** `check_scene_word_counts(scenes, min_words, max_words, tolerance=3, language)`\n\nPre-check for word count violations with a tolerance of +/-3 words. Generates specific MERGE/SPLIT feedback per scene.\n\n**Note:** In the current production flow, `scene_reconstructor.py` has replaced most uses of the text validator and word count checker as retry mechanisms. These validators may still be used for diagnostic logging.\n\n**Final output saved to:** `{video_dir}/screenplay_analysis.json`\n```json\n{\n    \"total_scenes\": 25,\n    \"scenes\": [ ... ],\n    \"batches_processed\": 3,\n    \"language\": \"en\"\n}\n```\n\n**Checkpoint:** `02_screenplay_analyzed`\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Generate Audio (`step_03_generate_audio`)\n\n**File:** Per-account orchestrator (line 1280) + `shared/processors/parallel_tts.py`\n\n**Action:** For each scene, generates TTS audio, validates quality, and produces final MP3 clips with WhisperX transcriptions.\n\nTwo dispatch paths based on config:\n\n#### KMS Parallel Path (Production)\n\n**Class:** `ParallelTTSProcessor` (`shared/processors/parallel_tts.py`)\n\nThree-phase architecture:\n\n##### Phase 1: TTS Polish (Batched Parallel, LLM)\n\n- Groups scenes into batches of 3 (`POLISH_BATCH_SIZE = 3`)\n- All batches run concurrently with `Semaphore(15)`\n- Model: `gpt-4.1-mini` via OpenAI, temperature 0.4\n- Each batch gets its own API call via `CentralizedKeyClient`\n\n**Pre-processing:** Each scene text is first run through `TextNormalizer.normalize()` (numbers to words, abbreviations, currency, units -- deterministic).\n\n**Polish prompt:** Per-language file at `shared/prompts/tts_polish/tts_polish_{lang}_system.txt`. Domain context and protected terms from YAML config are appended.\n\n**Input/output format:**\n```json\n// Input\n[{\"index\": 0, \"text\": \"...\"}, {\"index\": 1, \"text\": \"...\"}, {\"index\": 2, \"text\": \"...\"}]\n\n// Output\n{\"chunks\": [{\"index\": 0, \"text\": \"polished...\"}, ...]}\n```\n\n**Resume support:** Polished texts cached to `{clips_dir}/polished_texts.json`. If the file exists and has the correct count, Phase 1 is skipped.\n\n##### Phase 2: Gemini TTS (Parallel, API)\n\n- All pending scenes generated concurrently with `Semaphore(TTS_CONCURRENCY_CAP=3)`\n- Each scene has a 15-minute timeout loop (`TTS_SCENE_TIMEOUT = 900s`)\n- Key acquisition via `KmsSyncClient.get_next_key()` for model `gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts`\n- Client created via `genai_factory.create_genai_client()` (supports both API key and Service Account auth)\n\n**TTS API call:**\n```python\nclient.models.generate_content(\n    model=\"gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts\",\n    contents=text,\n    config=GenerateContentConfig(\n        response_modalities=[\"AUDIO\"],\n        speech_config=SpeechConfig(\n            language_code=\"en-US\",  # from LANGUAGE_CODE_MAP\n            voice_config=VoiceConfig(\n                prebuilt_voice_config=PrebuiltVoiceConfig(voice_name=\"Charon\")\n            )\n        ),\n    ),\n)\n```\n\n**Output format:** Raw PCM (24kHz, 16-bit, mono) converted to WAV via `_pcm_to_wav()`.\n\n**Each clip saved immediately to disk:** `{clips_dir}/clip_{NNN}_raw.wav` (crash recovery).\n\n**Resume support:** If `clip_NNN_raw.wav` already exists and is >1000 bytes, the scene is skipped.\n\n**Content block handling (inline safe rewriting):**\n- `PROHIBITED_CONTENT` finish reason -> immediate safe rewrite (key is healthy)\n- `EMPTY_RESPONSE` -> inferred content block\n- 5 keys fail with same prompt (`KEYS_BEFORE_REWRITE = 5`) -> suspected content block\n- Safe rewrite uses 4 progressive strategies:\n  1. `soften_explicit` -- Replace triggering terms with euphemisms\n  2. `indirect_narration` -- Change perspective\n  3. `metaphorical` -- Use metaphors\n  4. `contextual_summary` -- Reformulate as historical context\n- GPT-4.1-mini via KMS for rewriting, with template-based regex fallback\n- After `MAX_SAFE_REWRITES = 4` levels exhausted -> `PermanentBlockError` (pipeline stops)\n\n**If ANY scene fails, the entire pipeline STOPS.** This is a hard requirement.\n\n##### Phase 3: GPU Validation (Sequential)\n\nFor each scene (sequentially, GPU-bound):\n\n1. **Silence Trimming** (`_trim_silence_pydub`): Detects silences >1000ms at -40dB, keeps max 500ms. Uses pydub in-memory.\n\n2. **Loudness Normalization** (`AudioProcessor.normalize_loudness`): Target -16.0 dBFS.\n\n3. **NISQA Quality Gate** (`AudioQualityGate.analyze`):\n   - Model: `NonIntrusiveSpeechQualityAssessment` from torchmetrics (runs on GPU)\n   - Checks: MOS, noisiness, discontinuity, coloration, loudness, z-score\n   - Language-specific thresholds (calibrated from human curation of 72 speakers)\n   - If `needs_regeneration`: regenerate clip via sync KMS client, re-validate\n   - Max retries: `MAX_QG_RETRIES = 3`\n   - Best-effort fallback: uses highest MOS attempt if all retries fail\n\n4. **WhisperX Transcription** (`WhisperXService.transcribe`):\n   - Sends audio to local WhisperX API endpoint\n   - Returns `TranscriptionData` with segments, word timings, duration\n\n5. **Transcription Validation** (`TranscriptionValidator.validate`):\n   - Compares polished text against WhisperX transcription\n   - Uses `SequenceMatcher` (autojunk=False) for match ratio\n   - Language-specific thresholds: EN=60%, PT=75%, DE=65%, etc.\n   - Filters number words and known TTS Polish bugs from comparison\n   - Additional check: >5 extra words -> invalid (catches hallucinations)\n   - If invalid: regenerate clip, re-validate\n   - Max retries: `MAX_PIPELINE_RETRIES = 3`\n   - Best-effort fallback: uses highest match_ratio attempt\n\n6. **Export**: Final audio exported as MP3. Raw WAV deleted. Per-clip WhisperX JSON saved.\n\n**Resume support for Phase 3:** If `clip_NNN.mp3` AND `clip_NNN_whisperx.json` both exist, the scene is skipped.\n\n#### Local Sequential Path (Fallback)\n\nUsed when `key_management.enabled` is false OR `tts_engine` is \"alltalk\".\n\nSame per-scene pipeline but executed one scene at a time via `_generate_scene_audio()`. Uses local API keys for Gemini TTS (via `ApiKeyManager` + `api_keys_registry_tts.yaml`) or AllTalk for local GPU TTS.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Flow Summary\n\n```\nGoogle Sheet Row\n  |\n  v\nstep_01: script.txt (raw text)\n  |\n  v\nstep_02: _extract_text_batches() -> batches[] (~400 words each)\n  |\n  v\nstep_02: GPT-4.1-mini (per batch) -> raw scenes[]\n  |\n  v\nstep_02: reconstruct_scenes() -> fixed scenes[] (deterministic auto-fix)\n  |\n  v\nstep_02: screenplay_analysis.json\n  |\n  v\nstep_03 Phase 1: TextNormalizer.normalize() -> normalized text\n  |\n  v\nstep_03 Phase 1: GPT-4.1-mini TTS Polish (3 scenes/call) -> polished text\n  |\n  v\nstep_03 Phase 2: Gemini TTS API -> clip_NNN_raw.wav (PCM->WAV, 24kHz mono)\n  |                (on content block: GPT-4.1-mini safe rewrite -> retry)\n  v\nstep_03 Phase 3: pydub silence trim -> loudness normalize -> NISQA QG\n  |                (on QG fail: regenerate + retry)\n  v\nstep_03 Phase 3: WhisperX transcribe -> TranscriptionValidator\n  |                (on validation fail: regenerate + retry)\n  v\nclip_NNN.mp3 + clip_NNN_whisperx.json + clips_metadata.json + tts_validation.json\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Input Contract\n\n### Script Source\n\n**From Google Sheets:**\n- Sheet ID: `sheet_scripts_id` in YAML config\n- Sheet name: `sheet_scripts_name` (default: \"Scripts\" or \"Pagina1\")\n- Expected columns: title, description, script text, status\n- Status \"to do\" -> locked to \"processing\" on fetch\n\n**Direct input:**\n```python\norchestrator = Orchestrator003(language=\"en\", video_name=\"test\", script_content=\"full script text here\")\n```\n\n### YAML Config Fields Used by Bloco 1\n\n```yaml\nlanguage: \"en\"\n\nscreenplay_agent:\n  enabled: true\n  batch_size: 20          # (legacy, not used in current flow)\n  min_words: 19           # Overrides LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS\n  max_words: 57           # Overrides LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS\n  prompt: \"screenplay_agent_003_system.txt\"\n\ntts_engine: \"gemini\"      # \"gemini\" or \"alltalk\"\ngemini_voice: \"Charon\"    # Gemini TTS voice name\n\ntts_polish:\n  domain_context: \"World War II military history channel...\"\n  protected_terms:\n    - \"Wehrmacht\"\n    - \"Luftwaffe\"\n    # ... terms that must NOT be expanded by TTS Polish\n\nkey_management:\n  enabled: true\n  kms_url: \"https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app\"\n  machine_id: \"M1\"\n  fallback_to_local: true\n\nsheet_scripts_id: \"...\"\nsheet_scripts_name: \"Pagina1\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Output Contract\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\naccounts/003_wwii_photography/output/{language}/{video_name}/\n  script.txt                         # Raw script\n  screenplay_analysis.json           # Scenes with metadata\n  clips/\n    polished_texts.json              # Phase 1 cache (list of polished strings)\n    clip_001.mp3                     # Final per-scene audio\n    clip_002.mp3\n    ...\n    clip_001_whisperx.json           # Per-clip WhisperX transcription\n    clip_002_whisperx.json\n    ...\n    tts_validation.json              # Progressive validation log (all scenes)\n  clips_metadata.json                # Full metadata for all clips\n  logs/\n    tts_safe_rewriter_report.json    # Safe rewrite events (if any)\n    screenplay_validation_batch_N.json  # Per-batch reconstruction diagnostics\n  checkpoints/\n    01_script_fetched.json\n    02_screenplay_analyzed.json\n    03_audio_generated.json\n```\n\n### screenplay_analysis.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"total_scenes\": 25,\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_number\": 1,\n      \"text\": \"Scene narration text...\",\n      \"word_count\": 35,\n      \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\n      \"faction_shown\": \"allied\",\n      \"interpretation_mode\": \"literal\",\n      \"emotional_tone\": \"somber\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"batches_processed\": 3,\n  \"language\": \"en\"\n}\n```\n\n### clips_metadata.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"total_scenes\": 25,\n  \"successful_clips\": 25,\n  \"failed_clips\": 0,\n  \"clips\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_number\": 1,\n      \"clip_name\": \"clip_001\",\n      \"path\": \"clips/clip_001.mp3\",\n      \"duration_ms\": 8500,\n      \"original_text\": \"Scene text from screenplay...\",\n      \"polished_text\": \"Polished scene text for TTS...\",\n      \"quality_gate\": {\n        \"status\": \"passed\",\n        \"mos\": 3.85\n      },\n      \"whisperx\": {\n        \"transcribed_text\": \"WhisperX transcription...\",\n        \"match_ratio\": 0.92,\n        \"is_valid\": true\n      },\n      \"used_best_effort\": false,\n      \"word_timestamps\": [\n        {\"word\": \"The\", \"start\": 0.0, \"end\": 0.12},\n        {\"word\": \"war\", \"start\": 0.15, \"end\": 0.38}\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"failures\": []\n}\n```\n\n### clip_NNN_whisperx.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scene_number\": 1,\n  \"polished_text\": \"Polished text...\",\n  \"total_duration\": 8.5,\n  \"word_count\": 35,\n  \"full_transcript\": \"WhisperX full transcript...\",\n  \"segments\": [\n    {\n      \"start\": 0.0,\n      \"end\": 4.2,\n      \"text\": \"Segment text...\",\n      \"words\": [\n        {\"word\": \"The\", \"start\": 0.0, \"end\": 0.12},\n        {\"word\": \"war\", \"start\": 0.15, \"end\": 0.38}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. LLM Calls\n\n| Step | Agent | Model | Provider | Calls per Video | Purpose |\n|------|-------|-------|----------|----------------|---------|\n| 2 | Screenplay Agent | gpt-4.1-mini | OpenAI via KMS | ~3-5 (one per batch) | Split script into scenes |\n| 3 Phase 1 | TTS Polish | gpt-4.1-mini | OpenAI via KMS | ~8-10 (3 scenes per call) | Optimize text for TTS |\n| 3 Phase 2 | Safe Rewriter | gpt-4.1-mini | OpenAI via KMS | 0-4 per blocked scene | Rewrite content-blocked text |\n\n**Total LLM calls per video:** ~11-15 (normal), up to ~25 with content blocks.\n\n**All LLM calls use:**\n- Temperature: 0.3-0.4\n- Response format: `json_object`\n- Timeout: 120s\n- Key management: via KMS `CentralizedKeyClient` (async) or `KmsSyncClient` (sync)\n\n**Prompt files:**\n- Screenplay: `accounts/NNN/prompts/bloco1/{lang}/screenplay_agent_NNN_system.txt`\n- TTS Polish: `shared/prompts/tts_polish/tts_polish_{lang}_system.txt`\n- Safe Rewriter: `shared/prompts/tts_safe_rewriter/tts_safe_rewriter_{lang}_system.txt`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Deterministic Steps\n\n| Step | Component | File | What it Does |\n|------|-----------|------|-------------|\n| 1 | Script cleaning | `script_processor.py` | Remove special chars, normalize whitespace |\n| 1 | Language formatting | `script_processor.py` | PT/IT semicolon formatting, alphanumeric normalization, time/BC-AD/abbreviation expansion |\n| 2 | Batch extraction | Orchestrator `_extract_text_batches()` | Split script into ~400-word batches at sentence boundaries |\n| 2 | Scene reconstruction | `scene_reconstructor.py` | Auto-fix word counts, rebuild corrupted scenes |\n| 2 | Text validation | `scene_text_validator.py` | Check coverage, duplicates, missing text |\n| 2 | Word count check | `scene_word_count_checker.py` | Pre-check word count violations |\n| 3 | Text normalization | `text_normalizer.py` | Numbers to words, abbreviations, currencies (11 languages) |\n| 3 | PCM to WAV | `parallel_tts.py` `_pcm_to_wav()` | Convert raw PCM bytes to WAV format |\n| 3 | Silence trimming | `silence_trimmer.py` / `parallel_tts._trim_silence_pydub()` | Detect and trim >2s pauses to 1s |\n| 3 | Loudness normalization | `audio_processor.py` `normalize_loudness()` | Target -16 dBFS |\n| 3 | NISQA Quality Gate | `audio_quality_gate.py` | GPU-based audio quality assessment |\n| 3 | WhisperX transcription | `whisperx_service.py` | Local GPU transcription with word timings |\n| 3 | Transcription validation | `transcription_validator.py` | Match ratio + WER comparison |\n| 3 | Template safe rewrite | `parallel_tts._template_safe_rewrite()` | Regex-based word replacement fallback |\n\n---\n\n## 9. External Services\n\n| Service | Usage | Endpoint | Auth |\n|---------|-------|----------|------|\n| **OpenAI API** (GPT-4.1-mini) | Screenplay, TTS Polish, Safe Rewrite | `api.openai.com` | API key via KMS (`CentralizedKeyClient`) |\n| **Gemini TTS API** | Text-to-Speech generation | Google `genai` SDK | API key or Service Account via KMS |\n| **ElevenLabs API** | TTS for PT/ES (account 011) | `api.elevenlabs.io` | `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` env var |\n| **KMS Server** | Key acquisition, cooldowns, cost tracking | `https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app` | Machine ID |\n| **WhisperX** | Audio transcription + word alignment | Local HTTP API (port varies) | None (local service) |\n| **AllTalk** | Legacy local TTS (fallback) | Local HTTP API | None (local service) |\n| **Google Sheets** | Script fetching, status tracking | Google Sheets API | Service account credentials |\n| **Service Controller** | Start/stop AllTalk and WhisperX | Local HTTP API | None (local service) |\n\n### KMS Integration Details\n\n**Key acquisition flow:**\n1. `CentralizedKeyClient.call_with_resilience(model, call_fn)` (async) or `KmsSyncClient.get_next_key(model)` (sync)\n2. KMS returns `key_info` with `api_key` or `sa_filename + vertex_project_id`\n3. `genai_factory.create_genai_client(key_info, model)` creates the appropriate client\n4. On success: `report_success(key_id, model, tokens, ...)`\n5. On error: `report_error(key_id, model, error, ...)` (except content blocks)\n\n**Content blocks are NOT reported to KMS** -- the key is healthy, only the text content is problematic.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Error Handling\n\n### Screenplay (Step 2)\n\n| Failure | Handling |\n|---------|----------|\n| GPT returns malformed JSON | Exception propagated, step fails |\n| Word counts out of range | `scene_reconstructor` auto-fixes (deterministic) |\n| Text corrupted/missing | `scene_reconstructor` rebuilds from original text |\n| KMS no keys available | Async retry with backoff (KMS provides `retry_after_ms`) |\n\n### TTS (Step 3)\n\n| Failure | Handling |\n|---------|----------|\n| Gemini 429 (rate limit) | Rotate to next key via KMS, retry within 15-min timeout |\n| Gemini PROHIBITED_CONTENT | Immediate safe rewrite (4 progressive strategies) |\n| Gemini EMPTY_RESPONSE | After 2 rounds through all keys -> infer content block -> safe rewrite |\n| Gemini HARD_TIMEOUT (>160s) | Kill hung call, rotate to next key |\n| KMS no keys available | Wait `retry_after_ms`, retry within 15-min per-scene timeout |\n| Safe rewrite exhausted (4 levels) | `PermanentBlockError` -> pipeline STOPS |\n| NISQA quality fail | Regenerate clip (up to 3 attempts), then best-effort fallback |\n| WhisperX validation fail | Regenerate clip (up to 3 attempts), then best-effort fallback |\n| ANY scene fails completely | `RuntimeError` -> entire step 3 aborts |\n\n### Retry Constants\n\n```python\nMAX_PIPELINE_RETRIES = 3       # Full pipeline retries per scene (regen + revalidate)\nMAX_QG_RETRIES = 3             # NISQA quality gate retries per scene\nMAX_SAFE_REWRITES = 4          # Safe rewrite escalation levels\nTTS_CONCURRENCY_CAP = 3        # Max concurrent Gemini TTS calls\nTTS_SCENE_TIMEOUT = 900        # 15 minutes per scene (total)\nKEYS_BEFORE_REWRITE = 5        # Keys failed -> suspect content block\nHARD_TIMEOUT_S = 160           # Kill hung Gemini SDK call\nAPI_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000       # SDK timeout hint (milliseconds)\nRATE_LIMIT_COOLDOWN_S = 60.0   # Cooldown between key rotation rounds\n```\n\n### Resume/Crash Recovery\n\nAll three phases support resume:\n- **Phase 1:** `polished_texts.json` cache\n- **Phase 2:** `clip_NNN_raw.wav` files on disk\n- **Phase 3:** `clip_NNN.mp3` + `clip_NNN_whisperx.json` pairs\n\nIf the pipeline crashes mid-execution, re-running step 3 will skip already-completed work.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Per-Account Configuration\n\n### YAML Fields That Control Bloco 1\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `language` | str | required | ISO language code |\n| `tts_engine` | str | `\"alltalk\"` | `\"gemini\"` or `\"alltalk\"` |\n| `gemini_voice` | str | `\"Charon\"` | Gemini TTS voice name |\n| `screenplay_agent.min_words` | int | per-language | Min words per scene |\n| `screenplay_agent.max_words` | int | per-language | Max words per scene |\n| `screenplay_agent.prompt` | str | required | Prompt filename |\n| `tts_polish.domain_context` | str | `\"\"` | Channel domain description |\n| `tts_polish.protected_terms` | list | `[]` | Terms to preserve in TTS Polish |\n| `key_management.enabled` | bool | `false` | Enable KMS parallel mode |\n| `key_management.kms_url` | str | - | KMS server URL |\n| `key_management.machine_id` | str | `\"M1\"` | Machine identifier |\n| `sheet_scripts_id` | str | required | Google Sheet ID for scripts |\n| `sheet_scripts_name` | str | `\"Scripts\"` | Sheet tab name |\n\n### Language-Specific Word Limits\n\nDefined in the orchestrator class (`LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS`), overridable by `screenplay_agent.min_words`/`max_words` in YAML:\n\n| Language | Min Words | Max Words | Notes |\n|----------|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| en | 14 | 52 | |\n| pt | 16 | 57 | |\n| es | 18 | 68 | |\n| fr | 17 | 60 | |\n| de | 12 | 46 | |\n| it | 16 | 58 | |\n| tr | 18 | 66 | |\n| pl | 14 | 53 | |\n| ru | 14 | 52 | |\n| ja | 16 | 58 | Character count, not words |\n| ko | 16 | 57 | Character count, not words |\n| nl | 14 | 52 | |\n\n---\n\n## 12. Key Constants\n\n### Screenplay\n\n| Constant | Value | Location |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| `DEFAULT_SCENE_MIN_WORDS` | 18 | Orchestrator class |\n| `DEFAULT_SCENE_MAX_WORDS` | 45 | Orchestrator class |\n| `BATCH_MAX_WORDS` | 400 | Orchestrator class |\n| `Semaphore` for parallel batches | 8 | `ParallelScreenplayProcessor` |\n| GPT temperature | 0.4 | Multiple locations |\n| Sentence redistribution passes | 10 max | `scene_reconstructor._fix_word_counts` |\n| Word count tolerance | +/- 3 | `scene_word_count_checker` |\n\n### TTS\n\n| Constant | Value | Location |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| `POLISH_BATCH_SIZE` | 3 scenes/call | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| Polish `Semaphore` | 15 | `ParallelTTSProcessor._phase1_polish` |\n| `TTS_CONCURRENCY_CAP` | 3 | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `TTS_SCENE_TIMEOUT` | 900s (15 min) | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `MAX_PIPELINE_RETRIES` | 3 | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `MAX_QG_RETRIES` | 3 | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `MAX_SAFE_REWRITES` | 4 | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `KEYS_BEFORE_REWRITE` | 5 | `ParallelTTSProcessor` |\n| `HARD_TIMEOUT_S` | 160 | `GeminiTTSService` |\n| `API_TIMEOUT_MS` | 120,000 | `GeminiTTSService` |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_COOLDOWN_S` | 60.0 | `GeminiTTSService` |\n| PCM format | 24kHz, 16-bit, mono | `GeminiTTSService` / `parallel_tts.py` |\n| Silence trim threshold | 2.0s -> 1.0s | `SilenceTrimmer` defaults |\n| Silence detection dB | -40 dBFS | `SilenceTrimmer` / `parallel_tts` |\n| Max silence kept (Phase 3) | 500ms | `parallel_tts._trim_silence_pydub` |\n| Loudness target | -16.0 dBFS | `AudioProcessor.normalize_loudness` |\n| NISQA sample rate | 48,000 Hz | `AudioQualityGate` |\n| ElevenLabs model | `eleven_multilingual_v2` | `ElevenLabsTTSService` |\n| ElevenLabs stability | 0.6 | `ElevenLabsTTSService` |\n| ElevenLabs speed | 0.8 | `ElevenLabsTTSService` |\n| ElevenLabs chain depth | last 3 request IDs | `ElevenLabsTTSService` |\n\n### Transcription Validation Thresholds\n\n| Language | Match Ratio Threshold | Notes |\n|----------|-----------------------|-------|\n| en | 0.60 | Number words filtered |\n| pt | 0.75 | Contracted articles |\n| es | 0.70 | Contractions |\n| fr | 0.65 | Contractions + \"cents\" bug |\n| de | 0.65 | Compound numbers |\n| it | 0.70 | \"zero\" bug filtered |\n| tr | 0.75 | |\n| pl | 0.82 | Consonant clusters |\n| ru | 0.82 | Stress variations |\n| nl | 0.70 | |\n| ja | 0.75 | Character-based |\n| ko | 0.75 | Character-based |\n\n### NISQA Quality Gate Thresholds (Sample)\n\n| Language | MOS Threshold | Noisiness | Z-Score |\n|----------|--------------|-----------|---------|\n| en | 3.1 | 2.8 | -3.0 |\n| pt | 3.2 | 3.0 | -1.8 |\n| es | 3.2 | 2.5 | -1.5 (robust) |\n| de | 3.0 | 2.9 | -3.0 |\n\n---\n\n## Appendix: File Reference\n\n### Entry Points and Orchestration\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `accounts/NNN/workflow/orchestrator_NNN.py` | Per-account orchestrator (Bloco 1 = steps 0-3) |\n| `shared/processors/parallel_screenplay.py` | Async parallel screenplay batch processor via KMS |\n| `shared/processors/scene_reconstructor.py` | Deterministic scene auto-fix (zero LLM) |\n| `shared/processors/scene_text_validator.py` | Deterministic text coverage validation |\n| `shared/processors/scene_word_count_checker.py` | Deterministic word count pre-check |\n| `shared/processors/script_processor.py` | Script cleaning + language-specific formatting |\n\n### TTS Processing\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared/processors/parallel_tts.py` | 3-phase parallel TTS pipeline (Phase 1/2/3) |\n| `shared/processors/tts_polish_agent.py` | Standalone TTS Polish agent (used in local sequential path) |\n| `shared/processors/tts_safe_rewriter.py` | Standalone Safe Rewriter (used in local sequential path) |\n| `shared/processors/voice_selector.py` | Random voice selection from catalog (EN: Gemini, PT/ES: ElevenLabs) |\n| `shared/processors/narrator_gender_detector.py` | LLM-based narrator gender classifier (account 011 only) |\n| `shared/processors/silence_trimmer.py` | Silence detection and trimming (pydub + FFmpeg) |\n\n### Audio Services\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared/services/gemini_tts_service.py` | Gemini TTS API with key rotation (local sequential path) |\n| `shared/services/elevenlabs_tts_service.py` | ElevenLabs TTS for PT/ES (account 011) |\n| `shared/services/whisperx_service.py` | WhisperX transcription service (start/stop/transcribe) |\n| `shared/services/api_key_manager.py` | Local TTS API key manager (non-KMS path) |\n\n### Transcription and Validation\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared/processors/transcription_parser.py` | WhisperX result parsing and serialization |\n| `shared/processors/transcription_validator.py` | Match ratio + WER validation with language thresholds |\n| `shared/processors/audio_quality_gate.py` | NISQA-based audio quality assessment (GPU) |\n| `shared/processors/audio_processor.py` | Audio processing utilities (chunk splitting, trimming, normalization) |\n\n### Utilities\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared/utils/text_normalizer.py` | Numbers/abbreviations/units to words (11 languages) |\n| `shared/clients/centralized_key_client.py` | Async KMS client for parallel operations |\n| `shared/clients/kms_client_sync.py` | Sync KMS client for sequential operations |\n| `shared/clients/genai_factory.py` | Creates genai.Client for both API key and Service Account auth |\n\n### Prompts\n\n| Path Pattern | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `accounts/NNN/prompts/bloco1/{lang}/screenplay_agent_NNN_system.txt` | Screenplay agent system prompt |\n| `shared/prompts/tts_polish/tts_polish_{lang}_system.txt` | TTS Polish system prompt |\n| `shared/prompts/tts_safe_rewriter/tts_safe_rewriter_{lang}_system.txt` | Safe Rewriter system prompt |\n\n### Config\n\n| Path Pattern | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `accounts/NNN/configs/NNN-{lang}.yaml` | Per-account per-language configuration |\n| `gemini_api_keys/api_keys_registry_tts.yaml` | LOCAL per-machine TTS key registry (never committed) |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829890}}
{"type":"message","id":"c859109d","parentId":"67c771b0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.918Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_u7WwDFcc9wgkzJQZFDN9WdU0|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb34819099967c438c479fa3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 2 Output Contract -- Interface Specification for Bloco 3\n\n> **Purpose**: This document defines the EXACT output format that Bloco 2 (Visual Production) must produce for Bloco 3 (Video Composition) to consume. Any new Bloco 2 replacement MUST match this contract exactly.\n>\n> **Source of truth**: Traced backwards from `bloco3_preprocessor.py` (the consumer) and validated against production `video_spec.json` files.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Output Files\n\nBloco 2 produces a **single primary file** and several **supporting directories** inside the video data directory:\n\n```\n{account}/data/{lang}/{video_slug}/\n  video_spec.json              # PRIMARY CONTRACT FILE -- Bloco 3's sole input\n  images/\n    scene_001.png              # One image per scene (v1) or multiple (v2)\n    scene_002.png\n    ...\n  clips/\n    clip_001.mp3               # TTS audio per scene (from Bloco 1)\n    clip_002.mp3\n    ...\n  references/\n    char_001_reference.png     # Character portrait references\n    char_002_reference.png\n    ...\n  clips_metadata.json          # Bloco 1 output (scene durations, texts)\n  characters.json              # Character identification data\n  checkpoints/\n    09_video_spec_generated.json  # Completion checkpoint\n```\n\n### Path Convention\n\nThe `video_spec_path` passed to Bloco 3 is the absolute path to `video_spec.json`. Bloco 3 derives all other paths from:\n\n```python\nself.video_dir = self.video_spec_path.parent  # the video data directory\nself.output_dir = self.video_dir / \"remotion_{suffix}\"  # Bloco 3 output\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. video_spec.json -- Top-Level Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"metadata\": { ... },           // REQUIRED\n  \"global_resources\": { ... },   // OPTIONAL (may be null values)\n  \"characters\": [ ... ],         // REQUIRED (may be empty [])\n  \"scenes\": [ ... ]              // REQUIRED (non-empty)\n}\n```\n\n### 2.1. metadata (REQUIRED)\n\nAll fields accessed by Bloco 3 preprocessor with `self.metadata[key]` (i.e., will crash if missing):\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Bloco 3 Usage |\n|-------|------|----------|---------------|\n| `video_name` | string | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON metadata, Remotion project naming |\n| `video_title` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `account_id` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `language` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 (passed separately) |\n| `theme_style` | string | Soft-required | Slim JSON metadata (`get()` with default `\"\"`) |\n| `total_scenes` | int | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON metadata (also recalculated from `len(scenes)`) |\n| `total_duration_ms` | int | Optional | Not directly read by Bloco 3 |\n| `total_duration_frames` | int | **REQUIRED** | `self.total_frames`, last-scene clamping, NarrationLayer |\n| `fps` | int | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON metadata, NarrationLayer, Video.tsx |\n| `resolution` | object | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON metadata, planner prompts, Video.tsx |\n| `resolution.width` | int | **REQUIRED** | Remotion composition width |\n| `resolution.height` | int | **REQUIRED** | Remotion composition height |\n| `generated_at` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `bloco2_version` | string | Optional | Only present in v2-generated specs |\n\n**Example:**\n```json\n{\n  \"video_name\": \"why_bf_109_pilots_had_80_death_rate_the_brutal_rea\",\n  \"video_title\": \"Why Bf 109 Pilots Had 80 Death Rate The Brutal Rea\",\n  \"account_id\": \"003\",\n  \"language\": \"en\",\n  \"theme_style\": \"wwii_photography\",\n  \"total_scenes\": 145,\n  \"total_duration_ms\": 2117354,\n  \"total_duration_frames\": 63448,\n  \"fps\": 30,\n  \"resolution\": {\n    \"width\": 1920,\n    \"height\": 1080\n  },\n  \"generated_at\": \"2026-03-06T12:31:10.501617Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2. global_resources (OPTIONAL)\n\nNot consumed by Bloco 3. May contain null values. Preserved for historical compatibility.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"music\": null,\n  \"sfx_catalog\": null\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3. characters (REQUIRED, may be empty)\n\nAccessed as `self.video_spec.get(\"characters\", [])`. Each character object:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Bloco 3 Usage |\n|-------|------|----------|---------------|\n| `id` | string | **REQUIRED** | Filtering characters per batch (`c[\"id\"]`) |\n| `name` | string | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON characters (`c[\"name\"]`) |\n| `description` | string | **REQUIRED** | Slim JSON characters (`c[\"description\"]`) |\n| `is_famous` | bool | Optional | Not directly read by Bloco 3 |\n| `has_reference` | bool | Optional | Not directly read by Bloco 3 |\n| `reference_path` | string | Optional | Asset copying (references directory) |\n\n**Example:**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"char_001\",\n  \"name\": \"Joan of Arc\",\n  \"is_famous\": true,\n  \"has_reference\": true,\n  \"reference_path\": \"references\\\\char_001_reference.png\",\n  \"description\": \"Joan of Arc, 19-year-old French peasant girl...\"\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4. scenes (REQUIRED, non-empty)\n\nThe core data. Each scene is accessed as `self.scenes` with field lookups like `scene[\"scene_index\"]`, `scene[\"timing\"][\"start_frame\"]`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Per-Scene Schema (v1 format -- ALL production data)\n\nThis is the schema used by all current production video_spec.json files:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scene_index\": 1,\n  \"audio\": {\n    \"clip_path\": \"clips\\\\clip_001.mp3\",\n    \"duration_ms\": 13811,\n    \"duration_frames\": 414,\n    \"original_text\": \"At 32,000 feet above the Reich...\",\n    \"polished_text\": \"At 32,000 feet above the Reich...\",\n    \"word_timestamps\": [\n      {\n        \"word\": \"At\",\n        \"start_frame\": 1,\n        \"end_frame\": 14,\n        \"start_ms\": 31,\n        \"end_ms\": 473\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"visual\": {\n    \"image_path\": \"images/scene_001.png\",\n    \"interpretation_mode\": \"literal\",\n    \"shot_type\": \"close-up cockpit interior\",\n    \"visual_tone\": \"cold, harsh, claustrophobic...\",\n    \"what_to_show\": \"Close-up inside a Bf 109 cockpit...\",\n    \"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference...\"\n  },\n  \"characters_in_scene\": {\n    \"reference_strategy\": \"single_with_reference\",\n    \"characters_to_include\": [\"char_001\"],\n    \"character_names\": [\"Unnamed Luftwaffe Bf 109 Pilot\"],\n    \"visual_hierarchy\": null,\n    \"interaction_type\": null,\n    \"interaction_detail\": null,\n    \"requires_anonymization\": false\n  },\n  \"timing\": {\n    \"start_frame\": 0,\n    \"end_frame\": 414\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.1. scene_index (REQUIRED)\n\n- **Type**: int (1-indexed)\n- **Access**: `scene[\"scene_index\"]` (direct key, will crash if missing)\n- **Contract**: Sequential from 1 to N. Bloco 3 detects and re-indexes duplicates.\n\n### 3.2. audio (REQUIRED)\n\n| Field | Type | Required by B3 | How B3 reads it |\n|-------|------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `clip_path` | string | Soft | Not directly read by preprocessor (used for asset copy) |\n| `duration_ms` | int | Soft | Not directly read by preprocessor |\n| `duration_frames` | int | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"audio\"][\"duration_frames\"]` -- NarrationLayer generation, last-scene clamping |\n| `original_text` | string | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"audio\"][\"original_text\"]` -- slim JSONs for all agents with `include_original_text=True` |\n| `polished_text` | string | Soft-required | `scene[\"audio\"].get(\"polished_text\", \"\")` -- slim JSONs for agents with `include_polished_text=True` (accent_lettering, lettering_unified) |\n| `word_timestamps` | array | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"audio\"].get(\"word_timestamps\", [])` -- slim JSONs for lettering/SFX agents |\n\n### word_timestamps entry format (REQUIRED per word):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"word\": \"At\",\n  \"start_frame\": 1,\n  \"end_frame\": 14,\n  \"start_ms\": 31,\n  \"end_ms\": 473\n}\n```\n\nBloco 3 compacts these to `[\"word\", start_frame, end_frame]` in slim JSONs. Only `word`, `start_frame`, and `end_frame` are required. `start_ms` and `end_ms` are optional.\n\n### 3.3. visual (REQUIRED)\n\n| Field | Type | Required by B3 | How B3 reads it |\n|-------|------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `image_path` | string | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"visual\"][\"image_path\"]` -- animation agent slim JSONs |\n| `visual_tone` | string | Soft-required | `scene[\"visual\"].get(\"visual_tone\", \"\")` -- most agent slim JSONs |\n| `what_to_show` | string | Soft-required | `scene[\"visual\"].get(\"what_to_show\", \"\")` -- most agent slim JSONs |\n| `interpretation_mode` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `shot_type` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `image_prompt` | string | Optional | `scene[\"visual\"].get(\"image_prompt\", \"\")` -- only if `include_image_prompt=True` (not used by any current agent) |\n\n### 3.4. characters_in_scene (REQUIRED)\n\n| Field | Type | Required by B3 | How B3 reads it |\n|-------|------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `character_names` | array[string] | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"characters_in_scene\"].get(\"character_names\", [])` -- slim JSONs |\n| `characters_to_include` | array[string] | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"characters_in_scene\"].get(\"characters_to_include\", [])` -- character filtering per batch |\n| `reference_strategy` | string | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `visual_hierarchy` | object/null | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `interaction_type` | string/null | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `interaction_detail` | string/null | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n| `requires_anonymization` | bool | Optional | Not read by Bloco 3 |\n\n### 3.5. timing (REQUIRED)\n\n| Field | Type | Required by B3 | How B3 reads it |\n|-------|------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `start_frame` | int | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"timing\"][\"start_frame\"]` -- NarrationLayer, slim JSONs, all agents |\n| `end_frame` | int | **REQUIRED** | `scene[\"timing\"][\"end_frame\"]` -- slim JSONs, last-scene clamping |\n\n**Invariant**: `end_frame = start_frame + duration_frames` for all scenes except possibly the last (which gets clamped to `total_duration_frames`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Per-Scene Schema (v2 format -- visual_direction extension)\n\nThe v2 generator (`video_spec_generator_v2.py`) adds a `visual_direction` block to each scene for multi-image compositions. This is ADDITIVE -- all v1 fields remain. No production data currently uses this format.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scene_index\": 1,\n  \"scene_text\": \"narration text...\",\n  \"visual\": {\n    \"image_path\": \"images/scene_001_hero.png\"\n  },\n  \"audio\": { ... },\n  \"timing\": { ... },\n  \"characters_in_scene\": {\n    \"character_names\": [\"Joan of Arc\"]\n  },\n  \"visual_direction\": {\n    \"composition_type\": \"hero_with_stickers\",\n    \"elements\": [\n      {\n        \"slot_id\": \"scene_001_hero\",\n        \"role\": \"hero\",\n        \"file\": \"images/scene_001_hero.png\",\n        \"animation\": \"ken_burns\",\n        \"enter\": \"fade_in\",\n        \"exit\": \"fade_out\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"slot_id\": \"scene_001_sticker_1\",\n        \"role\": \"sticker\",\n        \"file\": \"images/scene_001_sticker_1.png\",\n        \"animation\": \"static\",\n        \"enter\": \"cut\",\n        \"exit\": \"cut\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### v2-specific fields read by Bloco 3:\n\n| Field | Read by | How |\n|-------|---------|-----|\n| `visual_direction.composition_type` | `_is_composition_scene()` | `scene.get(\"visual_direction\", {}).get(\"composition_type\", \"hero_simple\")` |\n| `visual_direction.elements` | `generate_composition_slim_jsons()` | Per-element: `role`, `file` |\n| `scene_text` | Not read by Bloco 3 preprocessor | Only in v2 generator output |\n\n**Composition types**: `hero_simple` (default/v1), `hero_with_stickers`, `composition_grid`, `sequence`, `hero_with_sequence`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Image File Convention\n\n### v1 (current production):\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Naming** | `scene_{NNN}.png` (zero-padded 3 digits) |\n| **Format** | PNG |\n| **Directory** | `{video_dir}/images/` |\n| **Count** | Exactly 1 per scene |\n| **Resolution** | Matches metadata resolution (1920x1080) |\n| **Reference** | `visual.image_path = \"images/scene_001.png\"` (relative to video_dir) |\n\n### v2 (multi-image compositions):\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Naming** | `scene_{NNN}_{role}.png` or `scene_{NNN}_{role}_{N}.png` |\n| **Roles** | `hero`, `sticker`, `seq`, `grid`, `bg` |\n| **Reference** | In `visual_direction.elements[].file` and `visual.image_path` (hero/first) |\n\n### Character References:\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Naming** | `char_{NNN}_reference.png` |\n| **Directory** | `{video_dir}/references/` |\n| **Reference** | `characters[].reference_path` |\n\n### Audio Clips:\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Naming** | `clip_{NNN}.mp3` |\n| **Directory** | `{video_dir}/clips/` |\n| **Reference** | `scenes[].audio.clip_path` (uses backslash on Windows: `\"clips\\\\clip_001.mp3\"`) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Bloco 3 Reads video_spec.json\n\n### 6.1. Loading (bloco3_preprocessor.py, constructor)\n\n```python\nwith open(self.video_spec_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    self.video_spec = json.load(f)\n\nself.metadata = self.video_spec[\"metadata\"]          # CRASH if missing\nself.scenes = self.video_spec[\"scenes\"]              # CRASH if missing\nself.characters = self.video_spec.get(\"characters\", [])  # safe default\nself.total_frames = self.metadata[\"total_duration_frames\"]  # CRASH if missing\n```\n\n### 6.2. Duplicate scene_index detection\n\nBloco 3 detects duplicate `scene_index` values and re-indexes sequentially (1..N):\n\n```python\nfor i, s in enumerate(self.scenes):\n    s[\"scene_index\"] = i + 1\n```\n\n### 6.3. Last-scene clamping\n\nIf the last scene's `start_frame + duration_frames > total_duration_frames`, Bloco 3 clamps:\n\n```python\nlast[\"audio\"][\"duration_frames\"] = self.total_frames - last[\"timing\"][\"start_frame\"]\nlast[\"timing\"][\"end_frame\"] = self.total_frames\n```\n\n### 6.4. Slim JSON generation\n\nFor each agent type, `_slim_scene()` extracts a subset of scene fields:\n\n```python\nslim = {\n    \"scene_index\": scene[\"scene_index\"],\n    \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": scene[\"timing\"][\"start_frame\"],\n        \"end_frame\": scene[\"timing\"][\"end_frame\"],\n    },\n    \"audio\": {\n        \"duration_frames\": scene[\"audio\"][\"duration_frames\"],\n    },\n}\n# Then conditionally adds: original_text, polished_text, word_timestamps,\n# visual.image_path, visual.visual_tone, visual.what_to_show, characters\n```\n\n### 6.5. Asset copying\n\n`copy_assets(video_dir)` copies from the video directory to Remotion's `public/`:\n\n- `images/*.png` and `*.jpg` -> `public/images/`\n- `clips/*.mp3` -> `public/clips/`\n- `references/*.png` -> `public/references/`\n- SFX from account `resources/sfx/` -> `public/sfx/` (with variant randomization)\n- Music from account `resources/music/` -> `public/music/` (with variant randomization)\n\n### 6.6. NarrationLayer.tsx generation\n\nReads from each scene:\n- `scene[\"scene_index\"]` -> clip file naming (`clip_{idx:03d}.mp3`)\n- `scene[\"timing\"][\"start_frame\"]` -> `<Sequence from={start}>`\n- `scene[\"audio\"][\"duration_frames\"]` -> `<Sequence durationInFrames={duration}>`\n\n### 6.7. Slim metadata builder\n\n```python\n{\n    \"video_name\": self.metadata[\"video_name\"],\n    \"total_scenes\": self.metadata[\"total_scenes\"],\n    \"total_duration_frames\": self.metadata[\"total_duration_frames\"],\n    \"fps\": self.metadata[\"fps\"],\n    \"resolution\": self.metadata[\"resolution\"],\n    \"theme_style\": self.metadata.get(\"theme_style\", \"\"),\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Required vs Optional Fields -- Summary\n\n### MUST EXIST (Bloco 3 crashes without these):\n\n**Top level:**\n- `metadata` (object)\n- `scenes` (array, non-empty)\n\n**metadata:**\n- `video_name` (string)\n- `total_scenes` (int)\n- `total_duration_frames` (int)\n- `fps` (int)\n- `resolution` (object with `width` and `height`)\n\n**Per scene:**\n- `scene_index` (int, 1-indexed)\n- `timing.start_frame` (int)\n- `timing.end_frame` (int)\n- `audio.duration_frames` (int)\n- `audio.original_text` (string)\n- `visual.image_path` (string)\n\n### SOFT-REQUIRED (accessed with `.get()`, defaults to empty):\n\n**Per scene:**\n- `audio.polished_text` (string, default `\"\"`)\n- `audio.word_timestamps` (array, default `[]`)\n- `visual.visual_tone` (string, default `\"\"`)\n- `visual.what_to_show` (string, default `\"\"`)\n- `visual.image_prompt` (string, default `\"\"`)\n- `characters_in_scene.character_names` (array, default `[]`)\n- `characters_in_scene.characters_to_include` (array, default `[]`)\n\n**Top level:**\n- `characters` (array, default `[]`)\n- `metadata.theme_style` (string, default `\"\"`)\n\n### OPTIONAL (not read by Bloco 3):\n\n- `global_resources` (entire block)\n- `metadata.video_title`\n- `metadata.account_id`\n- `metadata.language`\n- `metadata.total_duration_ms`\n- `metadata.generated_at`\n- `metadata.bloco2_version`\n- `visual.interpretation_mode`\n- `visual.shot_type`\n- `characters_in_scene.reference_strategy`\n- `characters_in_scene.visual_hierarchy`\n- `characters_in_scene.interaction_type`\n- `characters_in_scene.interaction_detail`\n- `characters_in_scene.requires_anonymization`\n- `characters[].is_famous`\n- `characters[].has_reference`\n- `characters[].reference_path`\n\n### OPTIONAL v2 EXTENSION (only when compositions enabled):\n\n- `visual_direction.composition_type` (string, default `\"hero_simple\"`)\n- `visual_direction.elements` (array of element objects)\n- `scene_text` (string)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Checkpoint Format\n\n### Bloco 2 completion checkpoint:\n\nFile: `{video_dir}/checkpoints/09_video_spec_generated.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"checkpoint_name\": \"09_video_spec_generated\",\n  \"description\": \"V3: video_spec.json consolidado para Bloco 3\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-03-06T09:31:10.605616\",\n  \"video_name\": \"why_bf_109_pilots_had_80_death_rate_the_brutal_rea\",\n  \"output_files\": [\"video_spec.json\"],\n  \"validation_criteria\": \"video_spec.json existe com scenes[], characters[], metadata\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"total_scenes\": 145,\n    \"total_characters\": 1,\n    \"total_duration_ms\": 2117354,\n    \"total_frames\": 63448,\n    \"output_file\": \"video_spec.json\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Bloco 3 checkpoints (what Bloco 3 creates):\n\n```\ncheckpoints/\n  10_remotion_preprocessed.json\n  11_planners_complete.json\n  12_resolver_complete.json\n  13_agents_complete.json\n  14_video_rendered.json\n  15_video_compressed.json\n  16_uploaded_and_tracked.json\n```\n\nBloco 3 does NOT check for Bloco 2's checkpoint file. It only checks that `video_spec.json` exists at the provided path.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Real Production Example (sanitized)\n\n### Complete video_spec.json structure for account 003 (145 scenes):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"video_name\": \"why_bf_109_pilots_had_80_death_rate_the_brutal_rea\",\n    \"video_title\": \"Why Bf 109 Pilots Had 80 Death Rate The Brutal Rea\",\n    \"account_id\": \"003\",\n    \"language\": \"en\",\n    \"theme_style\": \"wwii_photography\",\n    \"total_scenes\": 145,\n    \"total_duration_ms\": 2117354,\n    \"total_duration_frames\": 63448,\n    \"fps\": 30,\n    \"resolution\": { \"width\": 1920, \"height\": 1080 },\n    \"generated_at\": \"2026-03-06T12:31:10.501617Z\"\n  },\n  \"global_resources\": {\n    \"music\": null,\n    \"sfx_catalog\": null\n  },\n  \"characters\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"char_001\",\n      \"name\": \"Unnamed Luftwaffe Bf 109 Pilot\",\n      \"is_famous\": false,\n      \"has_reference\": true,\n      \"reference_path\": \"references\\\\char_001_reference.png\",\n      \"description\": \"28-year-old German Luftwaffe fighter pilot...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_index\": 1,\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"clip_path\": \"clips\\\\clip_001.mp3\",\n        \"duration_ms\": 13811,\n        \"duration_frames\": 414,\n        \"original_text\": \"At 32,000 feet above the Reich in January 1944...\",\n        \"polished_text\": \"At 32,000 feet above the Reich in January 1944...\",\n        \"word_timestamps\": [\n          { \"word\": \"At\", \"start_frame\": 1, \"end_frame\": 14, \"start_ms\": 31, \"end_ms\": 473 },\n          { \"word\": \"32,000\", \"start_frame\": 15, \"end_frame\": 47, \"start_ms\": 493, \"end_ms\": 1558 },\n          { \"word\": \"feet\", \"start_frame\": 49, \"end_frame\": 55, \"start_ms\": 1618, \"end_ms\": 1819 }\n        ]\n      },\n      \"visual\": {\n        \"image_path\": \"images/scene_001.png\",\n        \"interpretation_mode\": \"literal\",\n        \"shot_type\": \"close-up cockpit interior\",\n        \"visual_tone\": \"cold, harsh, claustrophobic, blue-gray winter light...\",\n        \"what_to_show\": \"Close-up inside a Bf 109 cockpit at extreme altitude...\",\n        \"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference...\"\n      },\n      \"characters_in_scene\": {\n        \"reference_strategy\": \"single_with_reference\",\n        \"characters_to_include\": [\"char_001\"],\n        \"character_names\": [\"Unnamed Luftwaffe Bf 109 Pilot\"],\n        \"visual_hierarchy\": null,\n        \"interaction_type\": null,\n        \"interaction_detail\": null,\n        \"requires_anonymization\": false\n      },\n      \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": 0,\n        \"end_frame\": 414\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Directory Structure Summary\n\n```\n{video_dir}/\n  video_spec.json                    # THE contract file\n  clips_metadata.json                # Bloco 1 output (durations, texts)\n  characters.json                    # Character identification data\n  script.txt                         # Original script\n  screenplay_analysis.json           # Screenplay analysis\n  scene_directions.json              # Scene direction data\n  image_prompts.json                 # Image generation prompts\n  images_metadata.json               # Image generation metadata\n  reference_map.json                 # Character reference mapping\n  images/\n    scene_001.png                    # PNG, 1920x1080, one per scene\n    scene_002.png\n    ...scene_{NNN}.png\n  clips/\n    clip_001.mp3                     # TTS audio, one per scene\n    clip_001_debug.json              # TTS debug info\n    clip_001_whisperx.json           # WhisperX alignment\n    ...\n  references/\n    char_001_reference.png           # Character portrait, one per character\n    ...\n  audio/                             # Raw audio files (Bloco 1)\n  checkpoints/                       # Pipeline completion state\n    01_script_fetched.json\n    02_screenplay_analyzed.json\n    ...\n    09_video_spec_generated.json     # B2 completion marker\n  logs/                              # Pipeline logs\n  prompts/                           # LLM prompts used\n  final/                             # Final rendered output\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. Critical Invariants\n\n1. **scene_index is 1-indexed** and must be sequential (or Bloco 3 re-indexes).\n2. **timing.start_frame of scene N+1 >= timing.end_frame of scene N** (no gaps allowed for NarrationLayer).\n3. **audio.duration_frames = timing.end_frame - timing.start_frame** (Bloco 3 uses both independently).\n4. **Image files MUST exist** at the path specified by `visual.image_path` relative to `video_dir`.\n5. **Clip files MUST exist** at `clips/clip_{NNN}.mp3` (Bloco 3 copies them to `public/clips/`).\n6. **word_timestamps MUST have `word`, `start_frame`, `end_frame`** (other fields optional).\n7. **total_duration_frames must equal the end_frame of the last scene** (or Bloco 3 clamps).\n8. **Encoding**: UTF-8 with `ensure_ascii=False` (supports all languages including Japanese, Korean, Arabic).\n9. **Path separators**: Windows backslash in stored paths (e.g., `\"clips\\\\clip_001.mp3\"`), but Bloco 3 uses `Path()` so both work.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Minimal Viable video_spec.json\n\nThe absolute minimum that Bloco 3 will accept without crashing:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"video_name\": \"test_video\",\n    \"total_scenes\": 2,\n    \"total_duration_frames\": 600,\n    \"fps\": 30,\n    \"resolution\": { \"width\": 1920, \"height\": 1080 }\n  },\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_index\": 1,\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"duration_frames\": 300,\n        \"original_text\": \"First scene narration.\"\n      },\n      \"visual\": {\n        \"image_path\": \"images/scene_001.png\"\n      },\n      \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": 0,\n        \"end_frame\": 300\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"scene_index\": 2,\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"duration_frames\": 300,\n        \"original_text\": \"Second scene narration.\"\n      },\n      \"visual\": {\n        \"image_path\": \"images/scene_002.png\"\n      },\n      \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": 300,\n        \"end_frame\": 600\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Note**: This minimal spec will work but produce lower quality output because `visual_tone`, `what_to_show`, `word_timestamps`, and `characters_in_scene` will all be empty defaults.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829906}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9f4f02c","parentId":"c859109d","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.931Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0Qltp7CpgmsR3i4dq8y9QQoa|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb3881909ebe10caf65233ed","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 2: Visual/Image Production Pipeline\n\n> **Status**: PRODUCTION (Bloco 2 v2 is the active engine)\n> **Config flag**: `bloco2_engine: \"v2\"` in per-account YAML configs\n> **Orchestrator**: `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/bloco2v2_orchestrator.py`\n> **Lines of code**: ~7,500+ across orchestrator + 15 step files + helpers\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [Overview](#1-overview)\n2. [Pipeline Steps (15-Step Breakdown)](#2-pipeline-steps)\n3. [The Image Generation Problem](#3-the-image-generation-problem)\n4. [Data Flow (Bloco 1 -> Bloco 2 -> Bloco 3)](#4-data-flow)\n5. [Input Contract](#5-input-contract)\n6. [Output Contract](#6-output-contract)\n7. [LLM Calls Per Step](#7-llm-calls-per-step)\n8. [KMS / API Key Usage](#8-kms--api-key-usage)\n9. [Error Handling](#9-error-handling)\n10. [Per-Account Configuration](#10-per-account-configuration)\n11. [What the Replacement Must Produce](#11-what-the-replacement-must-produce)\n12. [Bloco 2 v1 (Legacy Reference)](#12-bloco-2-v1-legacy-reference)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nBloco 2 is the **visual production block** of the Content Factory V3 pipeline. It receives a screenplay (text narrative broken into scenes) and dataset images (curated historical photographs) from Bloco 1 / the Dataset System, and produces a complete `visual_spec.json` that tells Bloco 3 exactly which images to display, how to animate them, and when to trigger visual elements.\n\n### What Bloco 2 Does End-to-End\n\n1. **Character identification** -- finds all named characters in the screenplay\n2. **Character-to-dataset matching** -- links characters to real historical photos\n3. **Portrait generation** -- creates AI portraits for characters without real photos\n4. **Image analysis** -- profiles every dataset image for quality, era, content\n5. **Entity-to-scene mapping** -- determines which images are relevant to which scenes\n6. **Composition planning** -- decides the visual layout per scene (hero, stickers, grids, sequences)\n7. **Image selection** -- multimodal LLM sees actual images and picks the best for each slot\n8. **Visual direction** -- defines animations, positions, timing, trigger words\n9. **Reference strategy** -- analyzes reference images for AI generation\n10. **Prompt authoring** -- creates creative briefs with era-authentic technical packages\n11. **JSON prompt building** -- translates briefs to Gemini Image API format\n12. **AI image generation** -- generates images via Gemini Image API / OpenRouter\n13. **Final assembly** -- downloads real images, resolves timestamps, produces `visual_spec.json`\n\n### Pipeline Phases\n\nThe 15 steps are organized into 5 sequential phases:\n\n| Phase | Steps | Description | Parallelism |\n|-------|-------|-------------|-------------|\n| **A: Character Pipeline** | 00, 00a, 00b, 00c | Identify characters, match to dataset, generate portraits | Sequential |\n| **B: Analysis** | 01, 02 (2a+2b) | Profile images, map entities to scenes | 01 parallel batches, 02a LLM + 02b pure Python |\n| **C: Composition** | 03, 03b, 04 | Plan layouts, review, select images | Sequential accumulator |\n| **D: Direction** | 05, 06 | Visual direction + reference strategy | Sequential (avoid 429 floods) |\n| **E: Generation** | 07, 08, 09, 10 | Prompts, JSON, image gen, assembly | Sequential |\n\n### Checkpoint System\n\nEvery step saves a checkpoint JSON envelope to `{video_dir}/checkpoints/04_{step_id}.json`. The pipeline resumes from the last completed checkpoint automatically. Checkpoints contain:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"step\": \"03_compositions_planned\",\n  \"step_name\": \"Composition Planner\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-03-25T14:30:00Z\",\n  \"video_name\": \"torpedo_boats\",\n  \"account_id\": \"003\",\n  \"language\": \"en\",\n  \"wall_time_seconds\": 45.2,\n  \"gemini_calls\": 8,\n  \"gemini_cost_usd\": 0.0012,\n  \"data\": { ... }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pipeline Steps\n\n### Step 00: Dataset Export (No-Op)\n- **File**: Inline in `bloco2v2_orchestrator.py` (`_step_00`)\n- **Type**: Pure Python, zero LLM\n- **Purpose**: Records that dataset images are downloaded to disk. Counts entities, assets, accepted/b-roll assets, and images in the registry.\n- **Input**: `dataset_images` dict (from Dataset System export)\n- **Output**: Counts dict (`total_entities`, `total_assets`, `accepted_assets`, `broll_assets`, `images_on_disk`)\n\n### Step 00a: Character Identifier\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_00a_character_identifier.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, batched)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 10 scenes per call\n- **Purpose**: Reads the full screenplay and identifies every individual character with identity resolution across batches using an accumulator pattern.\n- **Input**: `screenplay.scenes[]` + `screenplay.video_context`\n- **Output**: `{ \"characters\": [...], \"processing_log\": [...] }`\n- **Character object**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"id\": \"char_001\",\n    \"name\": \"Admiral Yamamoto\",\n    \"is_famous\": true,\n    \"description\": \"Japanese naval commander...\",\n    \"narrative_context\": {\n      \"known_references\": [\"Yamamoto\", \"the Admiral\"]\n    },\n    \"scenes_present\": [1, 3, 5, 8]\n  }\n  ```\n- **Key behavior**: Accumulator pattern -- each batch receives the current character list, returns new/updated characters. Group names (soldiers, troops, etc.) are automatically filtered out.\n- **Temperature**: 0.4\n\n### Step 00b: Character-Entity Matcher\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_00b_character_entity_matcher.py`\n- **Type**: Pure Python, zero LLM\n- **Purpose**: Cross-references characters from Step 0a against dataset entity data. Determines which characters have real photos (dataset) vs need AI-generated portraits.\n- **Input**: Step 0a characters + `dataset_images.entities[]` + `dataset_images.assets[]`\n- **Output**: `{ \"characters\": [...], \"source_summary\": { \"dataset\": N, \"ai_portrait\": N, \"no_portrait_needed\": N } }`\n- **Character object additions**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"char_id\": \"char_001\",\n    \"character_source\": \"dataset\" | \"ai_portrait\" | \"no_portrait_needed\",\n    \"entity_id\": \"uuid-...\",\n    \"entity_key\": \"yamamoto_isoroku\",\n    \"dataset_images\": [{ \"asset_id\": \"...\", \"storage_url\": \"...\", \"width\": 800, \"height\": 600, \"relevance_score\": 0.95 }],\n    \"portrait_needed\": true,\n    \"portrait_model\": \"search_grounded\" | \"standard\" | null\n  }\n  ```\n- **Portrait criteria**: Characters with 2+ scenes or `is_famous=true` get portraits. Famous characters use `search_grounded` model (Gemini with Google Search), others use `standard`.\n\n### Step 00c: Portrait Generator\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_00c_portrait_generator.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text + Gemini Image API)\n- **Model groups**: `bloco2_text` (Phase 1: prompt gen) + `bloco2_image` (Phase 2: image gen)\n- **Image model**: `gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview`\n- **Concurrency**: Phase 1 Sem(4), Phase 2 Sem(2)\n- **Timeout**: 600s (10 min) per character (shared across both phases)\n- **Purpose**: Creates AI-generated portrait images for characters that lack real photos. Portraits serve as identity locks -- sent as reference images to Step 9 for visual consistency.\n- **Two-phase process**:\n  1. **Phase 1**: LLM text call to produce structured JSON portrait prompt (subject, wardrobe, composition, era_authenticity, reference_instructions, negative_prompt)\n  2. **Phase 2**: Gemini Image API generates the portrait from the flattened prompt\n- **Input**: Step 0b characters + era_technical_package from account config\n- **Output**: `{ \"characters\": [...with portrait_path filled], \"portraits_generated\": N, \"portraits_failed\": N }`\n- **Safety handling**: `PortraitSafeRewriter` with 3 escalating rewrite levels on content blocks. After 5 keys tried with same prompt, escalates rewrite level.\n- **Reference images**: Downloads best dataset reference image for the character (if available) and sends as multimodal input.\n- **Output files**: `{video_dir}/portraits/{char_id}_portrait.png`\n\n### Step 01: Image Profiler\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_01_image_profiler.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini multimodal, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 6 images per call\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(6)\n- **Purpose**: Analyzes each dataset image for visual_summary, display_potential, reference_potential, detected_era, visual_layout, technical_quality, and person_identified.\n- **Input**: `dataset_images.assets[]` (filtered: rejected non-b-roll skipped) + `dataset_images.entities[]` + Step 0b character map\n- **Output**: `{ \"profiles\": [...], \"stats\": {...} }`\n- **Profile object**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"image_id\": \"uuid-...\",\n    \"entity_key\": \"yamamoto_isoroku\",\n    \"visual_summary\": \"Black and white photograph of...\",\n    \"display_potential\": { \"hero\": \"HIGH\", \"sticker\": \"LOW\", \"sequence\": \"MEDIUM\" },\n    \"reference_potential\": \"HIGH\",\n    \"detected_era\": { \"period\": \"1940s\", \"confidence\": 0.9 },\n    \"visual_layout\": { ... },\n    \"technical_quality\": { \"overall\": \"GOOD\", ... },\n    \"person_identified\": { \"char_id\": \"char_001\", \"name\": \"Yamamoto\", \"is_famous\": true }\n  }\n  ```\n- **Temperature**: 0.3\n\n### Step 02: Entity Mapper (2a + 2b combined)\nTwo sub-steps sharing a single checkpoint:\n\n#### Step 02a: Entity Alias Generator\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_02a_entity_alias_generator.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 15 scenes per chunk\n- **Purpose**: Analyzes screenplay text to generate alias/synonym lists for each entity. Example: entity \"yamamoto_isoroku\" gets aliases [\"Yamamoto\", \"the Admiral\", \"Isoroku\"].\n- **Input**: `dataset_images.entities[]` + `screenplay.scenes[]` + Step 0b character known_references\n- **Output**: `{ \"alias_map\": { \"entity_key\": [\"formal_name\", \"alias1\", \"alias2\"] }, \"stats\": {...} }`\n- **Temperature**: 0.3\n\n#### Step 02b: Entity-Scene Mapper\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_02b_entity_scene_mapper.py`\n- **Type**: Pure Python, zero LLM\n- **Purpose**: Cross-references alias map from 2a with image profiles and screenplay scenes to produce per-scene candidate image pools.\n- **Matching strategy**:\n  1. Word boundary alias matching (case-insensitive, with basic stemming)\n  2. Character entity presence from Step 0b `scenes_present`\n  3. Context inheritance: scenes with no direct matches inherit previous scene's entities\n  4. B-roll images always available in every scene\n- **Input**: Step 2a alias_map + Step 1 profiles + Step 0b characters + `screenplay.scenes[]`\n- **Output**: `{ \"scene_pools\": { \"scene_N\": { \"scene_index\": N, \"entities_mentioned\": [...], \"candidate_images\": [...], \"match_types\": { \"direct\": [...], \"inherited\": [...], \"character\": [...] } } } }`\n- **Match types**: `direct` (alias found in text), `character` (from scenes_present), `inherited` (no direct matches, inherit from previous scene), `broll` (always available)\n\n### Step 03: Composition Planner\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_03_composition_planner.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, sequential accumulator)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 7 scenes per call\n- **Purpose**: Decides composition TYPE per scene and creates SLOTS within each composition. Assigns source (real vs ai) per slot and suggests candidate/reference images.\n- **Composition types**: `hero_simple`, `hero_with_stickers`, `sequence`, `composition_grid`, `hero_with_sequence`\n- **Slot roles**: `hero`, `sticker`, `sequence_element`, `grid_element`, `background`\n- **Slot sources**: `real` (use dataset image) or `ai` (generate new image)\n- **Accumulator**: Tracks `allocated_display_ids` -- display images are unique (can't reuse across scenes), but reference images are free to reuse.\n- **Input**: `screenplay.scenes[]` + Step 1 profiles + Step 2b scene_pools + Step 0b characters\n- **Output**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"compositions\": [\n      {\n        \"scene_id\": 1,\n        \"composition_type\": \"hero_with_stickers\",\n        \"slots\": [\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_hero\",\n            \"role\": \"hero\",\n            \"source\": \"real\",\n            \"top_pick\": \"asset-uuid-...\",\n            \"alternatives\": [\"uuid-2\", \"uuid-3\"],\n            \"fallback_candidate\": \"uuid-4\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n            \"role\": \"sticker\",\n            \"source\": \"ai\",\n            \"ai_intent\": \"Close-up of torpedo mechanism\",\n            \"references_suggested\": [\"uuid-5\"],\n            \"characters\": [\"char_002\"]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ],\n    \"allocated_display_ids\": [\"uuid-1\", ...]\n  }\n  ```\n- **Temperature**: 0.4\n- **Validation**: Hallucinated scene_ids outside batch range are filtered. UUID corruption is detected and corrected via Levenshtein distance matching.\n\n### Step 03b: Composition Reviewer\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_03b_composition_reviewer.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (single call) + Pure Python mechanical fixes\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Purpose**: Cross-batch coherence review. Sees ALL compositions at once (unlike Step 03's 7-scene batches) to detect and fix: monotony, reference overuse, aesthetic breaks, text-in-image, poor real image selections.\n- **Two phases**:\n  1. **Mechanical fixes** (Python, no LLM): Fix `sequence_element` -> `slots` normalization, downgrade multi-slot compositions with <2 slots, fill missing `top_pick`\n  2. **LLM review** (single Gemini call): Receives compact view of all compositions, returns corrections list\n- **Input**: Step 03 compositions + Step 01 profiles\n- **Output**: `{ \"compositions\": [...corrected], \"allocated_display_ids\": [...rebuilt] }`\n- **Temperature**: 0.4\n\n### Step 04: Image Selector\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_04_image_selector.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini multimodal, sequential accumulator)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 5 scenes per call\n- **Purpose**: SEES actual candidate images (multimodal) and makes FINAL selection for each `source: \"real\"` slot. AI slots pass through unchanged.\n- **Key feature**: Sends actual image bytes to Gemini for visual judgment, not just metadata.\n- **Deduplication**: Validates no duplicate asset selections within a batch. Conflicts resolved via fallback candidates, pool expansion, or conversion to AI slot.\n- **Pool expansion**: When Step 03's candidate pool is exhausted, searches all profiles with matching entity_key.\n- **Input**: Step 03b compositions + Step 01 profiles + Step 0b characters + actual image bytes\n- **Output**: `{ \"selections\": [...], \"confirmed_display_ids\": [...], \"ai_slots_passthrough\": [...] }`\n- **Temperature**: 0.3\n\n### Step 05: Visual Director\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_05_visual_director.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_vision`\n- **Batch size**: 5 scenes per call\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(6)\n- **Purpose**: Defines HOW each image element appears in the video: animation, position, trigger words, duration, entry/exit behavior.\n- **Input**: Step 03 compositions + Step 04 selections + Step 01 profiles + Step 0b characters + WhisperX word timestamps + `clips_metadata`\n- **Output**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"directions\": [\n      {\n        \"scene_id\": 1,\n        \"composition_type\": \"hero_with_stickers\",\n        \"elements\": [\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_hero\",\n            \"role\": \"hero\",\n            \"source\": \"real\",\n            \"asset\": \"uuid-...\",\n            \"animation\": \"slow_zoom_in\",\n            \"duration\": \"full_scene\",\n            \"position\": \"center\",\n            \"enter\": \"fade_in\",\n            \"exit\": \"crossfade_to_next\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n            \"role\": \"sticker\",\n            \"source\": \"ai\",\n            \"asset\": \"ai_gen_scene_1_sticker_1\",\n            \"animation\": \"pop_in\",\n            \"duration\": 2.5,\n            \"position\": \"bottom_right\",\n            \"size\": \"medium\",\n            \"trigger_word\": \"torpedo\",\n            \"enter\": \"scale_up\",\n            \"exit\": \"fade_out\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n- **Post-validation pipeline** (Python, no LLM):\n  1. Trigger word validation: checks words exist in WhisperX transcript, uses `difflib.get_close_matches` for fuzzy correction\n  2. Position collision detection: ensures no two stickers share the same position\n  3. Unique AI asset names: canonical format `ai_gen_scene_{N}_{role}[_{idx}]`\n  4. Cross-batch monotony fixing: prevents >3 consecutive same enter/exit/size/position\n- **Temperature**: 0.4\n\n### Step 06: Reference Strategist\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_06_reference_strategist.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini multimodal, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_vision`\n- **Batch size**: 4 AI slots per call\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(6)\n- **Max refs per slot**: 4\n- **Max pool size**: 6\n- **Purpose**: SEES actual reference images (multimodal) and defines what to extract/ignore from each. Also acts as era gatekeeper. Portraits are auto-injected as `R9_person_identity`.\n- **Input**: Step 03 compositions + Step 04 confirmed_display_ids + Step 01 profiles + Step 0c portraits + Step 0b characters\n- **Output**: `{ \"strategies\": [{ \"slot_id\": \"...\", \"references_selected\": [{ \"image_id\": \"...\", \"role\": \"R1_atmosphere\", \"instruction\": \"extract lighting mood\", ... }], \"references_discarded\": [...] }] }`\n- **Temperature**: 0.3\n\n### Step 07: Prompt Director\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_07_prompt_director.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 4 AI slots per call\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(6)\n- **Purpose**: The most creative agent. Produces complete creative briefs per AI slot with `era_technical_package`. Enriches with character data, entity metadata, scene text.\n- **Input**: Step 03 compositions + Step 06 strategies + Steps 0a/0b/0c characters + screenplay + dataset entities\n- **Output**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"creative_briefs\": [\n      {\n        \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n        \"scene_id\": 1,\n        \"creative_brief\": {\n          \"primary_focus\": \"Close-up torpedo loading mechanism\",\n          \"narrative_tone\": \"tension, mechanical precision\",\n          \"emphasis\": [\"metallic surfaces\", \"crew hands\"],\n          \"de_emphasis\": [\"faces\", \"background\"],\n          \"atmosphere_priority\": \"claustrophobic, industrial\",\n          \"era_technical_package\": {\n            \"period\": \"1940s WWII\",\n            \"color_mode\": \"B&W\",\n            \"camera_model\": \"Speed Graphic 4x5\",\n            \"lens\": \"Kodak Ektar 127mm f/4.7\",\n            \"film_stock\": \"Kodak Tri-X 400\",\n            \"grain\": \"visible medium grain\",\n            \"sharpness\": \"medium\",\n            \"contrast\": \"high\",\n            \"negative_markers\": [\"color\", \"modern\", \"digital\"]\n          }\n        },\n        \"character_identity\": { ... },\n        \"reference_strategy\": [ ... ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n- **Required era_technical_package fields**: `period`, `color_mode`, `camera_model`, `lens`, `film_stock`, `grain`, `sharpness`, `contrast`, `negative_markers`\n- **Temperature**: 0.5\n\n### Step 08: JSON Prompt Builder\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_08_json_prompt_builder.py`\n- **Type**: LLM (Gemini text, parallel batches)\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_text`\n- **Batch size**: 5 AI slots per call\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(6)\n- **Purpose**: Technical translator. Takes creative briefs from Step 07 and translates each into the exact JSON format that produces best results with Gemini Image API. Makes zero creative decisions.\n- **Aspect ratio mapping**:\n  - `hero`, `sequence_element`, `background` -> `16:9`\n  - `sticker`, `grid_element` -> `1:1`\n  - Grid positions override: `left_half`/`right_half` -> `9:16`\n- **Required JSON sections**: `metadata`, `subject`, `camera`, `lighting`, `color_restriction`, `texture_and_imperfections`, `composition`, `quality_control`\n- **Input**: Step 07 creative_briefs + Step 03 compositions (for role/aspect)\n- **Output**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"json_prompts\": [\n      {\n        \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n        \"scene_id\": 1,\n        \"role\": \"sticker\",\n        \"aspect_ratio\": \"1:1\",\n        \"json_prompt\": {\n          \"metadata\": { \"era\": \"1940s\", \"style\": \"documentary\" },\n          \"subject\": { \"main\": \"torpedo loading mechanism\", \"action\": \"...\" },\n          \"camera\": { \"model\": \"Speed Graphic\", \"film_stock\": \"Tri-X 400\", ... },\n          \"lighting\": { ... },\n          \"color_restriction\": { \"mode\": \"black_and_white\", ... },\n          \"texture_and_imperfections\": { ... },\n          \"composition\": { \"framing\": \"close-up\", ... },\n          \"quality_control\": { \"positive\": [...], \"negative\": [...] }\n        },\n        \"reference_images\": [\n          {\n            \"ref_label\": \"REFERENCE_IMAGE_1\",\n            \"image_id\": \"uuid-...\",\n            \"role\": \"R1_atmosphere\",\n            \"instruction\": \"extract lighting mood\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n- **Validation**: Checks required sections, quality_control counts (negative >= 5, positive >= 3), camera specifics, reference label ordering.\n- **Temperature**: 0.3\n\n### Step 09: AI Image Generator\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_09_ai_image_generator.py`\n- **Type**: Gemini Image API + OpenRouter fallback\n- **Model group**: `bloco2_image`\n- **Concurrency**: Sem(3)\n- **Timeout**: 900s (15 min) per slot\n- **Keys before rewrite**: 5\n- **Purpose**: Pure executor. Takes JSON prompts from Step 08 + reference images and calls Gemini Image API. Makes zero creative decisions. Handles key rotation, retries, and Safe Prompt Rewriter.\n- **Generation flow**:\n  1. Load reference images (from dataset registry / portrait lookup)\n  2. Inject portrait as FIRST reference (\"IDENTITY LOCK\") if character slot\n  3. Add reference images with labels (REFERENCE_IMAGE_1, REFERENCE_IMAGE_2, ...)\n  4. Append prompt text LAST\n  5. Call Gemini Image API with `response_modalities=[\"IMAGE\", \"TEXT\"]` and `aspect_ratio`\n  6. On `CONTENT_BLOCK` -> escalate Safe Prompt Rewriter (SPR) level\n  7. After 5 keys with same prompt -> escalate SPR level\n  8. SPR has 4 levels before exhaustion\n- **Safe Prompt Rewriter** (`safe_prompt_rewriter_v2.py` / `SceneRewriter`): Rewrites the JSON prompt on safety blocks with escalating abstraction levels.\n- **Input**: Step 08 json_prompts + dataset image_registry + Step 0c portraits + Step 03 compositions (for char_map)\n- **Output**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"generated\": [\n      {\n        \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n        \"scene_number\": 1,\n        \"role\": \"sticker\",\n        \"output_path\": \"images/scene_001_sticker_1.png\",\n        \"aspect_ratio\": \"1:1\",\n        \"attempts\": 2,\n        \"rewritten\": false,\n        \"success\": true,\n        \"final_key\": \"AIzaSy...\",\n        \"latency_ms\": 8500,\n        \"references_used\": 3\n      }\n    ],\n    \"failed_slots\": [],\n    \"successful\": 15,\n    \"failed\": 0,\n    \"rewritten\": 2\n  }\n  ```\n- **Output files**: `{video_dir}/images/scene_{NNN}_{role}[_{index}].png`\n- **FATAL behavior**: If `NoKeysAvailableError` persists, the entire Step 09 raises (aborts pipeline). If any slots fail, Step 10 also raises `PipelineError`.\n\n### Step 10: Visual Spec Assembler\n- **File**: `bloco2v2/step_10_visual_spec_assembler.py`\n- **Type**: Pure Python, zero LLM\n- **Purpose**: Final assembler that downloads real images, resolves trigger word timestamps via WhisperX alignment, checks for failed AI slots, and merges ALL upstream outputs into `visual_spec.json`.\n- **Sub-operations**:\n  1. **Failed slot check**: Pipeline FAILS if any AI slot failed in Step 09\n  2. **Real image downloads**: Downloads from Supabase Storage to `{video_dir}/images/` (Sem(20))\n  3. **AI Recovery**: If real image downloads fail, runs Steps 07->08->09 for replacement AI images\n  4. **Trigger timestamp resolution**: 5-pass system (aligned, exact, prefix, contains, fallback 30%)\n  5. **Duration validation**: Checks element durations against scene audio duration\n  6. **VideoSpecGeneratorV2**: Generates final merged visual_spec.json\n- **Input**: ALL previous steps\n- **Output**: `{ \"visual_spec_path\": \"...\", \"assembly_log\": {...} }`\n- **Output files**:\n  - `{video_dir}/visual_spec.json` -- THE output consumed by Bloco 3\n  - `{video_dir}/visual_spec_debug.json` -- debug version with source metadata\n  - `{video_dir}/assembly_log.json` -- timing, download stats, trigger resolutions\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Image Generation Problem\n\n### Current Cost Issues\n\nBloco 2 v2 uses **Gemini Image API** and **OpenRouter** for AI image generation. The costs per video are driven by:\n\n1. **Text LLM calls** (Steps 00a, 01, 02a, 03, 03b, 04, 05, 06, 07, 08): ~10-30 calls per video at ~$0.15/M input + $0.60/M output tokens (Gemini 2.5 Flash). Approximate cost: **$0.01-0.05 per video**.\n\n2. **Image generation** (Steps 00c, 09): This is where costs explode. Each AI image slot costs:\n   - Gemini Image API: ~1,290 output tokens per image (~$0.001 per image on free tier, much more on paid)\n   - OpenRouter fallback: variable pricing per model\n   - A typical video has 15-40 AI image slots = **$0.02-0.10+ per video on image gen alone**\n\n3. **Rate limits are the real problem**: With 37 free Gemini keys, only 20 RPD per key = 740 images/day across ALL accounts. With 11 channels producing multiple videos, this is a severe bottleneck.\n\n### Why APIs are Unviable at Scale\n\n- **Free tier**: 20 RPD per key per model. With 37 keys = 740/day. At 30 images/video, that is ~24 videos/day maximum.\n- **Tier 1** (billing enabled): Higher limits but each image costs $0.001-0.01+. At 30 images/video x 30 videos/day x 11 channels = **$10-100+/day**.\n- **Content policy blocks**: Historical/military content triggers safety filters frequently. The Safe Prompt Rewriter adds overhead and still fails sometimes.\n- **Quality inconsistency**: Gemini Image API produces inconsistent quality, especially for period-accurate historical photographs.\n\n### Why OpenClaw / Browser Automation is the Replacement\n\nBrowser-based image generation (Midjourney, Flux, DALL-E via web) can:\n- Bypass API rate limits entirely\n- Access subscription-based pricing ($10-30/month unlimited vs per-image)\n- Use better models not available via API\n- Avoid content policy issues present in API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Flow\n\n### Bloco 1 -> Bloco 2\n\nBloco 1 produces:\n- **Screenplay** (`screenplay` dict): Complete narration broken into scenes with text, scene_numbers, video_context\n- **Clips metadata** (`clips_metadata` dict): Per-scene audio clips with duration_ms, word_timestamps (WhisperX)\n- **Dataset images** (`dataset_images` dict): Curated images from the Dataset System (entities, assets, image_registry)\n\n### Bloco 2 -> Bloco 3\n\nBloco 2 produces:\n- **`visual_spec.json`**: The SOLE output consumed by Bloco 3. Contains everything Bloco 3 needs to render the video.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Input Contract\n\nBloco 2 v2 Orchestrator constructor signature:\n\n```python\nBloco2V2Orchestrator(\n    video_dir: Path,          # e.g., \"data/en/torpedo_boats\"\n    account_dir: Path,        # e.g., \"accounts/003_wwii_photography\"\n    account_id: str,          # e.g., \"003\"\n    language: str,            # e.g., \"en\"\n    screenplay: dict,         # Full screenplay from Bloco 1\n    clips_metadata: dict,     # Per-scene audio clips from Bloco 1\n    dataset_images: dict,     # Dataset export from Dataset System\n    key_manager: Any,         # ApiKeyManager / KMS client\n    video_name: str,          # e.g., \"torpedo_boats\"\n)\n```\n\n### Screenplay Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"video_context\": {\n    \"title\": \"Japanese Torpedo Boats in WWII\",\n    \"era\": \"1940s\",\n    \"theme\": \"military_history\"\n  },\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_number\": 1,\n      \"text\": \"In the early hours of December 7th, 1941...\",\n      \"scene_text\": \"In the early hours of December 7th, 1941...\",\n      \"narration\": \"In the early hours of December 7th, 1941...\",\n      \"interpretation_mode\": \"literal\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Clips Metadata Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"1\": {\n    \"clip_path\": \"audio/scene_001.wav\",\n    \"duration_ms\": 5200,\n    \"word_timestamps\": [\n      { \"word\": \"In\", \"start\": 0.0, \"end\": 0.15 },\n      { \"word\": \"the\", \"start\": 0.15, \"end\": 0.25 }\n    ],\n    \"start_frame\": 0,\n    \"end_frame\": 156\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAlso supports per-clip WhisperX JSON files at `{video_dir}/clips/clip_{NNN}_whisperx.json`.\n\n### Dataset Images Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"entities\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"uuid-entity-...\",\n      \"entity_key\": \"yamamoto_isoroku\",\n      \"formal_name\": \"Admiral Isoroku Yamamoto\",\n      \"entity_type\": \"persons\",\n      \"sub_type\": \"military_leader\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"assets\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"uuid-asset-...\",\n      \"entity_id\": \"uuid-entity-...\",\n      \"storage_url\": \"https://supabase.co/storage/...\",\n      \"thumbnail_url\": \"https://...\",\n      \"width\": 800,\n      \"height\": 600,\n      \"relevance_score\": 0.95,\n      \"curation_status\": \"accepted\",\n      \"use_type\": \"direct_footage\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"High quality WWII-era photograph...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"image_registry\": {\n    \"uuid-asset-...\": {\n      \"local_path\": \"C:/path/to/downloaded/image.jpg\",\n      \"source\": \"storage\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"export_metadata\": {\n    \"total_entities\": 12,\n    \"accepted_assets\": 45,\n    \"broll_assets\": 8\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Output Contract\n\n### visual_spec.json (THE Output)\n\nThis is the CRITICAL output that Bloco 3 reads. Its format is defined by `VideoSpecGeneratorV2` in `video_spec_generator_v2.py`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"video_name\": \"torpedo_boats\",\n    \"language\": \"en\",\n    \"account_id\": \"003\",\n    \"total_scenes\": 25,\n    \"bloco2_version\": \"v2\",\n    \"total_images\": 38,\n    \"ai_generated\": 22,\n    \"real_from_dataset\": 16,\n    \"composition_types\": {\n      \"hero_simple\": 10,\n      \"hero_with_stickers\": 8,\n      \"sequence\": 4,\n      \"composition_grid\": 2,\n      \"hero_with_sequence\": 1\n    }\n  },\n  \"characters\": [\n    {\n      \"char_id\": \"char_001\",\n      \"name\": \"Admiral Yamamoto\",\n      \"is_famous\": true,\n      \"portrait_path\": \"portraits/char_001_portrait.png\",\n      \"scenes_present\": [1, 3, 5, 8]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_index\": 1,\n      \"scene_text\": \"In the early hours of December 7th, 1941...\",\n      \"visual\": {\n        \"image_path\": \"images/scene_001_hero.png\"\n      },\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"clip_path\": \"audio/scene_001.wav\",\n        \"duration_ms\": 5200,\n        \"word_timestamps\": [\n          { \"word\": \"In\", \"start\": 0.0, \"end\": 0.15 }\n        ]\n      },\n      \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": 0,\n        \"end_frame\": 156\n      },\n      \"characters_in_scene\": {\n        \"character_names\": [\"Admiral Yamamoto\"]\n      },\n      \"visual_direction\": {\n        \"composition_type\": \"hero_with_stickers\",\n        \"elements\": [\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_hero\",\n            \"role\": \"hero\",\n            \"file\": \"images/scene_001_hero.png\",\n            \"animation\": \"slow_zoom_in\",\n            \"enter\": \"fade_in\",\n            \"exit\": \"crossfade_to_next\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"scene_1_sticker_1\",\n            \"role\": \"sticker\",\n            \"file\": \"images/scene_001_sticker_1.png\",\n            \"animation\": \"pop_in\",\n            \"position\": \"bottom_right\",\n            \"size\": \"medium\",\n            \"trigger_word\": \"torpedo\",\n            \"trigger_ts\": 1.85,\n            \"trigger_match\": \"aligned\",\n            \"enter\": \"scale_up\",\n            \"exit\": \"fade_out\",\n            \"duration\": 2.5\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Key Output Files\n\n| File | Path | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `visual_spec.json` | `{video_dir}/visual_spec.json` | **THE output** consumed by Bloco 3 |\n| `visual_spec_debug.json` | `{video_dir}/visual_spec_debug.json` | Debug version with source metadata |\n| `assembly_log.json` | `{video_dir}/assembly_log.json` | Timing, download stats, trigger resolutions |\n| AI images | `{video_dir}/images/scene_{NNN}_{role}[_{idx}].png` | Generated AI images |\n| Real images | `{video_dir}/images/scene_{NNN}_{role}[_{idx}].png` | Downloaded dataset images |\n| Portraits | `{video_dir}/portraits/{char_id}_portrait.png` | AI-generated character portraits |\n| Pipeline summary | `{video_dir}/checkpoints/04_pipeline_summary.json` | Aggregated stats |\n| Step logs | `{video_dir}/bloco2_v2_logs/step_{id}_{name}/` | Per-step artifacts |\n\n---\n\n## 7. LLM Calls Per Step\n\nFor a typical 25-scene video with 12 entities and 45 dataset images:\n\n| Step | LLM Type | Model Group | Calls | Multimodal | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------------|-------|------------|-------|\n| 00 | None | - | 0 | No | Pure Python |\n| 00a | Text | `bloco2_text` | 3 | No | 25 scenes / 10 batch = 3 batches |\n| 00b | None | - | 0 | No | Pure Python |\n| 00c | Text + Image | `bloco2_text` + `bloco2_image` | ~10 | Yes (Phase 2) | 5 chars x 2 phases each |\n| 01 | Text (multimodal) | `bloco2_text` | 8 | Yes (images) | 45 images / 6 batch = 8 batches |\n| 02a | Text | `bloco2_text` | 2 | No | 25 scenes / 15 batch = 2 chunks |\n| 02b | None | - | 0 | No | Pure Python |\n| 03 | Text | `bloco2_text` | 4 | No | 25 scenes / 7 batch = 4 batches |\n| 03b | Text | `bloco2_text` | 1 | No | Single call reviews all |\n| 04 | Text (multimodal) | `bloco2_text` | 4 | Yes (images) | 20 real-slot scenes / 5 batch |\n| 05 | Text | `bloco2_vision` | 5 | No | 25 scenes / 5 batch |\n| 06 | Text (multimodal) | `bloco2_vision` | 5 | Yes (refs) | 20 AI slots / 4 batch |\n| 07 | Text | `bloco2_text` | 5 | No | 20 AI slots / 4 batch |\n| 08 | Text | `bloco2_text` | 4 | No | 20 AI slots / 5 batch |\n| 09 | Image gen | `bloco2_image` | ~20 | Yes (refs) | 1 per AI slot |\n| 10 | None | - | 0 | No | Pure Python (may run 07-09 for recovery) |\n\n**Total approximate**: ~70-80 LLM calls per video, of which ~20 are image generation.\n\n### Cost Estimate Per Video\n\n| Category | Calls | Approx Cost |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| Text LLM (Gemini 2.5 Flash free tier) | ~50-60 | $0.00 (free) |\n| Image gen (Gemini Image API free tier) | ~20-25 | $0.00 (free, limited RPD) |\n| Image gen (paid/OpenRouter fallback) | ~5-10 | $0.01-0.05 |\n| **Total per video** | ~75-85 | **$0.01-0.05** |\n\n---\n\n## 8. KMS / API Key Usage\n\n### Model Groups\n\n| Model Group | Used By | Models in Cascade | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------|-------------------|---------|\n| `bloco2_text` | Steps 00a, 00c(P1), 01, 02a, 03, 03b, 04, 07, 08 | Gemini 2.5 Flash -> Gemini 3.1 Flash Lite -> OR fallback | Text reasoning (JSON output) |\n| `bloco2_image` | Steps 00c(P2), 09 | Gemini 3.1 Flash Image Preview -> OR image gen | AI image generation |\n| `bloco2_vision` | Steps 05, 06 | Same as `bloco2_text` | Text with multimodal input |\n\n### Cascade Chain (Free Tier)\n\n1. **Gemini 2.5 Flash** (primary, quality)\n2. **Gemini 3.1 Flash Lite** (high-volume fallback)\n3. **OpenRouter** (paid fallback after 5 tier1 429s)\n\n### Tier Escalation\n\n```python\nFREE_429_THRESHOLD = 5   # after 5 consecutive free-tier 429s -> exclude free\nTIER1_429_THRESHOLD = 5  # after 5 consecutive tier1 429s -> exclude free + tier1\n```\n\nWhen both free and tier1 are excluded, only paid OpenRouter keys remain.\n\n### Key Rotation Pattern (Legacy: Pool-Size x Rounds)\n\nMost steps use the legacy pattern:\n- `MAX_ROUNDS = 3`\n- `COOLDOWN_BETWEEN_ROUNDS = 60` seconds\n- Pool size = number of available keys (typically 50+)\n- Per each round: try each key in pool\n- Between rounds: 60s cooldown\n\nSteps 00c and 09 use the newer **timeout-based pattern**:\n- Retry until per-slot deadline (600s for portraits, 900s for images)\n- No round/pool structure -- just keep trying keys until timeout\n- Uses `NoKeysAvailableError` with `retry_after_ms` for smart waiting\n\n### Error Reporting to KMS\n\nEvery step reports successes and errors to KMS via:\n- `report_kms_success(ctx, step_name, model, input_tokens, output_tokens, modality_details)`\n- `report_kms_error(ctx, step_name, model, error)`\n\n### OpenRouter Integration\n\nWhen KMS returns an OpenRouter key:\n- **Text calls**: `call_openrouter_json()` via OpenAI SDK with `response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"}`\n- **Multimodal text**: `call_openrouter_multimodal()` converts Gemini parts to OpenAI vision format\n- **Image generation**: `generate_image_openrouter()` via OpenAI SDK with `modalities=[\"image\", \"text\"]`\n\n---\n\n## 9. Error Handling\n\n### Unified Error Classifier\n\nFile: `bloco2v2/error_classifier.py`\n\nAll steps use a single `classify_error()` function that returns one of:\n\n| Category | Action | Triggers |\n|----------|--------|----------|\n| `CONTENT_BLOCK` | Safe Prompt Rewriter | safety/blocked/content_filter/harm, finish_reason PROHIBITED_CONTENT/SAFETY |\n| `RATE_LIMIT` | Rotate key, tier escalation | 429, resource_exhausted, quota |\n| `AUTH_ERROR` | Report key as invalid, rotate | 401, 403, unauthorized, invalid+key |\n| `OTHER` | Try next key with backoff | Everything else |\n\n### Per-Step Retry Behavior\n\n| Step | Pattern | Max Duration | On Exhaustion |\n|------|---------|-------------|---------------|\n| 00a-03b | Pool x 3 rounds | ~3 min per batch | Return empty (graceful degradation) |\n| 04 | Pool x 3 rounds | ~3 min per batch | Return None (Step 10 handles missing) |\n| 05-08 | Pool x 3 rounds | ~3 min per batch | Return empty list |\n| 00c | Timeout-based | 600s per character | Mark portrait as failed, continue |\n| 09 | Timeout-based | 900s per slot | Mark slot as failed, Step 10 raises PipelineError |\n\n### Safe Prompt Rewriter (SPR)\n\nUsed in Steps 00c (portrait) and 09 (image gen):\n- **Level 1**: Remove character name, keep physical description\n- **Level 2**: Remove distinctive features, generalize\n- **Level 3**: Fully generic period-appropriate figure\n- **Level 4**: Maximum abstraction\n\nTrigger: After `KEYS_BEFORE_REWRITE = 5` keys tried with same prompt, or immediately on `CONTENT_BLOCK`.\n\n### Circuit Breaker\n\n```python\nCONSECUTIVE_429_THRESHOLD = 15  # consecutive 429s before circuit breaker\nCIRCUIT_BREAKER_PAUSE = 40      # seconds to pause\n```\n\n### AI Recovery (Step 10)\n\nWhen real image downloads fail in Step 10:\n1. Builds recovery slots with `source: \"ai_recovery\"`\n2. Runs Steps 07 -> 08 -> 09 inline for replacement images\n3. Merges results back into pipeline state\n\n---\n\n## 10. Per-Account Configuration\n\n### YAML Config Fields Controlling Bloco 2\n\nFrom the sample config `003-en.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\n# Engine selection (CRITICAL -- determines v1 vs v2)\nbloco2_engine: \"v2\"\n\n# Key Management System\nkey_management:\n  enabled: true\n  kms_url: \"https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app\"\n  machine_id: \"M1\"\n  fallback_to_local: true\n\n# Dataset integration\ndataset:\n  enabled: true\n  trigger_word: \"wwii_photo_style\"\n  drive_folder_id: \"...\"\n  auto_upload: true\n\n# Visual style\ntheme_style: \"wwii_photography\"\n```\n\n### Prompt Files (Per-Account)\n\nPrompts are loaded with fallback: `{account_dir}/prompts/bloco2_v2/{language}/` -> `{account_dir}/prompts/bloco2_v2/_shared/`\n\nRequired prompt files:\n| Step | Prompt File |\n|------|-------------|\n| 00a | `00a_character_identifier.txt` |\n| 00c | `00c_portrait_generator.txt` |\n| 01 | `01_image_profiler.txt` |\n| 02a | `02a_entity_alias_generator.txt` |\n| 03 | `03_composition_planner.txt` |\n| 03b | `03b_composition_reviewer.txt` |\n| 04 | `04_image_selector.txt` |\n| 05 | `05_visual_director.txt` |\n| 06 | `06_reference_strategist.txt` |\n| 07 | `07_prompt_director.txt` |\n| 08 | `08_json_prompt_builder.txt` |\n\n### Era Technical Package\n\nThe era_technical_package is account-specific and defines the photographic era authenticity:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"camera\": \"Speed Graphic 4x5 press camera\",\n  \"lens\": \"Kodak Ektar 127mm f/4.7\",\n  \"film_stock\": \"Kodak Tri-X 400\",\n  \"grain\": \"visible medium grain, slight halation on highlights\",\n  \"color_profile\": \"B&W high contrast, deep blacks\",\n  \"printing\": \"fiber-based gelatin silver print\"\n}\n```\n\nCan be set via:\n1. `portrait_generator.era_technical_package` in YAML config\n2. Default in Step 00c code (Account 003 WWII defaults)\n\n---\n\n## 11. What the Replacement Must Produce\n\n> **THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT SECTION. The OpenClaw Bloco 2 replacement must produce outputs in this EXACT format so Bloco 3 can consume them unchanged.**\n\n### Primary Output: visual_spec.json\n\nThe replacement must write a file at `{video_dir}/visual_spec.json` with this exact structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"video_name\": \"<string>\",\n    \"language\": \"<string>\",\n    \"account_id\": \"<string>\",\n    \"total_scenes\": \"<int>\",\n    \"bloco2_version\": \"v2\",\n    \"total_images\": \"<int>\",\n    \"ai_generated\": \"<int>\",\n    \"real_from_dataset\": \"<int>\",\n    \"composition_types\": {\n      \"<composition_type>\": \"<count>\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"characters\": [\n    {\n      \"char_id\": \"<string>\",\n      \"name\": \"<string>\",\n      \"is_famous\": \"<bool>\",\n      \"portrait_path\": \"<relative_path_or_empty>\",\n      \"scenes_present\": [\"<int>\", \"...\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_index\": \"<int>\",\n      \"scene_text\": \"<string>\",\n      \"visual\": {\n        \"image_path\": \"<relative_path>\"\n      },\n      \"audio\": {\n        \"clip_path\": \"<relative_path>\",\n        \"duration_ms\": \"<int>\",\n        \"word_timestamps\": [\n          { \"word\": \"<string>\", \"start\": \"<float>\", \"end\": \"<float>\" }\n        ]\n      },\n      \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": \"<int>\",\n        \"end_frame\": \"<int>\"\n      },\n      \"characters_in_scene\": {\n        \"character_names\": [\"<string>\", \"...\"]\n      },\n      \"visual_direction\": {\n        \"composition_type\": \"<string>\",\n        \"elements\": [\n          {\n            \"slot_id\": \"<string>\",\n            \"role\": \"<string>\",\n            \"file\": \"<relative_path>\",\n            \"animation\": \"<string>\",\n            \"enter\": \"<string>\",\n            \"exit\": \"<string>\",\n            \"position\": \"<string (optional)>\",\n            \"size\": \"<string (optional)>\",\n            \"trigger_word\": \"<string (optional)>\",\n            \"trigger_ts\": \"<float (optional)>\",\n            \"trigger_match\": \"<string (optional)>\",\n            \"duration\": \"<float|'full_scene' (optional)>\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Required Image Files on Disk\n\nAll image paths in `visual_spec.json` are RELATIVE to `{video_dir}`. The replacement must place:\n\n1. **Hero/scene images**: `{video_dir}/images/scene_{NNN}_{role}[_{index}].png`\n   - Naming convention: `scene_001_hero.png`, `scene_001_sticker_1.png`, `scene_003_seq_1.png`, `scene_005_grid_1.png`\n   - Role abbreviations: `hero`, `sticker`, `seq` (sequence_element), `grid` (grid_element), `bg` (background)\n\n2. **Portrait images** (optional): `{video_dir}/portraits/{char_id}_portrait.png`\n\n### Field-by-Field Contract\n\n#### metadata (required)\n- `video_name`: string, video identifier\n- `language`: string, ISO language code\n- `account_id`: string, e.g. \"003\"\n- `total_scenes`: int, number of scenes\n- `bloco2_version`: string, set to \"v2\"\n- `total_images`: int, total images (AI + real)\n- `ai_generated`: int, count of AI-generated images\n- `real_from_dataset`: int, count of real dataset images\n- `composition_types`: dict mapping composition type names to counts\n\n#### characters (required, can be empty list)\n- `char_id`: string, unique character identifier\n- `name`: string, character display name\n- `is_famous`: bool\n- `portrait_path`: string, relative path to portrait PNG (empty if no portrait)\n- `scenes_present`: list of int scene indices\n\n#### scenes[].visual.image_path (CRITICAL for v1 compat)\n- Relative path to the PRIMARY/HERO image for the scene\n- This is what Bloco 3 v1 reads as the scene's image\n- Must point to the hero or background element's file\n\n#### scenes[].audio (passthrough from Bloco 1)\n- `clip_path`: relative path to audio WAV file\n- `duration_ms`: int, scene audio duration in milliseconds\n- `word_timestamps`: list of `{word, start, end}` dicts from WhisperX\n\n#### scenes[].timing (passthrough from Bloco 1)\n- `start_frame`: int\n- `end_frame`: int\n\n#### scenes[].characters_in_scene\n- `character_names`: list of character name strings present in this scene\n\n#### scenes[].visual_direction (CRITICAL for Bloco 3 v2)\n- `composition_type`: one of `hero_simple`, `hero_with_stickers`, `sequence`, `composition_grid`, `hero_with_sequence`\n- `elements[]`: ordered list of visual elements\n\n#### elements[] fields\n| Field | Required | Type | Values |\n|-------|----------|------|--------|\n| `slot_id` | Yes | string | `scene_{N}_{role}[_{idx}]` |\n| `role` | Yes | string | `hero`, `sticker`, `sequence_element`, `grid_element`, `background` |\n| `file` | Yes | string | Relative path to image PNG |\n| `animation` | Yes | string | `slow_zoom_in`, `static`, `pop_in`, `pan_left`, `pan_right`, `ken_burns`, etc. |\n| `enter` | Yes | string | `fade_in`, `fade_in_slow`, `fade_in_from_black`, `cut`, `crossfade_from_previous`, `scale_up` |\n| `exit` | Yes | string | `crossfade_to_next`, `fade_out`, `fade_out_to_black`, `cut`, `fade_out_slow` |\n| `position` | Stickers only | string | `top_left`, `top_center`, `top_right`, `center_left`, `center`, `center_right`, `bottom_left`, `bottom_center`, `bottom_right` |\n| `size` | Stickers only | string | `small`, `medium`, `large` |\n| `trigger_word` | Stickers only | string | Word from narration that triggers sticker appearance |\n| `trigger_ts` | Stickers only | float | Timestamp in seconds when trigger word is spoken |\n| `trigger_match` | Stickers only | string | `aligned`, `exact`, `prefix`, `contains`, `fallback_30pct` |\n| `duration` | Optional | float or string | Duration in seconds, or `\"full_scene\"` for heroes |\n| `order` | Sequences only | int | Display order within sequence |\n| `grid_position` | Grids only | string | `top_left`, `top_right`, `bottom_left`, `bottom_right`, `left_half`, `right_half`, `full_width` |\n\n### Element Z-Index / Sort Order\n\nElements in each scene MUST be sorted by:\n1. `hero`/`background` first (priority 0)\n2. `sequence_element` (priority 1, sorted by `order`)\n3. `grid_element` (priority 2, sorted by grid_position)\n4. `sticker` (priority 3, sorted by `trigger_ts`)\n\n### Image Specifications\n\n| Role | Aspect Ratio | Format |\n|------|-------------|--------|\n| hero | 16:9 | PNG |\n| sequence_element | 16:9 | PNG |\n| background | 16:9 | PNG |\n| sticker | 1:1 | PNG |\n| grid_element | 1:1 (default), 9:16 (left/right_half), 16:9 (full_width) | PNG |\n\n### What the Replacement Does NOT Need to Produce\n\nThe replacement does NOT need to:\n- Generate checkpoint files (those are internal to v2 pipeline)\n- Produce `visual_spec_debug.json` (optional debugging aid)\n- Produce `assembly_log.json` (optional metrics)\n- Run the StepLogger / bloco2_v2_logs\n- Report to KMS\n\nThe ONLY mandatory output is `visual_spec.json` + the actual image files on disk at the paths referenced in the JSON.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Bloco 2 v1 (Legacy Reference)\n\n### Overview\n\nBloco 2 v1 is the original 5-step pipeline. It is still functional but superseded by v2 for all production accounts.\n\n- **Config flag**: `bloco2_engine: \"v1\"` (or absent, defaults to v1)\n- **Helper file**: `bloco2v1_kms_helper.py`\n\n### v1 vs v2 Differences\n\n| Aspect | v1 | v2 |\n|--------|----|----|\n| Steps | 5 (steps 4-8 in overall numbering) | 15 (steps 00-10) |\n| Dataset integration | No | Yes (Dataset System) |\n| Character identification | No | Yes (00a, 00b, 00c) |\n| Real image selection | No | Yes (multimodal image selector) |\n| Composition types | hero_simple only | 5 types (hero, stickers, sequence, grid) |\n| Visual direction | Basic | Rich (animations, triggers, positions) |\n| Reference strategy | None | Multimodal reference analysis |\n| Portrait generation | No | Yes (AI portraits with identity lock) |\n| Era authenticity | Basic prompt instructions | Structured era_technical_package |\n| Safe Prompt Rewriter | Basic | SceneRewriter v2 with 4 levels |\n\n### v1 KMS Helper\n\n`bloco2v1_kms_helper.py` provides:\n- `call_kms_text_json()`: Sync Gemini text call via KMS with full pool retry\n- `KmsImageAdapter`: Wraps KmsSyncClient to match ApiKeyManager interface for image agents\n- `run_parallel_batches()`: ThreadPoolExecutor parallel runner\n\nUses the same retry constants as v2: `MAX_ROUNDS=3`, `COOLDOWN_BETWEEN_ROUNDS=60s`, `DELAY_AFTER_RATE_LIMIT=5s`.\n\n---\n\n## Appendix: File Reference\n\n### Bloco 2 v2 Core Files\n\n| File | Path | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|------|-------|---------|\n| Orchestrator | `shared/processors/bloco2v2_orchestrator.py` | ~660 | 15-step pipeline coordinator |\n| Step 00a | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_00a_character_identifier.py` | ~420 | Character identification |\n| Step 00b | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_00b_character_entity_matcher.py` | ~230 | Character-entity matching (Python) |\n| Step 00c | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_00c_portrait_generator.py` | ~930 | Portrait generation |\n| Step 01 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_01_image_profiler.py` | ~410 | Image profiling (multimodal) |\n| Step 02a | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_02a_entity_alias_generator.py` | ~360 | Entity alias generation |\n| Step 02b | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_02b_entity_scene_mapper.py` | ~280 | Entity-scene mapping (Python) |\n| Step 03 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_03_composition_planner.py` | ~500+ | Composition planning |\n| Step 03b | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_03b_composition_reviewer.py` | ~415 | Composition review |\n| Step 04 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_04_image_selector.py` | ~730 | Image selection (multimodal) |\n| Step 05 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_05_visual_director.py` | ~830 | Visual direction |\n| Step 06 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_06_reference_strategist.py` | ~670 | Reference strategy (multimodal) |\n| Step 07 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_07_prompt_director.py` | ~620 | Creative briefs |\n| Step 08 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_08_json_prompt_builder.py` | ~570 | JSON prompt building |\n| Step 09 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_09_ai_image_generator.py` | ~750 | AI image generation |\n| Step 10 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_10_visual_spec_assembler.py` | ~870 | Final assembly |\n\n### Supporting Files\n\n| File | Path | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| VideoSpecGeneratorV2 | `shared/processors/video_spec_generator_v2.py` | Generates visual_spec.json |\n| Error Classifier | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/error_classifier.py` | Unified error classification |\n| Retry Helper | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/retry_helper.py` | Retry constants + OpenRouter calls |\n| OR Image Helper | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/or_image_helper.py` | OpenRouter image generation |\n| Step Logger | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/step_logger.py` | Structured logging |\n| KMS Error Reporter | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/kms_error_reporter.py` | Error reporting to KMS |\n| Safe Prompt Rewriter v2 | `shared/processors/bloco2v2/safe_prompt_rewriter_v2.py` | Prompt safety rewriting |\n| Portrait Safe Rewriter | `shared/processors/portrait_safe_rewriter.py` | Portrait-specific rewriting |\n| GenAI Factory | `shared/clients/genai_factory.py` | Gemini client creation |\n| Bloco2 v1 KMS Helper | `shared/processors/bloco2v1_kms_helper.py` | Legacy v1 helper |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829920}}
{"type":"message","id":"17fefaee","parentId":"b9f4f02c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.945Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_v9sMfFizhRRDsSGeTs25TtCC|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb408190997b8840c6bdd94e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 3 GPT Planners & Account Configuration System\n\n> Production documentation as of 2026-04-02. Documents the ONLY LLM calls in Bloco 3 (Phase 2 + Phase 4 planners) and the account/machine configuration system that controls the entire pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [Planner Overview](#1-planner-overview)\n2. [Planner Prompts](#2-planner-prompts)\n3. [Model Configuration](#3-model-configuration)\n4. [Account YAML Schema](#4-account-yaml-schema)\n5. [Resource System](#5-resource-system)\n6. [Machine Config](#6-machine-config)\n7. [Config Loading Flow](#7-config-loading-flow)\n8. [Per-Language Variations](#8-per-language-variations)\n9. [Cost Profile](#9-cost-profile)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Planner Overview\n\nBloco 3 uses **4 GPT planners** -- the ONLY LLM calls in the entire block. Everything else (TSX generation, audio resolution, validation) is deterministic Python.\n\n| Planner | Phase | Model | Temp | Batching | Decides |\n|---------|-------|-------|------|----------|---------|\n| **Music Planner** | 2 | GPT-4.1-mini | 0.3 | Global (1 call for entire video) | Which music track for which scene range, mood intent |\n| **SFX Planner** | 2 | GPT-4.1-mini | 0.3 | 12 scenes per batch | Which SFX to place, trigger word, duration hint |\n| **Lettering Planner** | 2 | GPT-4.1-mini | 0.3 | 12 scenes per batch | Which text overlays to show, type, trigger word |\n| **Lettering Style Planner** | 4 | GPT-4.1-mini | 0.3 | 8 scenes per batch | Visual design: component, font, color, position, animation |\n\n### Pipeline Flow\n\n```\nPhase 1: Python Preprocessor\n    -> Generate slim JSONs (stripped catalogs, scene data)\n    -> Generate planner input files (music_planner_input.json, sfx_planner_batch_*.json, lettering_planner_batch_*.json)\n\nPhase 2: 3 GPT Planners (parallel)\n    -> Music Planner (1 global call)\n    -> SFX Planner (N batches of 12 scenes)\n    -> Lettering Planner (N batches of 12 scenes)\n\nPhase 3: Python AudioResolver + Validation\n    -> Validate planner track/SFX names against catalog\n    -> Inject file paths, volumes, frame boundaries\n    -> Invalid names SKIPPED with warning (pipeline continues)\n\nPhase 4: Python TSX Engine + Lettering Style Planner\n    -> Music/Animation/Transition TSX: deterministic Python (zero LLM)\n    -> Lettering: GPT Style Planner (N batches of 8 scenes) -> Python TSX Generator\n    -> SFX TSX: deterministic Python (zero LLM)\n\nPhase 5-6: Merge, Validate, Compile, Render\n```\n\nAll 4 planners run via `_call_planner_kms()` when KMS is enabled, or via direct OpenAI API otherwise. They all use `response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"}` and `max_tokens=4000`.\n\n### Prompt Locations\n\nPrompts are stored **per-account, per-language**:\n\n```\naccounts/{account}/prompts/bloco3/{language}/\n    music_planner_system.txt\n    sfx_planner_system.txt\n    lettering_planner_system.txt\n    lettering_style_planner_system.txt      (v1, language-agnostic, falls back to en/)\n    lettering_style_planner_v2_system.txt   (v2 with template pools, falls back to en/)\n```\n\nThe style planner prompts are language-agnostic (language is embedded in the JSON input), so they exist only under `en/` and are loaded with fallback: current language dir -> `en/` dir.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Planner Prompts\n\n### 2.1 Music Planner\n\n**File:** `music_planner_system.txt` (per-account, per-language)\n\n**Identity:** Film music supervisor creating a cue sheet. Purely analytical -- decides WHICH track, for WHICH scenes, with WHAT emotional intent. Does not decide volume, fade, or technical parameters.\n\n**Input:** JSON with `video_info` (total_scenes, total_duration_frames, fps), `scenes[]` (scene_index, timing, audio.original_text, visual.visual_tone), and `music_catalog` (stripped -- names, descriptions, moods, tags only, no paths/volumes).\n\n**Output:** JSON `{\"sections\": [...]}` where each section has:\n- `section_index` (int, 1-indexed)\n- `label` (descriptive label, e.g. \"Opening - Dark Prelude\")\n- `track_name` (exact name from catalog, no paths/extensions)\n- `scene_range` ([start, end] inclusive)\n- `mood_intent` (1-2 sentences describing emotional intent)\n\n**Key Rules:**\n- Typical 4-10 sections per video (no rigid limit)\n- 100% scene coverage, no gaps, contiguous sections\n- Minimum 5 scenes per section\n- Adjacent sections must use different tracks\n- Follows narrative arc: Opening (low) -> Development (medium) -> Climax (high) -> Resolution (low)\n- Visual tone matching: maps `epic_wide`, `intimate`, `action`, `tension`, etc. to track approaches\n\n### 2.2 SFX Planner\n\n**File:** `sfx_planner_system.txt` (per-account, per-language)\n\n**Identity:** Analytical sound effect placement agent. Identifies WHERE to place SFX for cinematic impact.\n\n**Input:** Batches of ~12 scenes with scene_index, audio.original_text, audio.word_timestamps (compact `[\"word\", start_frame, end_frame]`), visual.visual_tone, visual.what_to_show, and `sfx_catalog` (stripped).\n\n**Output:** JSON `{\"sfx\": [...]}` where each item has:\n- `scene` (int)\n- `sfx_name` (exact name from catalog)\n- `trigger_word` (string or null for transitions)\n- `type` (\"battle\" or \"transition\")\n- `between_scenes` ([int,int], only for transitions)\n- `duration_hint` (\"short\"|\"standard\"|\"extended\"|\"sustained\")\n\n**Key Rules:**\n- Two SFX types: **battle** (synced to spoken word) and **transition** (between scenes)\n- Duration hints: short (1-4s), standard (6-8s), extended (8-15s), sustained (15s+, can span scenes)\n- Density: minimum 2 per 12 scenes, typical 3-5, full video 20-35 total\n- Battle SFX ~60-70%, transition ~30-40%\n- Minimum 3 scenes between battle SFX\n- \"sustained\" for multi-scene action sequences (bombing raids, naval engagements)\n- Silence is powerful -- not every combat mention needs SFX\n\n### 2.3 Lettering Planner\n\n**File:** `lettering_planner_system.txt` (per-account, per-language)\n\n**Identity:** Analytical scanner identifying WHERE visual text should appear. Does NOT decide style, font, color, animation, or position.\n\n**Input:** Batches of 12 scenes with scene_index, start/end frames, audio.original_text, audio.word_timestamps, character list, and `characters_already_letterized` (cross-batch tracking).\n\n**Output:** JSON `{\"letterings\": [...]}` where each item has:\n- `scene` (int)\n- `type` (one of: date, character, location, statistic, comparison, battle, quote, impact, dramatic_phrase, word_cascade, dialogue)\n- `content` (display text, written form with digits, proper capitalization)\n- `context` (1 sentence explaining why this matters, in the same language as content)\n- `trigger_word` (lowercase, matches spoken form from word_timestamps)\n- Additional fields for specific types: `speaker` (quote/dialogue), `dialogue_id` (dialogue), `words` (word_cascade)\n\n**Key Rules -- Mandatory Categories:**\n1. **Dates/Years** -- every date/year mentioned, no exceptions\n2. **Character Names** -- budget of MAX 3 per character across entire video (first mention mandatory, 1 pivotal, 1 closing). Checked via `characters_already_letterized`\n3. **Geographic Locations** -- every named location at first significant mention\n4. **Statistics/Numbers** -- every significant number\n5. **Battle/Event Names** -- every named battle, operation, or event\n6. **Direct Historical Quotes** -- detected via dicendi verbs, quotation marks, narrator-as-character, indirect speech\n\n**Additional Types:**\n- impact (climactic peaks), dramatic_phrase (emotional weight), word_cascade (rapid sequences), dialogue (multi-speaker exchanges), sensory (visceral combat), command (military orders), comparison (two extremes)\n\n**Density:** Minimum 8 per batch of 12 scenes, typical 10-18. At least 2-3 dramatic entries per batch.\n\n**Content Adaptation:** Planner MAY rephrase narrator's words for maximum visual impact (e.g. \"launched without fighter cover\" becomes \"No escort. Into the heart of the fleet.\").\n\n**Trigger Word Rules:**\n- Match spoken form (numbers as words: \"1942\" -> \"nineteen\")\n- Use FIRST distinctive word (not generic words like \"the\", \"battle\")\n- Always lowercase\n- Verify against word_timestamps\n\n### 2.4 Lettering Style Planner\n\n**File:** `lettering_style_planner_system.txt` or `lettering_style_planner_v2_system.txt` (per-account, under `en/` with fallback)\n\n**Identity:** Visual style designer. Receives pre-identified lettering entries (from the Lettering Planner) and assigns ALL visual design decisions.\n\n**Input:** JSON with `video_context` (video_name, language, total_scenes, account_style), `characters`, `plan_entries[]` (with resolved trigger_frames), `style_catalog` (fonts, colors, positions, exit/entrance types, box styles, duration ranges), and `previous_batch_summary` (last fonts/positions/colors used).\n\n**Output:** JSON `{\"styled_entries\": [...]}` where each entry has:\n- `plan_index` (int, references input entry)\n- `component` (React component name, e.g. \"LocationReveal\", \"CharacterIntro\")\n- `trigger_frame` (int)\n- `duration_frames` (int)\n- `scene` (int)\n- `props` (component-specific: font, color, position, entranceType, exitType, text fields, etc.)\n\n**Type-to-Component Mapping (20 components):**\n\n| Planner Type | Component | Key Props |\n|-------------|-----------|-----------|\n| location | LocationReveal | location, detail?, position, font, accentColor, exitType, entranceType? |\n| date | DateReveal | date, subtitle?, position, color, accentColor, font, entranceType? |\n| character (first) | CharacterIntro | name, title, position, nameColor, accentColor, font |\n| character (repeat) | NameTag | name, subtitle?, position, color, accentColor, font |\n| statistic | SingleStatistic | number, label, position, numberColor, numberFont |\n| dramatic_phrase | DramaticReveal | text, emphasisWord?, emphasisColor, font |\n| contrast | ContrastPhrase | firstPart, secondPart, secondColor |\n| impact | ImpactPhrase | text, color, font |\n| battle | BattleNameCard | name, date? |\n| typewriter | TypewriterReveal | text, position, speed, accentColor |\n| word_cascade | WordCascade | words[], staggerFrames, colors[] |\n| quote | QuoteReveal | text, speaker, quoteColor?, speakerColor?, font? |\n| dialogue | DialogueExchange | line1, speaker1, line2, speaker2, color1?, color2? |\n| dialogue_poetic | GradualWordEntry | text, color?, font?, accentColor?, speaker? |\n| sensory | SensoryPhrase | text, color?, font?, shimmerColor? |\n| faction | FactionName | name, position?, color?, font? |\n| comparison | StatisticsComparison | left, right, leftLabel?, rightLabel?, leftColor?, rightColor? |\n| command | SplitCommand | text, color?, accentColor?, font? |\n| epoch | EpochMarker | text, lineColor?, subtitle?, font? |\n| flash | FullscreenFlash | text, color?, font?, bgOpacity? |\n\n**Font Catalog (10 fonts):**\n\n| Key | Google Font | Use Case |\n|-----|------------|----------|\n| serifFont | Cinzel | Dates, historical, treaties |\n| sansFont | Bebas Neue | Statistics, bold numbers, impact |\n| displayFont | Playfair Display | Character intros, dramatic reveals |\n| condensedFont | Oswald | Locations, name tags, labels |\n| heavyFont | Anton | Battles, strong statistics |\n| cleanFont | Montserrat | Subtitles, details, secondary text |\n| techFont | Teko | Military data, factions, comparisons |\n| refinedFont | Raleway | Refined subtitles, epoch markers |\n| crimsonFont | Crimson Text | Quotes, poetic dialogue |\n| russoFont | Russo One | Commands, military orders |\n\n**Multi-alphabet font fallback** is handled via `FONT_FALLBACK` in `lettering_style_catalog.py`:\n- Japanese (ja): Noto Serif JP / Noto Sans JP\n- Korean (ko): Noto Serif KR / Noto Sans KR\n- Arabic (ar): Noto Nasikh Arabic / Noto Sans Arabic / Noto Kufi Arabic\n- Cyrillic (ru): Noto Serif (only for Cinzel, Playfair, Crimson which lack Cyrillic glyphs)\n\n**Color Palette (30+ narrative-coded colors):**\n\n| Color | Hex | Meaning |\n|-------|-----|---------|\n| GOLD | #D4AF37 | Heroes, honor, victory, protagonist |\n| SILVER | #C0C0C0 | Antagonists, cold power, opposition |\n| CRIMSON | #DC143C | Danger, blood, death, battle |\n| BRONZE | #CD7F32 | Ancient, weathered, past empires |\n| STEEL_BLUE | #4682B4 | Tactical, cold, strategic, water |\n| AMBER | #FFBF00 | Urgency, fire, desert, energy |\n| DEEP_RED | #8B0000 | Suffering, siege, desperation |\n| IVORY | #FFFFF0 | Warm, historical, aged elegance |\n| MIDNIGHT_BLUE | #191970 | Night, secrecy, espionage, naval |\n| BLOOD_ORANGE | #CC5500 | Siege, fire, destruction |\n| PARCHMENT | #D4C5A9 | Aged document, old manuscript |\n| DEEP_BURGUNDY | #4A0000 | Dried blood, torture, darkness |\n| TOXIC_GREEN | #39FF14 | Poison, plague, disease |\n| ROYAL_PURPLE | #7B2D8E | Royalty, monarchy, coronation |\n| SAKURA_PINK | #FFB7C5 | Japan, cherry blossoms, Eastern aesthetics |\n| *(and 15+ more)* | | |\n\n**Mandatory Variety Rules:**\n- Never same font 3x in a row\n- Never same position 3x in a row\n- Never same entranceType 3x in a row\n- Overlapping entries MUST be at different positions (MIN_GAP=60 frames at same position)\n- entranceType omitted ~40% of the time for default animation\n- Positions: lower-left, lower-right, center, upper-right, upper-left, upper-center, lower-center\n- Center reserved for emphasis: DramaticReveal, ImpactPhrase, BattleNameCard, SingleStatistic, etc.\n\n**Entrance Types (11):** scale-blur, slide-left, slide-right, slide-up, drop-in, spring-scale, fade-in, zoom-out, slide-down, rotate-in, elastic-pop\n\n**Exit Types (7):** fade, blur, slide-up, slide-down, scale-out, slide-left, slide-right (only LocationReveal uses exitType)\n\n**Box Styles (8):** none, border-left, border-bottom, full-border, bg-gradient, bg-solid, pill, brackets\n\n**Post-Processing (Python, in `validate_styled_entries()`):**\n- Duration clamped to component-specific ranges (e.g. LocationReveal: 105-135 frames at 30fps)\n- Position collision detection: repositions entries that overlap at the same position\n- Sticker occupancy awareness (v2): avoids positions blocked by composition stickers\n- If ALL 7 positions occupied, shortens the longest active entry to free a position\n\n---\n\n## 3. Model Configuration\n\n### GPT-4.1-mini (the planner model)\n\nAll 4 planners use a single model configuration:\n\n```python\n\"gpt-41-mini\": ModelConfig(\n    provider=ModelProvider.OPENAI,\n    model_id=\"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n    input_cost_per_1m=0.40,    # $0.40 per 1M input tokens\n    output_cost_per_1m=1.60,   # $1.60 per 1M output tokens\n    max_context=1_000_000,     # 1M token context window\n    base_url=\"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n    api_key_env=\"OPENAI_API_KEY\",\n)\n```\n\nThe planner model is set at orchestrator initialization via `planner_model` parameter (default: `\"gpt-41-mini\"`).\n\n### KMS Integration\n\nWhen KMS is enabled (`key_management.enabled: true` in YAML), planners acquire OpenAI keys via the KMS:\n\n1. `_call_planner_kms()` uses `CentralizedKeyClient.call_with_resilience()` (async version)\n2. Creates `AsyncOpenAI(api_key=acquired_key)` per call\n3. Reports success/error back to KMS with token counts and context (agent_name, step_name, account_code, language, video_title)\n4. KMS handles key rotation, proactive cooldowns, and throttling\n\nThe KMS client (`kms_client_sync.py`) supports:\n- `get_next_key(model, service, model_group, exclude_tiers)` -- acquire key with automatic throttle handling\n- `report_success(key_id, model, ...)` -- report usage with token counts\n- `report_error(key_id, model, error, ...)` -- report failure, get alternative key\n- `call_with_resilience(model, call_fn, max_retries)` -- full retry loop with acquire/call/report cycle\n- HTTP retry: 3 retries with exponential backoff (0.5s, 1s, 2s) on connection errors\n\n### Without KMS\n\nWhen KMS is disabled, planners call via the orchestrator's `LLMClient.call()` using the `OPENAI_API_KEY` from `.env`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Account YAML Schema\n\nEach account has one YAML config per language at `accounts/{account}/configs/{account_id}-{lang}.yaml`. Every field documented below:\n\n### Core Identity\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `language` | string | YES | ISO language code: en, pt, es, fr, de, it, nl, pl, ru, tr, ja, ko, ar |\n\n### Screenplay Agent\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `screenplay_agent.enabled` | bool | YES | Whether screenplay generation is active |\n| `screenplay_agent.batch_size` | int | YES | Scenes per batch for screenplay generation (typically 20) |\n| `screenplay_agent.min_words` | int | NO | Minimum words per scene narration. Varies by language: EN=19, PT=21 (longer), JA uses char limits from orchestrator |\n| `screenplay_agent.max_words` | int | NO | Maximum words per scene narration. Varies by language: EN=57, PT=63 |\n| `screenplay_agent.prompt` | string | YES | Filename of the system prompt (e.g. \"screenplay_agent_003_system.txt\") |\n| `screenplay_agent.evaluator` | string | YES | Filename of the evaluator prompt |\n\n### Evaluators\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `enable_evaluators` | bool | YES | Global toggle for quality validation evaluators |\n\n### Prompt Generator\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `prompt_generator.batch_size` | int | YES | Batch size for image prompt generation (typically 12) |\n\n### Google Sheets/Drive\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `sheet_scripts_id` | string | YES | Google Sheets ID for video scripts |\n| `sheet_scripts_name` | string | YES | Sheet tab name (typically \"Pagina1\") |\n| `sheet_tracking_id` | string | YES | Google Sheets ID for production tracking |\n| `drive_folder_id` | string | YES | Google Drive folder for output files |\n\n### Voice / TTS\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `voice_sample` | string | YES | WAV filename for AllTalk TTS voice (e.g. \"male_03.wav\", \"brian_pt_01.wav\") |\n| `tts_engine` | string | YES | TTS engine: \"gemini\" (production) or \"alltalk\" (legacy local GPU) |\n| `gemini_voice` | string | YES (if gemini) | Gemini TTS voice name (e.g. \"Charon\") |\n\n### Bloco 2\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `bloco2_engine` | string | NO | \"v1\" (original 5-step) or \"v2\" (13-step with Dataset System). Only in some configs |\n\n### Bloco 3\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `bloco3_engine` | string | YES | \"python-tsx\" (production) or \"claude-sdk-opus\" (deprecated). ALL accounts use \"python-tsx\" |\n| `bloco3_compositions` | bool | NO | Enable CompositionLayer for multi-image scenes (Python TSX, zero LLM). Default false |\n| `bloco3_letterings_v2` | bool | NO | Enable v2 lettering with 222 templates + context pool pre-filtering. Default false |\n\n### Key Management (KMS)\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `key_management.enabled` | bool | YES | Enable centralized KMS key pool |\n| `key_management.kms_url` | string | YES (if enabled) | KMS server URL (Railway: \"https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app\") |\n| `key_management.machine_id` | string | YES (if enabled) | Machine identifier (e.g. \"M1\") |\n| `key_management.fallback_to_local` | bool | NO | Fall back to local API keys if KMS unreachable. Default false |\n\n### Resources\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `music` | string | YES | Legacy field, always empty string \"\" (music selected by planner from catalog) |\n| `music_volume` | float | YES | Base music volume multiplier (typically 0.02) |\n\n### Subtitles\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `subtitle_style` | string | YES | Subtitle visual style. All accounts use \"hormozi\" |\n| `subtitle_karaoke` | bool | YES | Enable karaoke-style word highlighting. All accounts: true |\n\n### Visual Style\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `theme_style` | string | YES | Visual theme identifier. Examples: \"wwii_photography\", \"dark_history_renaissance\", \"dark_forensics_noir\" |\n\n### Tracking\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `account_id` | string | YES | Account number (e.g. \"003\", \"005\") |\n\n### Dataset (LoRA Training)\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `dataset.enabled` | bool | YES | Enable dataset export for LoRA training |\n| `dataset.trigger_word` | string | YES (if enabled) | LoRA trigger word (e.g. \"wwii_photo_style\") |\n| `dataset.drive_folder_id` | string | YES (if enabled) | Google Drive folder for dataset uploads |\n| `dataset.auto_upload` | bool | NO | Auto-upload dataset to Drive after export |\n\n### TTS Polish\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `tts_polish.domain_context` | string | YES | Context string for TTS pronunciation polishing. Describes the channel's domain for proper pronunciation |\n| `tts_polish.protected_terms` | list[string] | YES | Terms that must not be altered by TTS polish (foreign words, acronyms, etc.) |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Resource System\n\n### Directory Structure\n\nResources are stored **per-account** (shared across all languages for that account):\n\n```\naccounts/{account}/resources/\n    music/\n        MUSIC_CATALOG.json           # Master catalog with all track metadata\n        {category}/\n            {track_name}_v1.mp3      # Variant 1\n            {track_name}_v2.mp3      # Variant 2\n            {track_name}_v3.mp3      # Variant 3 (sometimes v4)\n    sfx/\n        SFX_CATALOG.json             # Master catalog with all SFX metadata\n        {category}/\n            {sfx_name}_v1.mp3\n            {sfx_name}_v2.mp3\n            {sfx_name}_v3.mp3\n            {sfx_name}_v4.mp3\n```\n\n### Accounts with Resources\n\nAll 9 active accounts have both music and SFX resources:\n\n| Account | Music Categories | SFX Categories |\n|---------|-----------------|----------------|\n| 001_dark_forensics | dramatic, emotional, horror | environment, human, torture |\n| 002_wars_and_conquer | emotional, military, suspense, tension | cavalry, naval, special |\n| 003_wwii_photography | emotional, military, suspense, tension | cinematic (impacts, risers, whoosh, heartbeat, etc.) |\n| 004_dark_culture | dramatic, emotional, horror | environment, human, torture |\n| 005_dark_history | dramatic, emotional, horror | environment, human, torture |\n| 006_mansion_mystery | decay, dramatic, grandeur | architectural, environment, high_society, mansion_interior |\n| 008_battle_front | *(similar to 002/003)* | *(similar to 002/003)* |\n| 011_life_lessons | *(motivational/reflective)* | atmosphere (clock, rain, wind), cinematic (whoosh, tension riser) |\n| 013_dark_registries | *(period music)* | period (church bells) |\n\n### MUSIC_CATALOG.json Structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"account\": \"003_wwii_photography\",\n  \"catalog_type\": \"music\",\n  \"total_unique_tracks\": 30,\n  \"total_files\": 120,\n  \"usage_notes\": {\n    \"variant_selection\": \"System randomly selects one at render time\",\n    \"path_format\": \"music/{category}/{name}_v{N}.mp3\",\n    \"volume_tier\": \"background_music (0.03-0.06)\"\n  },\n  \"categories\": {\n    \"tension\": {\n      \"path\": \"music/tension/\",\n      \"tracks\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tension_high\",\n          \"variants\": 3,\n          \"description\": \"Intense orchestral tension...\",\n          \"duration_seconds\": 386,\n          \"best_moments\": [\"battle buildup\", \"climax\"],\n          \"tags\": [\"tension\", \"high\", \"battle\"],\n          \"mood\": \"anxious, intense, building\",\n          \"energy_level\": \"high\",\n          \"narrative_phases\": [\"development\", \"climax\"],\n          \"recommended_volume\": 0.15\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### SFX_CATALOG.json Structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"account\": \"003_wwii_photography\",\n  \"catalog_type\": \"sfx\",\n  \"total_unique_sfx\": 40,\n  \"total_files\": 160,\n  \"categories\": {\n    \"cinematic\": {\n      \"sfx\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"dramatic_impact\",\n          \"variants\": 4,\n          \"description\": \"Deep cinematic bass boom...\",\n          \"duration_seconds\": 2,\n          \"best_moments\": [\"dramatic reveals\", \"shocking statistics\"],\n          \"tags\": [\"dramatic\", \"impact\", \"boom\"],\n          \"loopable\": false,\n          \"versatile\": true,\n          \"recommended_volume\": 0.15\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### AudioResolver\n\n`shared/processors/audio_resolver.py` sits between planners and TSX generators:\n\n1. **Builds lookup tables** from `MUSIC_CATALOG.json` and `SFX_CATALOG.json` at init\n2. **Validates planner outputs:** checks every track_name/sfx_name exists in catalog\n3. **Injects runtime data:** file path, volume, duration_seconds, loopable flag, start_frame/end_frame (music)\n4. **Strips catalogs for planner input:** removes paths, volumes, variants -- keeps only name, description, metadata\n5. **Invalid names are SKIPPED** with a warning (pipeline continues, not fatal)\n\n**Catalog stripping** ensures planners never see file paths or volumes, only:\n- Music: name, description, duration_seconds, best_moments, tags, mood, energy_level, narrative_phases\n- SFX: name, description, duration_seconds, best_moments, tags, loopable, versatile\n\n### No Overlays\n\nThere are **no overlay resources** in the current production system. The `resources/` directories contain only `music/` and `sfx/` subdirectories. Overlays were part of the V1 system and have been removed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Machine Config\n\n**File:** `content_factory_v3/machine_config.yaml` (NOT in git -- per-machine)\n\nControls machine-specific settings that differ between production machines (M1, M2, M3).\n\n### Schema\n\n```yaml\n# Machine Identity\nmachine_id: \"M1\"\nmachine_name: \"RTX 4070 Super - M1\"\n\n# Local Services\nservices:\n  service_controller:\n    url: \"http://localhost:5123\"\n    startup_timeout: 120\n  alltalk:\n    url: \"http://localhost:7851\"    # AllTalk TTS\n    startup_timeout: 120\n  whisperx:\n    url: \"http://localhost:6123\"    # WhisperX transcription\n    startup_timeout: 60\n  comfyui:\n    url: \"http://localhost:8188\"    # ComfyUI image generation\n    startup_timeout: 180\n\n# Paths (machine-specific)\npaths:\n  project_root: \"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/content_factory_v3\"\n  credentials: \"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/content_factory_v3/credentials\"\n  temp_dir: \"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/content_factory_v3/temp\"\n  voices: \"C:/ContentFactory/alltalk_tts/voices\"\n\n# API Keys (can reference env vars with ${VAR_NAME})\napi_keys:\n  openai: \"${OPENAI_API_KEY}\"\n  google_imagen: \"${GOOGLE_IMAGEN_API_KEY}\"\n  google_cloud_project: \"${GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT}\"\n\n# Hardware Limits\nhardware:\n  max_parallel_jobs: 1\n  default_timeout: 300     # seconds\n  vram_gb: 6\n```\n\n### Fields Explained\n\n| Section | Field | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `machine_id` | string | Unique machine identifier used by KMS for tracking |\n| `services.*.url` | string | Local service URLs (differ per machine port assignment) |\n| `services.*.startup_timeout` | int | Seconds to wait for service startup |\n| `paths.project_root` | string | Absolute path to V3 root (differs per machine) |\n| `paths.credentials` | string | Google service account JSON location |\n| `paths.voices` | string | AllTalk TTS voice samples directory |\n| `api_keys.*` | string | Can be literal or `${ENV_VAR}` references |\n| `hardware.max_parallel_jobs` | int | Concurrent pipeline runs |\n| `hardware.vram_gb` | int | GPU VRAM for batch size decisions |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Config Loading Flow\n\n### Config Singleton (`shared/config.py`)\n\nThe `Config` class is a **singleton** that loads configuration once at import time:\n\n```\n1. Determine V3 root: Path(__file__).parent.parent  (content_factory_v3/)\n2. Load .env from V3 root (API keys, secrets) via python-dotenv\n3. Load machine_config.yaml from V3 root (paths, services, hardware)\n4. Optionally load config.yaml (legacy, if exists)\n```\n\n### Priority Order\n\n```\nmachine_config.yaml  >  .env  >  hardcoded defaults\n```\n\n- **machine_config.yaml:** Service URLs, local paths, hardware limits. MUST exist per machine.\n- **.env:** API keys (OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, etc.). Shared across machines.\n- **Hardcoded defaults:** Fallback values in Config properties.\n\n### Access Patterns\n\n```python\nfrom shared.config import config\n\n# Dot notation for nested keys\nconfig.get(\"services.alltalk.url\")\nconfig.get(\"paths.project_root\")\n\n# Required values (raises RuntimeError if missing)\nconfig.require(\"services.alltalk.url\", \"AllTalk TTS URL\")\n\n# Environment variables\nconfig.get_env(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n\n# Convenience properties\nconfig.machine_id        # \"M1\"\nconfig.xtts_base_url     # \"http://localhost:7851\"\nconfig.openai_api_key    # from .env or api_keys.openai\nconfig.vram_gb           # 6\n```\n\n### Account YAML Loading\n\nAccount YAMLs are loaded separately by the orchestrator (not by `Config`). The orchestrator:\n1. Receives `config_path` parameter pointing to `accounts/{account}/configs/{id}-{lang}.yaml`\n2. Loads YAML directly with `yaml.safe_load()`\n3. Extracts fields as needed (bloco3_engine, key_management, etc.)\n4. The account directory is derived from the config path's parent structure\n\n---\n\n## 8. Per-Language Variations\n\n### What Changes Per Language\n\n| Aspect | Language Variation |\n|--------|-------------------|\n| `language` field | ISO code: en, pt, es, fr, de, it, nl, pl, ru, tr, ja, ko, ar |\n| `screenplay_agent.min_words` / `max_words` | EN: 19-57, PT: 21-63, JA: uses char limits from orchestrator |\n| `voice_sample` | EN: \"male_03.wav\", PT: \"brian_pt_01.wav\", others vary |\n| `gemini_voice` | Same across languages for same account (e.g. \"Charon\") |\n| Google Sheets/Drive IDs | Different spreadsheet per language (separate content) |\n| Planner prompts directory | `prompts/bloco3/{language}/` -- same prompt content but located per-language |\n\n### What Does NOT Change Per Language\n\n| Aspect | Stays Same |\n|--------|------------|\n| `bloco3_engine` | \"python-tsx\" for all |\n| `bloco3_compositions` | Same per account |\n| `bloco3_letterings_v2` | Same per account |\n| `theme_style` | Same per account |\n| `account_id` | Same per account |\n| `music_volume` | Same per account |\n| `subtitle_style` | \"hormozi\" for all |\n| `subtitle_karaoke` | true for all |\n| `key_management.*` | Same per account |\n| `dataset.*` | Same per account |\n| `tts_polish.domain_context` | Same per account (English description for all) |\n| `tts_polish.protected_terms` | Same per account |\n| Resources (music/sfx) | Shared across languages per account |\n\n### Planner Prompt Copies\n\nPlanner prompts (`music_planner_system.txt`, `sfx_planner_system.txt`, `lettering_planner_system.txt`) exist as copies per language under `prompts/bloco3/{lang}/`. For example, account 003 has prompts in: de, en, es, fr, it, ja, ko, nl, pl, pt, ru, tr (12 languages).\n\nThe **style planner prompts** (`lettering_style_planner_system.txt`, `lettering_style_planner_v2_system.txt`) exist only under `en/` and are loaded with fallback (try current language -> fall back to `en/`). This is because the style planner is language-agnostic -- the language is embedded in the JSON input.\n\n### Languages Per Account\n\n| Account | Languages |\n|---------|-----------|\n| 003_wwii_photography | de, en, es, fr, it, ja, ko, nl, pl, pt, ru, tr (12) |\n| 005_dark_history | ar, de, en, es, fr, it, ja, ko, nl, pl, pt, ru, tr (13) |\n\nAccount 005 includes Arabic (ar) which is not present in 003.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Cost Profile\n\n### Per-Video LLM Cost Breakdown\n\nFor a typical 60-scene, ~10-minute video:\n\n| Planner | Calls | Input Tokens (est.) | Output Tokens (est.) | Cost (est.) |\n|---------|-------|--------------------|--------------------|-------------|\n| Music Planner | 1 | ~6,000 | ~800 | $0.004 |\n| SFX Planner | 5 batches (60/12) | ~4,000 x 5 = 20,000 | ~600 x 5 = 3,000 | $0.013 |\n| Lettering Planner | 5 batches (60/12) | ~5,000 x 5 = 25,000 | ~1,200 x 5 = 6,000 | $0.020 |\n| Lettering Style Planner | 8 batches (60/8) | ~3,000 x 8 = 24,000 | ~1,500 x 8 = 12,000 | $0.029 |\n| **TOTAL** | **19 calls** | **~75,000** | **~21,800** | **~$0.065** |\n\n### Cost Formula\n\n```\ncost = (input_tokens * $0.40 / 1,000,000) + (output_tokens * $1.60 / 1,000,000)\n```\n\n### Cost Per Scale\n\n| Scale | Videos | Bloco 3 LLM Cost |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| 1 video | 1 | ~$0.065 |\n| 1 account x 1 language | 5 videos/day | ~$0.33/day |\n| 9 accounts x 12 languages | 540 videos/day | ~$35/day |\n\n### What Is Free (Zero LLM)\n\nEverything in Bloco 3 except the 4 planners is deterministic Python:\n- Phase 1: Preprocessing (slim JSONs, planner inputs)\n- Phase 3: AudioResolver (name validation, path injection)\n- Phase 4: Music TSX, Animation TSX, Transition TSX, SFX TSX (all Python generators)\n- Phase 4: Lettering TSX generation (Python, post-style-planner)\n- Phase 5: Merge, finalize, TSX validation, auto-fix\n- Phase 6: Compile test, parallel render (4 chunks), render recovery\n\n---\n\n## Key Source Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared/processors/bloco3_orchestrator.py` | Main pipeline (~3250 lines), all 6 phases |\n| `shared/processors/bloco3_preprocessor.py` | Slim JSONs, planner input generation |\n| `shared/processors/audio_resolver.py` | Name->path+volume resolver for music/SFX |\n| `shared/processors/lettering_style_planner.py` | Style planner input builder, GPT response parser, validation |\n| `shared/processors/lettering_style_catalog.py` | Fonts, colors, positions, duration ranges, component schemas |\n| `shared/processors/lettering_context_filter.py` | Template pre-filtering (9 pools, 222 templates), sticker occupancy |\n| `shared/config.py` | Singleton config manager (machine_config.yaml + .env) |\n| `shared/clients/kms_client_sync.py` | Synchronous KMS client (acquire/report/retry) |\n| `machine_config.yaml` | Per-machine paths, services, hardware |\n| `accounts/{id}/configs/{id}-{lang}.yaml` | Per-account per-language configuration |\n| `accounts/{id}/resources/music/MUSIC_CATALOG.json` | Per-account music catalog |\n| `accounts/{id}/resources/sfx/SFX_CATALOG.json` | Per-account SFX catalog |\n| `accounts/{id}/prompts/bloco3/{lang}/*.txt` | Per-account per-language planner prompts |\n| `prompts/en/lettering_style_planner_system.txt` | Shared style planner prompt (repo-level) |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829931}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfaec142","parentId":"17fefaee","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SspXQbzeEcB02GLsuQojTFtg|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb448190b57e954ea88c69e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bloco 3 -- Video Assembly & Render Pipeline\n\n> **Status**: PRODUCTION (all accounts, all languages)\n> **Last verified**: 2026-04-02\n> **Location**: `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/bloco3_orchestrator.py` (~3250 lines)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nBloco 3 is the final pipeline block in Content Factory V3. It takes the fully-prepared `video_spec.json` (output of Bloco 1 + Bloco 2) and produces a rendered MP4 video using Remotion (React-based video framework).\n\nThe pipeline uses a **hybrid architecture**:\n- **GPT-4.1-mini** for creative planning decisions (music, SFX, lettering) -- the ONLY LLM calls in B3\n- **Python TSX Engine** for deterministic TSX code generation -- zero LLM cost\n- **Claude SDK** for animation batches only (creative, non-deterministic image animations)\n- **Remotion 4.x** for final compilation and parallel chunk rendering\n\n**Typical pipeline run**: ~120 scenes, 3 batches, 4-6 GPT planner calls + N animation SDK calls. Total LLM cost per video: $0.02-0.08 (planners only; TSX engine is free).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Phase Breakdown\n\nThe orchestrator (`Bloco3Orchestrator.run()`) executes 6 sequential phases:\n\n| Phase | Name | Engine | LLM Calls | Description |\n|-------|------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| 1 | Preprocessor | Python | 0 | Slim JSONs, Remotion project scaffolding, NarrationLayer.tsx, planner inputs, asset copying |\n| 2 | GPT Planners | GPT-4.1-mini | 1 music + N lettering + N SFX | Creative planning: music sections, SFX placement, lettering entries (all parallel) |\n| 3 | Audio Resolver | Python | 0 | Validate planner outputs against catalogs, inject file paths + volumes + frame ranges |\n| 4 | Agents (TSX Generation) | Python TSX + Claude SDK | 0 (TSX) + N (animation) | Generate all TSX layers: music, transitions, lettering, SFX (Python) + animation (SDK) |\n| 5 | Merge + Finalize + Validate | Python | 0-few (render_fix) | Merge batches into layer files, generate integration TSX, static validation + auto-fix |\n| 6 | Render | Remotion + FFmpeg | 0-few (recovery) | Compile test, parallel 4-chunk render, FFmpeg concatenation |\n\n### Phase execution flow:\n\n```\nPhase 1: Preprocessor\n    |\n    v\nPhase 2: GPT Planners (music + sfx + lettering -- all parallel via asyncio.gather)\n    |\n    v\nPhase 3: Audio Resolver (validate names, inject paths/volumes/frames)\n    |\n    v\nPhase 4: Agents (all parallel via asyncio.gather)\n    |-- Music TSX Generator (Python, deterministic)\n    |-- Transition TSX Generator (Python, deterministic, per batch)\n    |-- Lettering TSX Generator (Python, via GPT style planner)\n    |-- SFX TSX Generator (Python, deterministic)\n    |-- Animation Batch Agent (Claude SDK, per batch)\n    |-- [Composition TSX Generator (Python, when enabled)]\n    |\n    v\nPhase 5: Merge + Finalize\n    |-- Merge AnimBatch_N.tsx -> AnimationLayer.tsx\n    |-- Merge TransBatch_N.tsx -> TransitionLayer.tsx\n    |-- LettBatch.tsx -> LetteringLayer.tsx\n    |-- MusicSections.tsx + SFXComplete.tsx -> SoundtrackLayer.tsx\n    |-- Generate Video.tsx, Root.tsx, index.ts\n    |-- TSX static validation + auto-fix\n    |\n    v\nPhase 6: Render\n    |-- npm install (if needed)\n    |-- Compile test (1 frame at each chunk boundary + midpoints)\n    |-- Auto-fix loop (up to 3 attempts via render_fix agent)\n    |-- Parallel 4-chunk render (npx remotion render)\n    |-- EPIPE retry (halved concurrency)\n    |-- FFmpeg concat -> video_final.mp4\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Entry Point\n\n### Direct invocation via `run_bloco3.py`:\n\n```bash\n# Full pipeline + render\npython run_bloco3.py <video_key> python-tsx --render\n\n# With account prefix (non-default accounts)\npython run_bloco3.py 005:roman_en python-tsx --render\n\n# Dry run (Phase 1 only, prints summary)\npython run_bloco3.py 005:roman_en python-tsx --dry-run\n\n# Render only (skip all agents, render existing TSX files)\npython run_bloco3.py 005:roman_en python-tsx --render-only\n\n# Specify language for planner prompts\npython run_bloco3.py 005:roman_en python-tsx --render --language en\n\n# List available models and videos\npython run_bloco3.py --list-models\n```\n\n### Arguments:\n\n| Argument | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `<video_key>` | Yes | Video name or `NNN:video_name` (e.g., `005:roman_en`) |\n| `<model>` | Yes | Model name: `python-tsx` (production), `claude-sdk-opus`, `or-deepseek-v3`, etc. |\n| `--render` | No | Execute Remotion render after pipeline |\n| `--render-only` | No | Skip all phases, render existing TSX files directly |\n| `--dry-run` | No | Run Phase 1 only, print pipeline summary |\n| `--language XX` | No | Language code for planner prompts (default: `en`). Valid: en, ar, de, es, fr, it, ja, ko, nl, pl, pt, ru, tr |\n\n### Programmatic invocation:\n\n```python\nfrom shared.processors.bloco3_orchestrator import Bloco3Orchestrator\n\norchestrator = Bloco3Orchestrator(\n    video_spec_path=Path(\"accounts/005/data/en/video_name/video_spec.json\"),\n    account_dir=Path(\"accounts/005_dark_history\"),\n    language=\"en\",\n    model_map={\"animation_batch\": \"python-tsx\", ...},  # or all \"python-tsx\"\n    batch_size=40,\n    output_suffix=\"python_tsx\",\n    planner_model=\"gpt-41-mini\",\n    animation_model=\"claude-sdk-opus\",\n    kms_url=\"https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app\",  # optional\n    kms_machine_id=\"M1\",\n    config={\n        \"bloco3_compositions\": False,\n        \"bloco3_letterings_v2\": False,\n    },\n)\n\nresult = await orchestrator.run(render=True)\n# result = {\"status\": \"success\", \"total_time_seconds\": ..., \"usage\": {...}}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Input Requirements\n\nThis is the **critical contract** between Bloco 2 (upstream) and Bloco 3. Everything listed here MUST exist before B3 can run.\n\n### 4.1 `video_spec.json` (MANDATORY)\n\nThe single source of truth for the entire video. Located at:\n```\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/video_spec.json\n```\n\n**Top-level structure**:\n```json\n{\n    \"metadata\": {\n        \"total_duration_frames\": 3600,\n        \"total_scenes\": 120,\n        \"fps\": 30,\n        \"width\": 1920,\n        \"height\": 1080,\n        \"video_name\": \"...\",\n        \"language\": \"en\"\n    },\n    \"scenes\": [ ... ],\n    \"characters\": [ ... ]\n}\n```\n\n**Each scene in `scenes[]` MUST have**:\n\n```json\n{\n    \"scene_index\": 1,\n    \"timing\": {\n        \"start_frame\": 0,\n        \"end_frame\": 90\n    },\n    \"audio\": {\n        \"duration_frames\": 90,\n        \"original_text\": \"The narration text for this scene.\",\n        \"polished_text\": \"Polished version for accent lettering.\",\n        \"word_timestamps\": [\n            {\"word\": \"The\", \"start_frame\": 0, \"end_frame\": 8},\n            {\"word\": \"narration\", \"start_frame\": 9, \"end_frame\": 25},\n            ...\n        ]\n    },\n    \"visual_tone\": \"dark, dramatic, cinematic\",\n    \"what_to_show\": \"A dimly lit courtroom with ancient architecture\",\n    \"characters_in_scene\": {\n        \"characters_to_include\": [\"char_001\", \"char_002\"]\n    },\n    \"visual_direction\": {\n        \"composition_type\": \"hero_simple\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Field usage by agent**:\n\n| Field | Animation | Lettering | Music Planner | SFX Planner | Transition |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|---------------|-------------|------------|\n| `scene_index` | Y | Y | Y | Y | Y |\n| `timing.start_frame` | Y | Y | Y | Y | Y |\n| `timing.end_frame` | Y | Y | Y | Y | Y |\n| `audio.duration_frames` | Y | Y | Y | Y | Y |\n| `audio.original_text` | Y | Y | Y | - | - |\n| `audio.polished_text` | - | Y (accent) | - | - | - |\n| `audio.word_timestamps[]` | - | Y | - | Y | - |\n| `visual_tone` | Y | Y | Y | Y | Y |\n| `what_to_show` | Y | Y | - | Y | Y |\n| `characters_in_scene` | - | Y | - | - | - |\n| `visual_direction.composition_type` | Y | - | - | - | - |\n\n### 4.2 TTS Audio Clips (MANDATORY)\n\nEach scene MUST have a corresponding MP3 narration clip:\n```\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/clips/clip_001.mp3\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/clips/clip_002.mp3\n...\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/clips/clip_NNN.mp3\n```\n\nNaming convention: `clip_{scene_index:03d}.mp3` (zero-padded to 3 digits).\n\nThe preprocessor generates `NarrationLayer.tsx` referencing these clips. If ANY clip is missing, the render will fail with a missing `staticFile` error.\n\n### 4.3 Scene Images (MANDATORY)\n\nEach scene MUST have its generated image:\n```\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/images/scene_001.png\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/images/scene_002.png\n...\n```\n\nThe animation agent uses these to generate Ken Burns effects, zoom/pan animations, etc. Missing images cause render failures.\n\n### 4.4 Account Resources (MANDATORY)\n\n**SFX Catalog** -- `accounts/NNN/resources/sfx/`:\n- `SFX_CATALOG.json` -- catalog with categories, SFX names, recommended_volume, duration_seconds, loopable flags\n- `*.mp3` files organized in category subdirectories (e.g., `cavalry/horses_galloping_group.mp3`)\n- Variant files supported (e.g., `sword_fight_v1.mp3`, `sword_fight_v2.mp3` -- one picked randomly)\n\n**Music Catalog** -- `accounts/NNN/resources/music/`:\n- `MUSIC_CATALOG.json` -- catalog with categories, track names, recommended_volume, duration_seconds\n- `*.mp3` files organized in category subdirectories (e.g., `epic/war_drums_intense.mp3`)\n- Variant files supported (same variant randomization as SFX)\n\n**Catalog JSON structure** (both SFX and Music follow this pattern):\n```json\n{\n    \"categories\": {\n        \"category_name\": {\n            \"tracks\": [\n                {\n                    \"name\": \"track_name\",\n                    \"recommended_volume\": 0.04,\n                    \"duration_seconds\": 180,\n                    \"description\": \"...\"\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor SFX, the key is `\"sfx\"` instead of `\"tracks\"`, and entries also have `\"loopable\": true/false`.\n\n### 4.5 Planner Prompts (MANDATORY)\n\nPer-account, per-language prompt files:\n```\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/<lang>/music_planner_system.txt\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/<lang>/sfx_planner_system.txt\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/<lang>/lettering_planner_system.txt\n```\n\n### 4.6 Agent Prompts (MANDATORY for Claude SDK agents)\n\n```\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/batch_agents/animation_batch_system.txt\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/global_agents/music_sections_system.txt\naccounts/NNN/prompts/bloco3/integration/render_fix_system.txt\n```\n\n### 4.7 Optional Inputs\n\n- **Reference images**: `data/<lang>/<video_slug>/references/*.png` -- copied to Remotion public/\n- **Composition templates**: `accounts/NNN/bloco3_v2/compositions/*.tsx` -- only when `bloco3_compositions: true`\n- **Lettering v2 templates**: `accounts/NNN/bloco3_v2/letterings/*.tsx` -- only when `bloco3_letterings_v2: true`\n\n---\n\n## 5. GPT Planners\n\nThe ONLY LLM calls in Bloco 3. All use **GPT-4.1-mini** via OpenAI API (or KMS key rotation).\n\n### 5.1 Music Planner\n\n- **Input**: All scenes (global, not batched) + stripped music catalog (names + descriptions only, no paths/volumes)\n- **Output**: `music_plan.json` with `sections[]`, each containing:\n  - `section_index`, `label`, `track_name`, `scene_range: [start, end]`, `mood_intent`\n- **Cost**: ~$0.003 per call (single call for entire video)\n- **Temperature**: 0.3, max_tokens: 4000, response_format: json_object\n\n### 5.2 SFX Planner\n\n- **Input**: Batched scenes (12 scenes/batch) + stripped SFX catalog\n- **Output**: Per-batch SFX assignments with sfx_name, scene_index, trigger_word, duration_hint, sfx_type (battle/transition)\n- **Cost**: ~$0.002 per batch\n- **Batching**: 12 scenes per planner batch (separate from the 40-scene agent batches)\n\n### 5.3 Lettering Planner\n\n- **Input**: Batched scenes (12 scenes/batch) + word timestamps + characters\n- **Output**: Per-batch lettering entries with type, content, trigger_word, scene index\n- **Types planned**: character_name, location, date, statistic, dramatic_phrase, quote, dialogue, weapon, faction, etc.\n- **Cost**: ~$0.002 per batch\n\n### 5.4 Lettering Style Planner (Phase 4, not Phase 2)\n\n- **Runs in Phase 4** as part of the Python lettering pipeline\n- **Input**: Resolved lettering entries + style catalog (fonts, colors, positions, components)\n- **Output**: `styled_entries` with component assignment, font, color, position, entrance/exit type, duration\n- **Model**: GPT-4.1-mini, temperature 0.3\n- **Batching**: 8 scenes per style batch (`SCENES_PER_STYLE_BATCH`)\n- **Cost**: ~$0.002 per batch\n\n### 5.5 Total Planner Cost\n\nFor a typical 120-scene video:\n- 1 music planner call\n- 10 lettering planner batches (120/12)\n- 10 SFX planner batches (120/12)\n- ~15 lettering style planner batches (120/8)\n- **Total: ~36 GPT-4.1-mini calls, ~$0.05-0.08**\n\n---\n\n## 6. Python TSX Engine\n\nThe production engine (`bloco3_engine: \"python-tsx\"`). Generates deterministic TSX code with zero LLM cost for all layers except animation.\n\n### 6.1 Music TSX Generator (`music_tsx_generator.py`)\n\n- **Input**: `music_agent_input.json` (resolved plan with paths, volumes, frame ranges)\n- **Output**: `batches/MusicSections.tsx`\n- **Logic**:\n  - Crossfade overlap: 300 frames (10s) between adjacent sections\n  - Fade in: 270 frames (9s), Fade out: 300 frames (10s), Last section: 360 frames (12s)\n  - Premount: 30 frames for smoother audio start\n  - Looping: auto-detected when track duration < section duration\n- **Constants derived from analyzing 24 real SDK outputs**\n\n### 6.2 Transition TSX Generator (`transition_tsx_generator.py`)\n\n- **Input**: Scene boundaries from preprocessor\n- **Output**: `batches/TransBatch_N.tsx` (one per batch)\n- **Logic**:\n  - ~50% of boundaries are CUTS, ~50% get transition effects\n  - Seeded RNG (video name as seed) for reproducibility\n  - 16 transition types in 4 categories: smooth, dynamic, impact, artistic\n  - No consecutive repetition of same effect 3+ times\n  - Impact transitions (FlashWhite, ZoomWithShake) limited to max 2 per batch\n  - First batch opens with FadeFromBlack, last batch ends with FadeToBlack\n\n### 6.3 Lettering TSX Generator (`lettering_tsx_generator.py`)\n\n- **Input**: `styled_entries` from GPT style planner (Phase 4)\n- **Output**: `batches/LettBatch.tsx` (or multiple chunks merged)\n- **Logic**:\n  - 10 Google Fonts (Cinzel, BebasNeue, PlayfairDisplay, Oswald, Anton, Montserrat, Teko, Raleway, CrimsonText, RussoOne)\n  - Script-aware: Latin, CJK (Japanese/Korean), Arabic (RTL) with fallback fonts\n  - 14+ lettering component types (TypewriterText, WordCascade, StampText, GlitchText, etc.)\n  - Each entry positioned at trigger_frame from word timestamps\n  - Entrance/exit animation types per component\n\n**Supporting modules**:\n- `lettering_style_catalog.py` -- fonts, colors, positions, duration ranges, component props\n- `lettering_context_filter.py` -- pre-filters templates per entry type (9 context pools, ~222 templates)\n- `lettering_style_planner.py` -- GPT style assignment (the one GPT call in this pipeline)\n\n### 6.4 SFX TSX Generator (`sfx_tsx_generator.py`)\n\n- **Input**: `sfx_synced_input.json` (resolved plan with paths, volumes, frame positions)\n- **Output**: `batches/SFXComplete.tsx`\n- **Logic**:\n  - Duration table: short (90-120f), standard (180-240f), extended (240-450f), sustained (450-900f)\n  - Transition SFX: 120 frames, fade_in=15, fade_out=30\n  - Looping support for extended/sustained SFX\n  - Trigger word alignment: SFX starts at the frame where the trigger word appears\n  - FadingAudio component with per-frame volume interpolation\n\n### 6.5 Composition TSX Generator (`composition_tsx_generator.py`)\n\n- **Input**: Pre-picked template assignments from `CompositionTemplatePicker`\n- **Output**: `batches/CompBatch_N.tsx`\n- **Only active when** `bloco3_compositions: true` in config\n- **Types**: hero_with_stickers, composition_grid, sequence, hero_with_sequence\n- **Template picker** (`composition_template_picker.py`): seeded RNG, catalog-based, deterministic\n\n### 6.6 Animation Batch Agent (Claude SDK -- NOT Python)\n\nAnimation is the one layer that still uses an LLM (Claude SDK with Opus or Sonnet):\n- **Input**: Slim JSON with scene images, visual_tone, what_to_show\n- **Output**: `batches/AnimBatch_N.tsx`\n- **Why not Python**: Animation decisions are creative (Ken Burns direction, zoom targets, pan speeds)\n- **Tools**: Write only (3 max turns)\n- **Concurrency**: Semaphore-controlled; SDK=1 (CLI lock), API=16\n\n---\n\n## 7. TSX Validation + Auto-fix\n\n### 7.1 Static Validator (`tsx_validator.py`)\n\nRuns in Phase 5 after merge, checks ALL TSX files (batches/ and src/):\n\n| Check | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `_check_basic_tsx` | Verify file is actually TSX (not analysis text) |\n| `_check_banned_fonts` | Block fonts with corrupted WOFF2 (SourceCodePro, SourceSansPro, SourceSerifPro) |\n| `_check_wrong_imports` | Catch `@remotion/media` (v5) imports -- project uses Remotion v4 |\n| `_check_interpolate_ranges` | Validate `interpolate()` input/output ranges are valid |\n| `_check_unsafe_interpolate_range` | Catch interpolate ranges that could produce NaN |\n| `_check_hold_black_frames` | Detect excessive holdBlackFrames in transitions |\n| `_check_duration_in_frames` | Verify durationInFrames > 0 |\n| `_check_easing_functions` | Validate Easing.* calls against Remotion's API |\n| `_check_sequence_bounds` | Verify Sequence from+duration does not exceed total_frames |\n| `_check_static_files` | Verify staticFile() references exist in public/ |\n| `_check_nested_quotes_in_jsx_props` | Detect nested quote issues in JSX |\n\n### 7.2 Auto-fix (Layer 2)\n\nAutomatic fixes applied without LLM:\n- **Unicode escapes**: `\\u00B0` literal -> actual `°` character\n- **Unicode quotes**: smart quotes -> ASCII quotes\n- **Banned fonts**: SourceCodePro -> RobotoMono, etc.\n- **Invalid easing**: `Easing.ease` -> `Easing.inOut(Easing.quad)`, etc.\n- **Sequence bounds**: clamp to total_frames\n\n### 7.3 Render Fix Agent (Layer 3)\n\nWhen auto-fix cannot resolve issues:\n- Uses Claude SDK (render_fix agent type)\n- Has Read + Write + Glob tools (5 max turns)\n- Reads the problematic file, diagnoses, writes fix\n- Re-validated after fix\n\n---\n\n## 8. Render Pipeline\n\n### 8.1 Compile Test (Phase 6, first step)\n\nBefore the full render, a fast compile test validates TSX compilation:\n- Renders 1 frame from each of the 4 chunk boundaries + midpoints (~8 test frames)\n- Each test renders in under 2 minutes\n- If compilation fails, error is sent to `render_fix` agent\n- **Retry loop**: up to 3 auto-fix attempts before failing\n\n### 8.2 Parallel Chunk Render (Phase 7)\n\n```\nTotal frames split into 4 chunks\nEach chunk: separate npx remotion render process\nEach process: independent FFmpeg encoder (the bottleneck being parallelized)\n```\n\n**Render command per chunk**:\n```bash\nnpx remotion render Video chunk_NN.mp4 \\\n    --frames=START-END \\\n    --codec=h264 \\\n    --gl=angle \\\n    --x264-preset=ultrafast \\\n    --concurrency=WORKERS\n```\n\n- **Chunks**: 4 (optimal for most machines)\n- **Concurrency per chunk**: `max(4, cpu_count // 4)` -- typically 8 on 16-core\n- **Total concurrency**: `concurrency=32` recommended for 128GB RAM machines\n- **Timeout**: 3600 seconds (60 min) per chunk\n- **Progress polling**: every 30 seconds via log file parsing\n\n### 8.3 EPIPE Recovery\n\nIf a chunk fails with EPIPE (memory pressure):\n- Detected by scanning chunk log files for \"EPIPE\"\n- Failed chunk re-rendered sequentially with halved concurrency\n- Only the specific failed chunk is retried, not all 4\n\n### 8.4 TSX Error Recovery\n\nIf chunks fail with TSX/compilation errors (not EPIPE):\n- Error messages parsed from chunk logs\n- Combined errors sent to render_fix agent\n- After fix, only failed chunks are re-rendered (`skip_existing=True`)\n- Successful chunks (>1MB mp4) are reused\n\n### 8.5 FFmpeg Concatenation\n\nAfter all chunks complete:\n```bash\nffmpeg -y -f concat -safe 0 -i concat_list.txt -c copy video_final.mp4\n```\n- **Stream copy** (no re-encoding) -- near-instant\n- Chunk files deleted after concatenation\n\n### 8.6 Output Location\n\n```\naccounts/NNN/data/<lang>/<video_slug>/remotion_python_tsx/out/video_final.mp4\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. Output\n\n### 9.1 Final Video\n\n- **Format**: MP4, H.264 codec, AAC audio\n- **Resolution**: 1920x1080 (from video_spec metadata)\n- **FPS**: 30\n- **Location**: `<video_dir>/remotion_<suffix>/out/video_final.mp4`\n\n### 9.2 Pipeline Summary\n\n`<output_dir>/pipeline_summary.json`:\n```json\n{\n    \"status\": \"success\",\n    \"pipeline_version\": \"standard\",\n    \"total_time_seconds\": 245.3,\n    \"output_dir\": \"...\",\n    \"planner_model\": \"gpt-41-mini\",\n    \"music_plan_sections\": 5,\n    \"sfx_plan_count\": 42,\n    \"lettering_plan_count\": 67,\n    \"usage\": {\n        \"total_cost_usd\": 0.0523,\n        \"total_input_tokens\": 128000,\n        \"total_output_tokens\": 24000,\n        \"total_duration_seconds\": 45.2,\n        \"total_agents\": 36,\n        \"failed_agents\": 0,\n        \"by_agent_type\": { ... }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 9.3 Intermediate Artifacts\n\nAll preserved in the output directory for debugging:\n\n| Directory | Contents |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `slim_jsons/` | All slim JSONs, planner inputs/outputs, resolved plans |\n| `batches/` | Individual TSX batch files (AnimBatch_N, TransBatch_N, LettBatch, MusicSections, SFXComplete) |\n| `src/` | Merged layer files (AnimationLayer, TransitionLayer, LetteringLayer, SoundtrackLayer, NarrationLayer, Video.tsx, Root.tsx) |\n| `public/` | Images, clips, SFX, music (all assets Remotion needs) |\n| `agent_logs/` | Full input/output logs for every agent call |\n| `out/` | Chunk logs, final video |\n\n### 9.4 Post-Processing\n\nBloco 3 itself does NOT handle:\n- **Compression**: Done externally (FFmpeg re-encode with target bitrate)\n- **YouTube upload**: Done by the queue system\n- **Metadata stripping**: `metadata_stripper.py` provides FFmpeg args to remove encoder fingerprints\n\nThe `metadata_stripper.py` module provides:\n```python\nfrom shared.processors.metadata_stripper import get_metadata_strip_args\n# Returns: [\"-map_metadata\", \"-1\", \"-map_metadata:s:v\", \"-1\", ...]\n# Removes encoder versions, timestamps, software info to prevent YouTube fingerprinting\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Error Handling\n\n### 10.1 Compilation Errors\n\n- **Compile test**: 1-frame render at chunk boundaries before full render\n- **Auto-fix loop**: Up to 3 attempts, each sends error to render_fix agent (Claude SDK)\n- **TSX validator**: Catches common Remotion errors before they reach the compiler\n\n### 10.2 Render Failures\n\n| Error Type | Detection | Recovery |\n|------------|-----------|----------|\n| EPIPE (memory) | Log file contains \"EPIPE\" | Retry chunk with halved concurrency |\n| TSX error | Non-zero exit + no valid MP4 | render_fix agent + re-render chunk |\n| Timeout | >3600s per chunk | Kill process tree, mark as failed |\n| Non-zero exit with valid MP4 | Exit code != 0 but MP4 > 1MB | Treated as success (warning logged) |\n\n### 10.3 Planner Failures\n\n- JSON parse failure: Plan set to empty, pipeline continues (layers will be empty but valid)\n- Invalid track/SFX names: Skipped with warning (AudioResolver), pipeline continues\n\n### 10.4 Agent Failures\n\n- Claude SDK timeout: 1200 seconds (20 min) per agent call\n- Retries: 4 retries for SDK mode, 2 for API mode\n- Invalid TSX output: `_retry_with_feedback()` sends bad output back with error description\n- Concurrency semaphore prevents overloading: SDK=1, CLI=2, OpenCode=4, API=16\n\n---\n\n## 11. Per-Account Configuration\n\n### YAML Config Fields (in `accounts/NNN/configs/NNN-lang.yaml`)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `bloco3_engine` | string | `\"python-tsx\"` | Engine mode. `\"python-tsx\"` = production, `\"claude-sdk-opus\"` = full LLM |\n| `bloco3_compositions` | bool | `false` | Enable multi-image composition scenes (CompositionLayer) |\n| `bloco3_letterings_v2` | bool | `false` | Enable context pool pre-filtering + new lettering templates |\n\n### Orchestrator Constructor Config\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `video_spec_path` | Path | required | Path to video_spec.json |\n| `account_dir` | Path | required | Account root directory |\n| `language` | str | `\"en\"` | Language code for planner prompts |\n| `model_map` | Dict | DEFAULT_MODEL_MAP | Model assignment per agent type |\n| `batch_size` | int | `40` | Scenes per agent batch |\n| `planner_model` | str | `\"gpt-41-mini\"` | Model for GPT planners |\n| `animation_model` | str | `\"claude-sdk-opus\"` | Model for animation batches (only one still using LLM) |\n| `kms_url` | str | None | KMS server URL for key rotation |\n| `kms_machine_id` | str | `\"M1\"` | Machine identifier for KMS |\n| `output_suffix` | str | None | Suffix for output dir (e.g., `\"python_tsx\"` -> `remotion_python_tsx/`) |\n\n### Resource Requirements Per Account\n\nEach account MUST have:\n```\naccounts/NNN/\n    resources/\n        sfx/\n            SFX_CATALOG.json\n            <category>/<name>.mp3\n        music/\n            MUSIC_CATALOG.json\n            <category>/<name>.mp3\n    prompts/\n        bloco3/\n            <lang>/\n                music_planner_system.txt\n                sfx_planner_system.txt\n                lettering_planner_system.txt\n            batch_agents/\n                animation_batch_system.txt\n            global_agents/\n                music_sections_system.txt\n            integration/\n                render_fix_system.txt\n    configs/\n        NNN-<lang>.yaml\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12. How to Wrap This for Paperclip HTTP Webhook\n\nBloco 3 is designed to be invoked as a single async function. Wrapping it in an HTTP webhook requires:\n\n### 12.1 Minimum Webhook Payload\n\n```json\n{\n    \"video_spec_path\": \"/absolute/path/to/video_spec.json\",\n    \"account_dir\": \"/absolute/path/to/accounts/NNN_name\",\n    \"language\": \"en\",\n    \"render\": true,\n    \"engine\": \"python-tsx\",\n    \"animation_model\": \"claude-sdk-opus\",\n    \"kms_url\": \"https://web-production-0a8dd.up.railway.app\",\n    \"kms_machine_id\": \"M1\"\n}\n```\n\n### 12.2 Pre-conditions the Webhook Must Verify\n\nBefore invoking `Bloco3Orchestrator.run()`:\n\n1. **`video_spec.json` exists** and is valid JSON with `metadata`, `scenes[]`, `characters[]`\n2. **All TTS clips exist**: `clips/clip_001.mp3` through `clips/clip_NNN.mp3`\n3. **All scene images exist**: `images/scene_001.png` through `images/scene_NNN.png`\n4. **SFX catalog exists**: `resources/sfx/SFX_CATALOG.json` + all referenced MP3 files\n5. **Music catalog exists**: `resources/music/MUSIC_CATALOG.json` + all referenced MP3 files\n6. **Planner prompts exist**: all 3 planner system prompts for the target language\n7. **Agent prompts exist**: animation_batch, render_fix system prompts\n8. **API keys available**: `OPENAI_API_KEY` env var (for GPT planners), or KMS URL configured\n9. **Node.js + npm available**: Required for `npx remotion render`\n10. **FFmpeg available**: Required for chunk concatenation\n\n### 12.3 Wrapper Code\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom shared.processors.bloco3_orchestrator import Bloco3Orchestrator\n\nasync def handle_bloco3_webhook(payload: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Paperclip webhook handler for Bloco 3.\"\"\"\n    \n    model_map = {k: \"python-tsx\" for k in DEFAULT_MODEL_MAP}\n    \n    orchestrator = Bloco3Orchestrator(\n        video_spec_path=Path(payload[\"video_spec_path\"]),\n        account_dir=Path(payload[\"account_dir\"]),\n        language=payload.get(\"language\", \"en\"),\n        model_map=model_map,\n        batch_size=40,\n        output_suffix=\"python_tsx\",\n        planner_model=\"gpt-41-mini\",\n        animation_model=payload.get(\"animation_model\", \"claude-sdk-opus\"),\n        kms_url=payload.get(\"kms_url\"),\n        kms_machine_id=payload.get(\"kms_machine_id\", \"M1\"),\n        config={},\n    )\n    \n    result = await orchestrator.run(render=payload.get(\"render\", True))\n    \n    # Result includes status, timing, cost, output_dir\n    return result\n```\n\n### 12.4 Expected Runtime\n\n| Video Length | Scenes | Pipeline Time | Render Time | Total |\n|-------------|--------|---------------|-------------|-------|\n| 3 min | ~40 | ~30s | ~3 min | ~4 min |\n| 8 min | ~120 | ~60s | ~8 min | ~10 min |\n| 15 min | ~200 | ~90s | ~15 min | ~17 min |\n\nPipeline time is dominated by GPT planner calls (~30-60s) and Claude SDK animation calls (~30-60s each, but parallelized). Render time scales linearly with frame count.\n\n### 12.5 Output to Return\n\nThe webhook should return:\n- `pipeline_summary.json` contents (status, cost, timing)\n- Path to `video_final.mp4`\n- Path to `pipeline_summary.json` for full details\n\n---\n\n## Appendix: File Map\n\n| File | Lines | Role |\n|------|-------|------|\n| `bloco3_orchestrator.py` | ~3250 | Main orchestrator: 6 phases, all agents, render |\n| `bloco3_preprocessor.py` | ~2100 | Slim JSONs, Remotion project, merge engine |\n| `audio_resolver.py` | ~250 | Name -> path + volume resolver |\n| `music_tsx_generator.py` | ~300 | MusicSections.tsx (deterministic) |\n| `transition_tsx_generator.py` | ~400 | TransBatch_N.tsx (seeded RNG) |\n| `lettering_tsx_generator.py` | ~800 | LettBatch.tsx (deterministic from styled_entries) |\n| `lettering_style_planner.py` | ~300 | GPT style assignment for lettering entries |\n| `lettering_style_catalog.py` | ~400 | Fonts, colors, positions, component schemas |\n| `lettering_context_filter.py` | ~200 | Pre-filter templates per entry type (9 pools) |\n| `sfx_tsx_generator.py` | ~500 | SFXComplete.tsx (deterministic) |\n| `composition_tsx_generator.py` | ~200 | CompBatch_N.tsx (deterministic, optional) |\n| `composition_template_picker.py` | ~100 | Seeded template selection for compositions |\n| `tsx_validator.py` | ~500 | Static TSX validation + auto-fix |\n| `metadata_stripper.py` | ~60 | FFmpeg args for metadata removal |\n| `run_bloco3.py` | ~128 | CLI entry point |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829945}}
{"type":"message","id":"50ad13a3","parentId":"cfaec142","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:40:29.974Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qIVhXcCi1NbqXjYQvoy5064g|fc_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fddcb488190a07f0bf7084b0c3a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Auto Content Factory V2 - Context Document\n\n**Date:** 2026-04-02\n**Author:** Lucca + Claude (planning session)\n**Status:** Planning Phase\n\n---\n\n## 1. Background: What Exists Today\n\n### Content Factory V3 (Production)\n\nThe Content Factory V3 is a fully operational, deterministic video production pipeline that produces faceless YouTube videos across 39 channels, 8 accounts, and 11 languages. It runs on Windows machines with RTX GPUs and 128GB RAM.\n\n**Architecture:** 3 sequential processing blocks (Blocos):\n\n| Block | Name | Function | Tech |\n|-------|------|----------|------|\n| **Bloco 1** | Script to Audio | Script → Screenplay → TTS → Timestamps | Python + GPT planners |\n| **Bloco 2** | Visual Production | Scene direction → Image generation → Visual assets | Python + Gemini/OR APIs |\n| **Bloco 3** | Video Assembly | Music/SFX/Lettering planning → TSX Engine → Remotion Render | Python + Remotion |\n\n**Key files:**\n- `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/bloco3_orchestrator.py` (~3250 lines)\n- `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/bloco3_preprocessor.py`\n- `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/audio_resolver.py`\n- `content_factory_v3/shared/processors/tsx_validator.py`\n- `content_factory_v3/run_bloco3.py`\n\n### Auto Content Factory V1 (Legacy)\n\nThe first attempt at creating an agentic layer on top of V3. Located at `auto_content_factory_legacy/`. This was an ambitious but premature effort to transform the ENTIRE V3 pipeline into OpenClaw agents with a 5-level hierarchy (CEO → PM → VO → Branch Managers → Operators).\n\n**What was built:**\n- 23 documentation files (comprehensive architecture specs)\n- Production Manager runtime (Python) - reads PUB sheets, selects channels by urgency\n- Video Orchestrator runtime - initializes runs, fetches scripts, manages directories\n- S1 (Pre-Production) supervisor runtime with batching, validation, retries\n- S2 (Audio) runtime with TTS generation, transcription, alignment\n- 149 workspace .md files defining agent identities\n- 40 YAML account configurations\n- HTML visualization dashboard (`departamento-agentico.html`)\n\n**Why it was abandoned:** Overengineering. The attempt to agentify everything — including parts that already worked perfectly (Blocos 1 and 3) — consumed 3+ days of effort on Sector 1 alone with inconsistent results. The realization: only Bloco 2 (visual production) actually needs agentic capabilities.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Real Problem\n\n### Production is Stopped\n\nThe Content Factory V3's **only blocking problem** is image generation in Bloco 2:\n\n1. **Google Cloud credits exhausted** — All 156 Service Accounts suspended by Google for multi-account free trial abuse (24 Mar 2026)\n2. **API pay-per-use is unviable** — Nano Banana (Google) costs ~$6/video just for images\n3. **No API platform offers unlimited plans** — All image/video generation APIs are pay-per-use\n\n### The Solution: Browser Automation\n\nWeb platforms offer **monthly subscription plans with unlimited generation**:\n- **Freepik** — Image generation (multiple models), unlimited on Pro plan\n- **Higgsfield** — Image-to-video animation, unlimited on subscription\n- **Gemini Web** — Google's models via browser interface, free/Pro plans\n\n**Playwright** (browser automation) was tested successfully on Freepik — an agent can navigate the web UI, generate images, download them, all without API costs.\n\n### Quality Improvement Opportunity\n\nBeyond solving the cost problem, browser-capable agents can:\n- **Search real images/videos** from archives (Wikimedia, Archive.org, LoC, etc.)\n- **Generate AI images** on platforms with the best models (not limited to one API)\n- **Animate images to video** using img2video platforms\n- **Evaluate quality visually** (vision models can judge results)\n- **Retry strategically** (not just retry the same prompt, but reformulate)\n\nThis is where agentic capabilities provide **real ROI** — the tasks are exploratory, qualitative, and require judgment.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Architecture Decision\n\n### Core Insight (from ChatGPT analysis, 2 Apr 2026)\n\n> \"Don't agentify something just because you can. Only agentify where the agent generates real advantage.\"\n\n### Three-Layer Architecture\n\n| Layer | Purpose | Implementation |\n|-------|---------|----------------|\n| **A — Orchestration** | Decide what to produce, coordinate, track state, handle exceptions | Paperclip dashboard |\n| **B — Deterministic Capabilities** | Existing V3 logic — TTS, validation, rendering, etc. | Python scripts (V3 as-is) |\n| **C — Agent-Worth Capabilities** | Image search, visual generation, animation, quality evaluation | OpenClaw + Playwright |\n\n### The Pattern\n\n```\nAgent creates first version\n    ↓\nPython normalizes / validates / corrects\n    ↓\nSpecialized agent refines semantic ambiguities\n    ↓\nPython performs final checks\n```\n\nThis hybrid pattern is more robust than pure agent-to-agent chains because it avoids instruction drift, fidelity loss, higher costs, unpredictability, and debugging difficulty.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The New Architecture: Paperclip + OpenClaw\n\n### Why Paperclip\n\n**Paperclip** (github.com/paperclipai/paperclip) is an open-source orchestration layer for AI agent companies. 38k+ GitHub stars in 4 weeks (launched March 2026). MIT license.\n\n**What it provides:**\n- Dashboard with visibility into all agents, tasks, activity\n- Inbox for human approvals (act as \"board\", not operator)\n- Heartbeat system — agents wake on schedule, check state, continue working\n- Budget tracking per agent\n- Multiple companies/departments in one instance\n- Ticketing system with full audit trail\n- Routines (cron-like recurring tasks)\n- Skills marketplace\n\n**Critical capability: Multi-adapter support.** Paperclip supports 6 first-class adapters:\n\n| Adapter | Use Case |\n|---------|----------|\n| `claude_local` | Claude Code agents |\n| `openclaw-gateway` | **OpenClaw agents via WebSocket** |\n| `codex_local` | OpenAI Codex agents |\n| `gemini_local` | Gemini CLI agents |\n| `cursor` | Cursor IDE agents |\n| **HTTP webhooks** | **Any script/service that responds to HTTP** |\n\nThis means we can have **OpenClaw agents for Bloco 2** and **HTTP webhook \"agents\" for Blocos 1 and 3** (which just invoke existing Python scripts), all coordinated in one dashboard.\n\n### The Target Architecture\n\n```\nPAPERCLIP (Dashboard + Heartbeats + Budget + Inbox)\n│\n├─ CEO Agent (Claude Code adapter)\n│   Purpose: Strategic decisions, priority, escalation\n│   Model: Claude Opus / Sonnet\n│   Heartbeat: 4-8h\n│\n├─ Production Manager (HTTP webhook adapter)\n│   Purpose: Read PUB sheet → calculate runway → select channel\n│   Implementation: Python script (can reuse V1 legacy PM logic)\n│   Cost: $0 (no LLM)\n│\n├─ Video Orchestrator (Claude Code adapter)\n│   Purpose: Coordinate B1 → B2 → B3 for a single video\n│   Manages: directory creation, state tracking, error handling\n│   Heartbeat: 30min during active production\n│\n├─ Bloco 1 Director (HTTP webhook adapter)\n│   Purpose: Invoke V3 Bloco 1 pipeline\n│   Implementation: Python wrapper around existing V3 code\n│   Input: job config (account, language, script)\n│   Output: screenplay, TTS clips, timestamps, scene_bible\n│   Cost: Existing V3 costs (GPT planners, minimal)\n│\n├─ Bloco 2 Director (OpenClaw Gateway adapter) ← PRIMARY INVESTMENT\n│   Purpose: Coordinate visual production team\n│   Implementation: OpenClaw supervisor with specialized operators\n│   Operators:\n│     - Image Searcher (Playwright - archives, stock sites)\n│     - Image Generator (Playwright - Freepik, Gemini web)\n│     - Video Animator (Playwright - Higgsfield)\n│     - Visual Evaluator (Vision model - quality judgment)\n│     - Asset Manager (Python - organize, deduplicate, catalog)\n│   Cost: ~$0 (subscriptions already paid, browser automation is free)\n│\n└─ Bloco 3 Director (HTTP webhook adapter)\n    Purpose: Invoke V3 Bloco 3 pipeline\n    Implementation: Python wrapper around existing V3 code\n    Input: scene_bible + images/videos + audio clips\n    Output: final MP4 video\n    Cost: Existing V3 costs (zero LLM - Python TSX Engine)\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nPM selects channel → creates job JSON\n        │\n        ▼\nVO receives job → creates video directory → fetches script\n        │\n        ▼\nB1 Director → runs V3 Bloco 1 → outputs: scene_bible.json + clips/*.mp3\n        │\n        ▼\nB2 Director → OpenClaw team:\n  ├─ Reads scene_bible.json (visual descriptions per scene)\n  ├─ Searches real images/videos (Playwright)\n  ├─ Generates AI images where needed (Freepik via Playwright)\n  ├─ Animates selected images (Higgsfield via Playwright)\n  ├─ Evaluates quality (vision model)\n  └─ Outputs: images/*.jpg + videos/*.mp4 + asset_registry.json\n        │\n        ▼\nB3 Director → runs V3 Bloco 3 → outputs: final.mp4\n        │\n        ▼\nVO → compress → upload Drive → update sheets → report\n```\n\n### What Changes vs V1 Legacy\n\n| Aspect | V1 (Legacy) | V2 (New) |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| Scope | Transform EVERYTHING into agents | Only agentify Bloco 2 |\n| Orchestrator | Custom OpenClaw hierarchy | Paperclip dashboard |\n| B1 execution | OpenClaw agents (rebuilt) | V3 Python as-is (HTTP wrapper) |\n| B2 execution | OpenClaw agents (planned) | OpenClaw agents (Playwright) |\n| B3 execution | OpenClaw agents (rebuilt) | V3 Python as-is (HTTP wrapper) |\n| Visibility | None (terminal logs) | Paperclip dashboard |\n| Heartbeats | Manual | Automatic (configurable) |\n| Budget | Untracked | Per-agent tracking |\n| Approval flow | None | Inbox-based |\n| Complexity | 5-level hierarchy, ~60 agents | Flat: CEO + PM + VO + 3 directors |\n| Time to production | Months | Weeks |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Principles\n\n1. **Invoke, don't rebuild** — B1 and B3 are wrappers around V3, not reimplementations\n2. **Agentify only where it matters** — B2 is the only block that benefits from agentic capabilities\n3. **Browser is the API** — Monthly subscriptions + Playwright > pay-per-use APIs\n4. **Hybrid is stronger** — Agent creates → Python validates → Agent refines → Python checks\n5. **Dashboard over terminals** — Paperclip gives visibility without 20 open terminals\n6. **Start minimal, expand later** — Get B2 working first, optimize B1/B3 integration after\n\n---\n\n## 6. Immediate Next Steps\n\n1. **Document V3 Blocos** — Deep analysis of what each block does TODAY in production\n2. **Map data contracts** — Exact inputs/outputs between B1 → B2 → B3\n3. **Install Paperclip** — Set up on M1, configure company\n4. **Create B2 OpenClaw team** — Define agents, skills, Playwright workflows\n5. **Build HTTP wrappers** — For B1 and B3 to respond to Paperclip heartbeats\n6. **Test E2E** — One video, one channel, full pipeline through Paperclip\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- **V3 Codebase:** `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\`\n- **V1 Legacy:** `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory_legacy\\`\n- **OpenClaw HTML:** `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\OpenClaw\\departamento-agentico.html`\n- **Paperclip GitHub:** `github.com/paperclipai/paperclip`\n- **Paperclip Website:** `paperclip.ing`\n- **ChatGPT Conversation (2 Apr 2026):** `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Downloads\\luccaechatreformopenclaw`\n- **KMS System:** `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\key-management-system\\`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775140829945}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ab7e7e0","parentId":"50ad13a3","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:41:17.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Beleza. Li os docs e o que eu compreendo é **muito claro e bem mais pragmático** do que a direcção onde a gente estava a sofrer com o S1 em OpenClaw.\n\n## Leitura central\n\nEsses documentos basicamente formalizam esta tese:\n\n**o V3 já é um sistema forte, modular e muito mais híbrido do que parecia — e o erro seria tentar reimplementar isso inteiro como sistema agêntico.**\n\nA arquitectura que emerge dos docs é:\n\n- **Bloco 1** já funciona muito bem como pipeline híbrido\n- **Bloco 2** é o verdadeiro ponto problemático e o melhor candidato para agentificação\n- **Bloco 3** já é fortíssimo, com pouca dependência de LLM, e deve ser preservado quase como está\n- portanto o novo sistema não deve “substituir V3”\n- ele deve **orquestrar V3 + substituir/expandir só a parte visual onde há ROI real**\n\n---\n\n# O que os docs mostram bloco por bloco\n\n## 1) Bloco 1 não é um “setor para reinventar”\nPelo contrário: ele já é quase o exemplo ideal de arquitectura híbrida.\n\n### O padrão real do Bloco 1 é:\n- Python limpa e formata script\n- **Screenplay Agent** divide em cenas\n- Python reconstrói/corrige tudo deterministicamente\n- **TTS Polish Agent** refina o texto\n- Gemini TTS gera áudio\n- Python faz trim, loudness, NISQA, WhisperX, validação, retries\n\nOu seja:\n\n**LLM para julgamento local / ambiguidade**\n+\n**Python para correção mecânica / validação / robustez**\n\nIsso está explícito tanto em `bloco1_agents_and_prompts.md` quanto em `bloco1_script_to_audio.md`.\n\n### Implicação estratégica\nO doc praticamente confirma aquilo que tu disseste de manhã:\n\n**não faz sentido gastar energia a transformar o Bloco 1 em supervisor + operadores OpenClaw se ele já está operacionalmente resolvido.**\n\nO que faz sentido é:\n- tratá-lo como **capability / service / wrapper invocável**\n- preservar prompts, contratos e pós-processamento Python\n- deixar o sistema novo apenas **chamar** esse bloco\n\nEm resumo:\n**Bloco 1 = preservar e encapsular, não reescrever.**\n\n---\n\n## 2) Bloco 2 é onde está o problema real — e também a alavancagem real\nEste é o coração da mudança.\n\nOs docs de Bloco 2 deixam claro que ele é:\n- o bloco mais longo\n- o mais caro em complexidade operacional\n- o mais dependente de geração visual\n- o mais sensível a rate limits / content blocks / qualidade inconsistente\n- o mais “aberto”, exploratório e qualitativo\n\n### O pipeline actual do Bloco 2\nHoje ele faz:\n- identificar personagens\n- casar personagens com dataset\n- gerar retratos\n- perfilar imagens reais\n- mapear entidades para cenas\n- planear composições\n- seleccionar imagens com LLM multimodal\n- definir direcção visual\n- criar estratégia de referências\n- escrever creative briefs\n- traduzir briefs para JSON prompt\n- gerar imagens por API\n- montar `visual_spec.json`\n\nIsto é muito sofisticado.  \nMas os próprios docs deixam evidente o gargalo:\n\n### O problema real do B2\n- image APIs custam caro ou têm limite\n- Gemini/free tier não escala\n- paid APIs ficam inviáveis\n- content blocks atrapalham\n- qualidade visual não é consistente\n\nE o próprio doc já aponta a resposta conceptual:\n\n**browser automation / Playwright / plataformas com subscrição mensal**\ncomo:\n- Freepik\n- Higgsfield\n- Gemini web\n\n### Implicação estratégica\nAqui sim o OpenClaw faz sentido.\n\nPorque aqui o problema é:\n- navegar interfaces\n- escolher entre opções\n- iterar visualmente\n- avaliar qualidade\n- fazer retries estratégicos\n- usar browser como interface operacional\n\nEm resumo:\n**Bloco 2 = principal investimento agêntico.**\n\n---\n\n## 3) Bloco 3 também não deve ser reinventado\nOs docs do Bloco 3 são bem importantes porque mostram uma coisa que talvez não estivesse tão explícita antes:\n\n**Bloco 3 já é majoritariamente determinístico.**\n\nEle usa GPT-4.1-mini só para planners específicos:\n- music planner\n- sfx planner\n- lettering planner\n- lettering style planner\n\nE o resto é:\n- Python\n- TSX generation\n- validação\n- merge\n- render\n- Remotion\n- FFmpeg\n\nOu seja, o Bloco 3 não é um “caos LLM”.  \nEle é um engine de produção bem sólido.\n\n### Implicação estratégica\nNovamente:\n- não faz sentido transformá-lo numa hierarquia de agentes OpenClaw\n- faz sentido **invocá-lo como runtime externo**\n- talvez via HTTP wrapper / capability / job runner\n\nEm resumo:\n**Bloco 3 = preservar e expor como serviço.**\n\n---\n\n# O que os documentos dizem sobre a nova arquitectura\n\nO `v2_context.md` é o documento mais explícito nisso.\n\nEle cristaliza esta decisão:\n\n## Nova arquitectura em 3 camadas\n\n### A — Orchestration\n- decidir o que produzir\n- coordenar jobs\n- acompanhar estado\n- tratar exceções\n- tracking / dashboard / heartbeat\n\n### B — Deterministic Capabilities\n- o V3 actual\n- Bloco 1\n- grande parte do Bloco 3\n- tudo o que já é reproduzível e forte\n\n### C — Agent-Worth Capabilities\n- pesquisa de imagens reais\n- geração visual por browser\n- animação por browser\n- avaliação visual\n- retries qualitativos\n\nIsto bate exactamente com o ponto mais importante:\n\n**o novo sistema não deve ser um replacement total do V3; deve ser uma camada de coordenação + substituição focada do Bloco 2.**\n\n---\n\n# O papel do Paperclip nos docs\n\nOutra coisa muito clara: os docs não estão só a falar de OpenClaw.\n\nEles estão a propor **Paperclip como camada de orquestração empresarial**.\n\n## Função do Paperclip\n- dashboard\n- heartbeats\n- inbox de aprovação\n- budget tracking\n- coordenação entre adapters\n- rotina / visibilidade / auditoria\n\n## E a arquitectura-alvo fica algo como:\n- CEO agent\n- PM\n- VO\n- B1 Director\n- B2 Director\n- B3 Director\n\nMas com uma diferença crítica em relação à tentativa anterior:\n\n### Antes\nqueríamos agentificar quase tudo\n\n### Agora\na proposta é:\n- **B1 Director** chama V3 Bloco 1\n- **B2 Director** coordena OpenClaw/Playwright\n- **B3 Director** chama V3 Bloco 3\n\nIsto é muito mais pragmático.\n\n---\n\n# A fronteira arquitectural mais importante que eu extraio\n\nSe eu condensar tudo numa frase:\n\n**esses docs defendem que a automação actual já contém grande parte da “inteligência correcta”, e que o próximo passo não é refazer tudo em agentes, mas sim reorganizar o sistema para que a agentificação entre apenas onde a natureza da tarefa realmente exige exploração e julgamento visual.**\n\n---\n\n# O que eu compreendo como decisão de arquitectura implícita\n\n## 1. V3 continua a ser o backbone real\nNão é legado morto.  \nÉ substrate operacional activo.\n\n## 2. O erro do auto_content_factory_legacy foi de escopo\nO problema não era a ambição.\nEra **ter escolhido reabrir blocos já resolvidos**.\n\n## 3. O contract entre blocos é o activo mais importante\nOs docs estão fortemente orientados a:\n- input contract\n- output contract\n- invariants\n- ficheiros obrigatórios\n- estrutura de artefactos\n\nOu seja:\n**o sistema novo deve respeitar contratos, não reescrever lógica à toa.**\n\n## 4. O verdadeiro replacement não é “o pipeline inteiro”\nÉ essencialmente:\n- **Bloco 2**\n- e a camada superior de coordenação / monitorização\n\n## 5. OpenClaw faz mais sentido como “executor de capacidades abertas”\ne não como substrate universal para tudo\n\n---\n\n# A minha síntese operacional\n\nSe eu tivesse de traduzir esses docs em direcção prática, eu diria isto:\n\n### O plano certo agora é:\n- **não mexer estruturalmente no Bloco 1**\n- **não reinventar o Bloco 3**\n- **mapear perfeitamente os contratos B1 → B2 → B3**\n- **usar o sistema novo para coordenar o pipeline**\n- **concentrar design agêntico forte no Bloco 2**\n- **tratar browser automation como a nova camada crítica de produção visual**\n\n---\n\n# O que eu acho que tu e o Claude estavam a fazer nesses docs\n\nVocês estavam, na prática, a fazer uma **descompressão conceptual do V3** para responder a uma pergunta estratégica maior:\n\n> “o que realmente precisa ser reconstruído, e o que só precisa ser encapsulado e orquestrado?”\n\nE a resposta implícita dos docs é:\n\n- **reconstruir / reinventar:** Bloco 2 + camada de coordenação\n- **encapsular / preservar:** Bloco 1 + Bloco 3\n\n---\n\n# Minha conclusão mais honesta\n\nEu compreendo estes documentos como uma **correcção de rumo séria**.\n\nEles dizem:\n\n- o V3 já tem muita estrutura boa\n- a dor com S1/OpenClaw foi um sinal de fronteira mal colocada\n- a nova arquitectura deve ser **menos ideológica e mais económica**\n- o centro do problema é visual\n- o centro da solução é **Paperclip + OpenClaw/Playwright no Bloco 2 + wrappers para B1/B3**\n\n## Em linguagem bem directa:\n**a gente não deveria tentar transformar a fábrica inteira em agentes.**\n**a gente deveria usar agentes só onde a fábrica actual ainda não sabe operar bem: o visual.**\n\nSe quiser, no próximo passo eu posso transformar esta leitura em um destes formatos:\n\n1. **“o que eu concordo / o que eu contestaria nesses docs”**\n2. **“arquitectura final recomendada em diagrama textual”**\n3. **“plano de execução por fases sem overengineering”**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fe0a708819093c91d1d55767678\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":54796,"output":2216,"cacheRead":37504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94516,"cost":{"input":0.13699,"output":0.03324,"cacheRead":0.009375999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.179606}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775140829971,"responseId":"resp_04df5a497775ef210169ce7fdee49481909d5ced158a515577"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5635662f","parentId":"8ab7e7e0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:47:51.211Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-02 11:47 GMT-3] Legal que vc entendeu. Eu vou tocar com o Claude code toda a questão do bloco 1 e bloco 3, vamos eu e você nos concentrar aqui naquilo que seria o bloco 2 novo agora com agentes openclaw. Estou confiante que o bloco 2 com openclaw, representa o que estávamos planejando para S3, S4, S5 E S6. C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory_legacy\\docs\\branches da uma olhada no que a gente itnha planejado pra eles antes"}],"timestamp":1775141271198}}
